{"sentences": [{"text": "POLICE SOURCES HAVE REPORTED THAT UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS PLANTED A BOMB IN FRONT OF A MORMON CHURCH IN TALCAHUANO DISTRICT."}, {"text": "THE BOMB, WHICH EXPLODED AND CAUSED PROPERTY DAMAGE WORTH 50,000 PESOS, WAS PLACED AT A CHAPEL OF THE CHURCH OF JESUS CHRIST OF LATTER-DAY SAINTS LOCATED AT NO 3856 GOMEZ CARRENO STREET."}, {"text": "THE SHOCK WAVE DESTROYED A WALL, THE ROOF, AND THE WINDOWS OF THE CHURCH, BUT DID NOT CAUSE ANY INJURIES."}, {"text": "CARABINEROS BOMB SQUAD PERSONNEL IMMEDIATELY WENT TO THE LOCATION AND DISCOVERED THAT THE BOMB WAS MADE OF 50 GRAMS OF AN-FO (AMMONIUM NITRATE-FUEL OIL BLASTING AGENTS) AND A SLOW FUSE."}, {"text": "CARABINEROS SPECIAL FORCES SOON RAIDED A LARGE AREA TO TRY TO ARREST THOSE RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ATTACK, BUT THEY WERE UNSUCCESSFUL."}, {"text": "THE POLICE HAVE ALREADY INFORMED THE APPROPRIATE AUTHORITIES, THAT IS, THE NATIONAL PROSECUTOR AND THE TALCAHUANO CRIMINAL COURT, OF THIS ATTACK."}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "AMINTA PLATERO WAS KILLED WHEN HER CAR WAS HIT BY ANOTHER CAR DRIVEN BY FORMER DEPUTY PUBLIC SECURITY MINISTER RINALDO GOLCHER."}, {"text": "AT THE TIME OF THE ACCIDENT, GOLCHER WAS ACCOMPANIED BY U.S. MILITARY ATTACHE ANGEL MENENDEZ."}, {"text": "THE INCIDENT OCCURRED AT 0100 ON 26 AUGUST AT THE INTERSECTION OF WEST 1ST STREET AND NORTH 51ST AVENUE."}, {"text": "COL GOLCHER WAS SUPPOSEDLY IN ISRAEL WHERE HE WAS SENT AS THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT'S MILITARY ATTACHE; HOWEVER, THE WELL-KNOWN LEADER OF THE DEATH SQUADS WAS SEEN AT 0100 IN DOWNTOWN SAN SALVADOR ACCOMPANIED BY NONE OTHER THAN THE U.S. MILITARY REPRESENTATIVE IN OUR COUNTRY."}, {"text": "THIS HAPPENED ONLY HOURS AFTER COLONEL (ADOLFO ARNOLDO) MAJANO'S BODYGUARDS WERE MURDERED."}, {"text": "THE CIRCUMSTANCES SURROUNDING THIS INCIDENT RAISE SEVERAL QUESTIONS."}, {"text": "WHAT WERE THESE TWO SOLDIERS DOING AT 0100?"}, {"text": "WHERE WERE GOLCHER'S BODYGUARDS?"}, {"text": "WHERE WERE HIS COMPANION'S BODYGUARDS?"}, {"text": "THE TWO MEN WERE PROBABLY RETURNING FROM A CORRUPTION CENTER, A NIGHT CLUB--ONE OF THOSE EXCLUSIVE CLUBS WHERE THE U.S. ADVISERS AND OTHER U.S. AND SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS SPEND THE DOLLARS THEY STEAL FROM THE FUNDS ALLOTTED TO EL SALVADOR AND WHERE THEY PLAN CRIMES AGAINST THE PEOPLE."}, {"text": "MUCH MORE COULD BE SAID; HOWEVER, THE TRUTH IS THAT THE INCIDENT WAS NO MERE ACCIDENT."}, {"text": "MRS PLATERO IS ANOTHER VICTIM OF THE MADNESS AFFECTING AN ARMY DIRECTED BY U.S. ADVISERS."}, {"text": "THERE IS NOT MUCH DIFFERENCE BETWEEN THIS INCIDENT AND THE HURLING OF A GRENADE BY A SOLDIER DRIVEN CRAZY BY THE PSYCHOLOGICAL TERRORISM PRACTICED BY THE ARMY ADVISERS AND CHIEFS."}, {"text": "THERE IS NO DOUBT IN OUR MINDS THAT GOLCHER WILL NOT BE TRIED FOR THIS NEW CRIME, JUST AS HE HAS NOT BEEN TRIED FOR THE MANY CRIMES HE HAS BEEN RESPONSIBLE FOR AS CHIEF OF THE REPRESSIVE CORPS AND DEATH SQUADS."}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "A JUDGE HAS ORDERED THE RELEASE OF FORMER CAPTAIN ALVARO SANABRIA, WHO IS IMPLICATED IN THE ASSASSINATION OF MSGR OSCAR ARNULFO ROMERO, BECAUSE OF CONTRADICTORY STATEMENTS BY A KEY WITNESS."}, {"text": "COURT SOURCES HAVE EXPLAINED, HOWEVER, THAT THE CONSTITUTIONAL COURT WILL NOW HAVE TO DECIDE WHETHER OR NOT TO ACCEPT THE ACQUITTAL OF THE SOLDIER."}, {"text": "THE DECISION ISSUED BY JUSTICE ROMEO AURORA ACQUITTING AND ORDERING THE RELEASE OF THE FORMER CAPTAIN WAS MADE, ACCORDING TO THE DOCUMENT, BECAUSE AMADO ANTONIO GARAY REYES--THE ALLEGED DRIVER OF THE PERSON WHO ASSASSINATED MSGR ROMERO--CANNOT BE CONSIDERED A RELIABLE WITNESS."}, {"text": "THE JUDGEMENT PRESENTED TO THE CONSTITUTIONAL COURT NOTES THAT THIS WITNESS HAS MADE STATEMENTS THAT CONTRADICT TESTIMONY HE GAVE AT THE 4TH CRIMINAL COURT 7 YEARS AFTER THE CRIME WAS COMMITTED."}, {"text": "FOR THIS REASON, THE JUDGE, BASED ON ARTICLES 497 AND 498 OF THE PENAL CODE AND ARTICLE 53 OF THE CONSTITUTIONAL PROCEDURES LAW HAS RULED THAT THERE IS NO MERIT FOR ARRESTING THE MILITARY MAN, WHO HAS BEEN TRIED IN ABSENTIA."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, COURT OFFICIALS HAVE EXPLAINED THAT THIS DOCUMENT ISSUED BY JUDGE AURORA IS ONLY A REPORT ON HIS RULING, WHICH ACCORDING TO THE LAW CAN BE EITHER REVOKED OR CONFIRMED BY THE CONSTITUTIONAL COURT."}, {"text": "FOR THIS REASON, THIS DECISION IS NOT BEING VIEWED AS A FINAL RULING."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0013", "message_template": 1, "message_template_optional": true, "incident_date": {"sentences": [{"text": "BOGOTA INRAVISION TELEVISION CADENA 1 IN SPANISH AT 1730 GMT ON 1 SEPTEMBER BROADCASTS APPROXIMATELY 3 MINUTES OF REPORTS BY NATIONAL POLICE DIRECTOR GENERAL JOSE GUILLERMO MEDINA SANCHEZ, WHO CONFIRMS THAT 15 CIVILIANS WERE KILLED "TUESDAY NIGHT" IN EL TOMATE, CANALETES MUNICIPALITY, CORDOBA DEPARTMENT, BY A GANG "POSSIBLY BELONGING TO THE POPULAR LIBERATION ARMY.""}, {"text": "THE INITIAL REPORT MENTIONS 10 KILLED, BUT GEN MEDINA MENTIONS "12 KILLED, 15 INJURED, AND 26 SHACKS BURNED.""}, {"text": "THE REPORTER ASKS GEN MEDINA IF THOSE WHO WERE KILLED BELONGED TO A CIVIL DEFENSE GROUP, GEN MEDINA SAYS THEY DID NOT."}, {"text": "IN ANOTHER REPORT, WHICH LASTS 1 MINUTE, THE ANNOUNCER SAYS PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO WILL TONIGHT DISCLOSE HIS GOVERNMENT'S PEACE PROPOSAL, WHICH CONTAINS THREE BASIC POINTS: "REGIONAL DIALOGUE, DEMOBILIZATION, HANDING OVER OF WEAPONS, AND PARDON.""}, {"text": "THE REST OF THIS REPORT GIVES THE 40-YEAR BACKGROUND OF VIOLENCE."}, {"text": "NEAR THE END OF THE CAST, THE ANNOUNCER ADDS TO THE INITIAL REPORT ON THE EL TOMATE ATTACK WITH A 3-MINUTE UPDATE THAT ADDS "2 INJURED, 21 HOUSES DESTROYED, AND 1 BUS BURNED.""}, {"text": "REPORTER OSVALDO CASTILLA DESCRIBES VIDEO IMAGES OF HOW THE AREA WAS LEFT."}, {"text": "CASTILLA REPORTS THAT "TUESDAY NIGHT, WHILE RESIDENTS SLEPT OR WATCHED TELEVISION, 30 GUERRILLAS DRESSED IN MILITARY UNIFORMS SET THE SHACKS ON FIRE, INDISCRIMINATELY SHOOTING THOSE WHO RAN FOR THEIR LIVES, WHILE SPRAYING GASOLINE ON OTHERS AND SETTING THEM ON FIRE.""}, {"text": "THE ANNOUNCER SAYS THAT BESIDES THE DEAD, THERE ARE SEVERAL PEOPLE MISSING, AND THAT THE ATTACKERS LEFT SLOGANS PAINTED ON WALLS."}, {"text": "THE ANNOUNCER SAYS THE ATTACK IS THOUGHT TO HAVE BEEN CARRIED OUT BY AN ARMY OF NATIONAL LIBERATION GROUP."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0015", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 01 SEP 88"]}], "incident_location": {"sentences": [{"text": "EARLY THIS MORNING, TWO POWERFUL BOMBS ROCKED SAN SALVADOR'S METROPOLITAN AREA."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO REPORTS, THE BOMBS WERE PLANTED BY FMLN URBAN GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "THE POWERFUL BOMBS WERE PLANTED IN TWO GOVERNMENT VEHICLES, LICENSE PLATES 6906 AND 6895, USED BY THE RURAL BASIC HEALTH PLAN SECTION OF THE HEALTH MINISTRY."}, {"text": "THE DESTROYED CARS WERE PARKED AT FIRST STREET WEST AND 21ST AVENUE NORTH."}, {"text": "THE BOMBS, PLANTED UNDER THE CAR HOODS, SHATTERED THE WINDSHIELDS AND DESTROYED THE CAR BODIES."}, {"text": "STRANGELY ENOUGH, THE REBELS DID NOT LEAVE LEAFLETS, AS IS THEIR CUSTOM."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED) IN A COMMUNIQUE READ THIS AFTERNOON OVER THE PHONE, THE FMLN GENERAL COMMAND CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE DESTRUCTION OF THE TWO VEHICLES."}, {"text": "THEY SAID THIS IS PART OF THE URBAN GUERRILLAS' LATEST CAMPAIGN TO SABOTAGE GOVERNMENT PROPERTY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0016", {"sentences": [{"text": "INTERIOR, MIGRATION, AND JUSTICE MINISTER JUAN CARLOS DURAN HAS SAID THAT SINCE 1985 PRESIDENT VICTOR PAZ ESTENSSORO'S ADMINISTRATION MADE GREAT PROGRESS IN THE STRUGGLE AGAINST DRUG TRAFFICKING FOR THE BENEFIT OF BOLIVIAN SOCIETY."}, {"text": "THE INTERIOR MINISTER SAID THAT THE CURRENT ADMINISTRATION HAS OBTAINED GREAT ACHIEVEMENTS IN ITS STRUGGLE AGAINST DRUG TRAFFIKING BY ELIMINATING 80 PERCENT OF THIS ILLEGAL ACTIVITY."}, {"text": "DURAN SAID THAT DURING PAZ' ADMINISTRATION ABOUT 1,000 PEOPLE CONNECTED WITH DRUG TRAFFICKING HAVE BEEN ARRESTED, 1,000 COCAINE LABORATORIES HAVE BEEN DESTROYED, AND 20 TONS OF DRUGS HAVE BEEN CONFISCATED."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT BOLIVIAN SOCIETY HAS WITNESSED THESE ACHIEVEMENTS AS PART OF THE GOVERNMENT'S EFFORT TO ERADICATE DRUG TRAFFICKING FROM THE NATIONAL TERRITORY."}, {"text": "THE INTERIOR MINISTER EXPRESSED GREAT ANNOYANCE AT AN ARTICLE PUBLISHED BY THE NEWSPAPER EL PAIS, OF MADRID, SPAIN, IN WHICH FELIPE KEMPFF, SON OF THE MURDERED BOLIVIAN SCIENTIST NOEL KEMPFF, ASSERTS THAT THE BOLIVIAN AND U.S. GOVERNMENTS ALLOW THE MANUFACTURING OF COCAINE AND USE THE PROCEDES TO FINANCE THE INTERNATIONAL STRUGGLE AGAINST COMMUNISM."}, {"text": "DURAN SAID: "I WILL ASK THE DISTRICT PROSECUTOR TO SUMMON FELIPE KEMPFF TO COURT IN ORDER TO MAKE HIM TELL EVERYTHING HE KNOWS."}, {"text": "HE MUST SAY TO WHOM THE {"sentences": [{"text": "THREE NEW TERRORIST ATTACKS WERE CARRIED OUT EARLY THIS MORNING, AT AN AIRPORT IN BARRANQUILLA, AT THE COMMUNIST PARTY HEADQUARTERS IN FLORENCIA, AND AT THE CERRO AZUL MILITARY INSTALLATIONS IN URABA."}, {"text": "THE POLICE CONFIRMED THAT UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS ARMED WITH MACHINEGUNS ATTACKED THE COLOMBIAN AIR FORCE INSTALLATIONS IN THE CAPITAL OF ATLANTICO."}, {"text": "THERE WERE NO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "THE MALAMBO AREA, CLOSE TO THE BARRANQUILLA INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, WHERE THE AIR BASE IS LOCATED, WAS IMMEDIATELY MILITARIZED."}, {"text": "GUARDS AT THE SITE REPELLED THE ATTACK, WHICH WAS APPARENTLY STAGED BY GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "SIMILARLY, IT WAS LEARNED THAT A BOMB EXPLODED TODAY AT THE COMMUNIST PARTY HEADQUARTERS IN THE CAPITAL OF CAQUETA, CAUSING CONSIDERABLE PROPERTY DAMAGE."}, {"text": "IT WAS IMMEDIATELY ANNOUNCED THAT NO ONE HAD BEEN INJURED OR KILLED IN THE EXTREMIST ACTION."}, {"text": "IT WAS ALSO ANNOUNCED THAT SUSPECTED SUBVERSIVES STAGED ANOTHER ATTACK ON THE INSTALLATIONS OF THE BATTALION STATIONED IN URABA AT CERRO AZUL, NEAR TURBO."}, {"text": "THESE TERRORIST ATTACKS TOOK PLACE 1 DAY AFTER THE SERIOUS ATTACK LAUNCHED AT THE 2D ARMY DIVISION HEADQUARTERS IN BUCARAMANGA, WHICH RESULTED IN SEVEN PEOPLE INJURED AND CONSIDERABLE PROPERTY DAMAGE, AFFECTING NINE HOMES."}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "A TERRORIST ATTACK, IN WHICH CZECHOSLOVAK BOMBS WERE USED, HAS DESTROYED FOUR HIGH TENSION TOWERS IN THE CENTRAL REGION."}, {"text": "THIS ATTACK HAS CUT THE ELECTRICITY SUPPLY TO A VAST REGION BETWEEN COPIAPO AND SANTIAGO."}, {"text": "THE BLACKOUT OCCURRED ON SATURDAY NIGHT, 1 OCTOBER, AND LASTED FOR APPROXIMATELY ONE-HALF HOUR IN THE METROPOLITAN REGION."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO ENDESA (NATIONAL ELECTRIC POWER, INC.), ONE OF THE TOWERS KNOCKED DOWN WAS LOCATED ON KM 24 OF THE MELIPILLA-RAPEL HIGHWAY."}, {"text": "THE TOWER, LOCATED IN THE MAITENES SECTOR, IS ONE OF THE MAIN TOWERS OF THE HIGH TENSION NETWORK."}, {"text": "ANOTHER TOWER DESTROYED BY THE TERRORISTS WAS TOWER NO 430 IN THE ITAHUA-ALTO JAHUEL SECTOR, WHICH IS CONNECTED TO THE MAIN ELECTRICITY NETWORK."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION TO THESE FOUR DESTROYED TOWERS, OTHER EXPLOSIONS WERE HEARD THAT SAME NIGHT IN SANTIAGO."}, {"text": "THEY WERE CAUSED BY BOMBS PLANTED BY TERRORISTS WHO SEEK TO FRIGHTEN THE POPULATION."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO POLICE SOURCES, THE BOMBS USED TO CAUSE SO MUCH DAMAGE ARE POWERFUL CZECHOSLOVAK-MADE PLASTIC BOMBS, OF THE SAME TYPE THAT WERE FOUND AMONG THE CLANDESTINE ARSENALS SMUGGLED INTO THE COUNTRY BY THE MARXIST LEFTISTS AT CARRIZAL BAJO."}, {"text": "THE TERRORISTS ALSO USED TNT IN THEIR BOMB ATTACKS."}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "AN EXPLOSION HAS DESTROYED A SECTION OF THE MULTIPURPOSE PIPELINE RUNNING FROM BARRANCABERMEJA TO BUCARAMANGA."}, {"text": "THE EXPLOSION OCCURRED IN ALTO DE SAN PABLO WHILE GASOLINE AND PROPANE GAS WERE BEING PUMPED TO BUCARAMANGA."}, {"text": "WE HAVE A REPORT NOW FROM TERESA RUEDA."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (RUEDA) COMMUNICATIONS TO AND FROM PUERTO PETROLERO AND BUCARAMANGA HAVE BEEN CUT OFF SINCE EARLY TODAY, AFTER AN ATTEMPT TO DYNAMITE THE MULTIPURPOSE PIPELINE DESTROYED A 100-METER SECTION OF THE CENTRAL HIGHWAY."}, {"text": "THE SUPPLY OF GAS TO BUCARAMANGA WILL ALSO BE AFFECTED BY THIS EVENT."}, {"text": "IT IS ESTIMATED THAT IT WILL TAKE AT LEAST 3 DAYS TO RESTORE NORMAL TRAFFIC, BECAUSE IT WILL BE NECESSARY TO USE DYNAMITE TO REMOVE ROCKS CURRENTLY BLOCKING THE HIGHWAY."}, {"text": "THE ATTEMPTED SABOTAGE OCCURRED AT THE 65-KM MARK ON THE BUCARAMANGA - BARRANCABERMEJA HIGHWAY, 20 KM FROM THE PLACE WHERE A MILITARY CONVOY WAS AMBUSHED LAST WEDNESDAY."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE SECOND TIME THAT AN ATTEMPTED SABOTAGE OF THE BUCARAMANGA - BARRANCABERMEJA MULTIPURPOSE PIPELINE, WHICH CARRIES PROPANE GAS, GASOLINE, AND ACPM (NOT FURTHER IDENTIFIED) HAS TAKEN PLACE."}, {"text": "THE EXPLOSION DESTROYED A 30-METER SECTION OF PIPELINE, AND SPARKED A FIRE THAT HAS NOT YET BEEN EXTINGUISHED."}, {"text": "LOSSES CAUSED BY THE SABOTAGE, WHICH HAS BEEN ATTRIBUTED TO THE ELN, HAVE YET TO BE ASCERTAINED."}, {"text": "IT IS ESTIMATED THAT REPAIRS TO THE HIGHWAY ALONE WILL COST THE PUBLIC WORKS MINISTRY 5 MILLION PESOS."}, {"text": "(ISMAEL OROZCO, PUBLIC WORKS DIRECTOR FOR THE 5TH DISTRICT) WELL, AFTER INITIAL TALKS WITH ECOPETROL (COLOMBIAN PETROLEUM ENTERPRISE) TECHNICIANS TODAY, BEGINNING AT 1700, AFTER THE FIRE IS UNDER CONTROL, THEY WILL BEGIN RESTORING SERVICE ON THE OIL PIPELINE."}, {"text": "(RUEDA) AT THIS TIME, THERE IS TRAFFIC CONGESTION NEAR THE SUGAMOSO BRIDGE."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) (PASSAGE OMITTED) WHILE STILL ON THE SUBJECT, ECOPETROL'S PRESIDENT, WHO TRAVELED THIS MORNING TO BARRANCABERMEJA TO ATTEND A FORUM ON THE MAGDALENA RIVER, REPORTED THAT, SO FAR THIS YEAR, TERRORIST ATTACKS HAVE COST HIS COMPANY $300 MILLION."}, {"text": "WE HAVE THIS REPORT FROM MARIA CLARA GRACIA."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (GRACIA) ECOPETROL HAS LOST 95 BILLION PESOS IN REVENUES THIS YEAR DUE TO THE 44 TERRORIST ATTACKS ON THE CANO LIMON - COVENAS OIL PIPELINE."}, {"text": "IN THESE ATTACKS, 13.2 MILLION BARRELS OF CRUDE OIL HAVE BEEN LOST."}, {"text": "THE AREAS MOST AFFECTED BY THESE ATTACKS ARE IN SUCRE, ARAUCA, NORTE DE SANTANDER, AND SANTANDER DEPARTMENTS."}, {"text": "(REPORTER ALVARO AYALA) DOCTOR, COULD THESE TERRORIST ATTACKS LEAD TO AN INCREASE IN FUEL PRICES IN COLOMBIA?"}, {"text": "(DR ANDRES RESTREPO LONDONO, PRESIDENT OF ECOPETROL) OBVIOUSLY, THERE WILL COME A TIME WHEN, FACED WITH INCREASING INTERNAL PRODUCTION COSTS AND FALLING REVENUES, WE ARE GOING TO HAVE TO CONSIDER COMPENSATING OUR LOSSES WITH AN INCREASE IN DOMESTIC OIL PRICES, BUT THAT IS A MEASURE WE ARE NOT ABOUT TO ADOPT AT THIS TIME."}, {"text": "(GRACIA) TODAY'S LANDSLIDE, WHICH DESTROYED A SECTION OF THE MULTIPURPOSE PIPELINE BETWEEN BARRANCABERMEJA AND BUCARAMANGA, HAS RESULTED IN ESTIMATED LOSSES TOTALLING 1.435 BILLION PESOS."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED) (END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "IT WAS DISCLOSED IN THIS CAPITAL TODAY THAT A BOMB EXPLODED AT THE FRONT DOOR OF THE HOME OF A PERUVIAN ARMY GENERAL, CAUSING DAMAGES BUT NO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "THE BOMB WENT OFF 48 HOURS AFTER A MEMBER OF THE ARMY SUSTAINED A BULLET WOUND."}, {"text": "THE TERRORIST ATTACK WAS PERPETRATED AT DAWN ON SATURDAY, 9 OCTOBER, BY A GROUP OF UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS WHO HURLED A BOMB AT THE HOME OF GENERAL ENRIQUE FRANCO, IN THE SAN BORJA NEIGHBORHOOD IN LIMA, FROM A PASSING VEHICLE."}, {"text": "THE BOMB SERIOUSLY DAMAGED THE GENERAL'S VEHICLE, DESTROYED HIS HOME'S FRONT DOOR, AND SHATTERED ITS WINDOW PANES, AS WELL AS THOSE OF NEIGHBORING HOUSES."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE LOCAL MEDIA THAT OBTAINED INFORMATION FROM POLICE SOURCES, THE EXPLOSION, HOWEVER, DID NOT HURT ANY OF THE MEMBERS OF THE GENERAL'S FAMILY, WHO WERE SLEEPING AT THE THE TIME."}, {"text": "TWO DAYS AGO, AN ARMY TECHNICIAN, WHO WAS DRIVING HOME, SUSTAINED A BULLET WOUND WHEN A GROUP OF UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS, RIDING IN ANOTHER VEHICLE, FIRED THEIR WEAPONS AT HIM."}, {"text": "THE INCIDENT OCCURRED NEAR LA BANDERA PLAZA IN THE PUEBLO LIBRE DISTRICT OF LIMA."}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "HONDURAN MILITARY SOURCES YESTERDAY REPORTED THAT SEVERAL TIMES IN SEPTEMBER, EPS SOLDIERS ENTERED HONDURAN TERRITORY AND HARASSED THE 6TH INFANTRY BATTALION OBSERVATION POST IN EL PITAL, CIFUENTES, EL PARAISO DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "THE RAIDS INTO HONDURAN TERRITORY AND THE HARASSMENTS OCCURRED AS FOLLOWS: 1. ON 19 AUGUST 1988, EPS TROOPS SET UP COMMUNICATIONS TRACKING EQUIPMENT (RADAR) IN LOMA FRIA, WHICH WAS PROTECTED BY MISSILES AND ANTIAIRCRAFT MACHINEGUNS."}, {"text": "2. ON 21 AUGUST 1988, EPS SOLDIERS KIDNAPPED HONDURAN CITIZENS ROSALIO MEJIA RODRIGUEZ AND HER SON GUILLERMO SAUL MEJIA HERRERA, WHO WERE TAKEN TO NICARAGUAN TERRITORY."}, {"text": "3. ON 6 SEPTEMBER 1988, AN EPS PATROL ENTERED HONDURAN TERRITORY AND HARASSED THE 6TH INFANTRY BATTALION POSTS LOCATED IN EL PITAL, CIFUENTES."}, {"text": "OUR TROOPS RESPONDED TO THEIR FIRE AND SUFFERED NO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "4. ON 9 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS SOLDIERS ATTACKED WITH MACHINEGUN AND MORTAR FIRE THE 9TH INFANTRY BRIGADE BATTALION POST IN CERRO PELON, LA LAMPARA, QUEBRADA DEL ORO, AND TAPALCHI, IN POTECA RIVER, PARAISO."}, {"text": "DURING THE ATTACK, SOLDIER JOSE MARIO CHICAS DIAZ WAS WOUNDED."}, {"text": "OUR TROOPS RESPONDED TO THE FIRE AND REPORTED NO (FURTHER) CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "5. ON 10 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS TROOPS CONTINUED ATTACKING THE SAME 9TH INFANTRY BRIGADE BATTALION POST WITH 50-MM MACHINEGUNS; PATROLS WERE INCREASED AND PERSONNEL AND WEAPONS WERE DEPLOYED TO THE GUAPINOL, COMARCA, PARAISITO, AND COMARCA GUANITO SECTORS, NEAR THE POTECA RIVER."}, {"text": "6. ON 14 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS SOLDIERS HARASSED WITH MACHINEGUN FIRE THE 9TH INFANTRY BRIGADE POST LOCATED IN EL GUINEO AND PUEBLO NUEVO, CIFUENTES."}, {"text": "NO CASUALTIES WERE REPORTED."}, {"text": "7. ON 18 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS SOLDIERS ATTACKED POSITIONS HELD BY THE 9TH INFANTRY BATTALION AT LA CONGOLONA ON THE POTECA RIVER WITH 82 - AND 120-MM MORTARS, RPG-7'S, AND RIFLE FIRE."}, {"text": "THE FIRE WAS RETURNED WITHOUT ANY REPORTED CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "8. ON 19 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS SOLDIERS ATTACKED, WITH MORTARS, RIFLE, AND RPG-7'S, POSITIONS HELD BY THE 6TH INFANTRY BATTALION IN EL PITAL, AND ALSO IN ADUENA VIEJA, GUASAPO, AND CIFUENTES."}, {"text": "OUR TROOPS RETURNED THE FIRE WITHOUT ANY REPORTED CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "9. ON 20 SEPTEMBER 1988, THE EPS FREED HECTOR ROSALES MEJIA RODRIGUEZ AND HIS SON GUILLERMO SAUL MEJIA HERRERA, WHO HAD BEEN KIDNAPPED BY EPS TROOPS ON 21 AUGUST 1988."}, {"text": "10. ON 24 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS TROOPS HARASSAED WITH RIFLE FIRE A 6TH INFANTRY BATTALION POSITION IN ADUANA VIEJA, CIFUENTES, WITHOUT ANY REPORTED CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "11. ON 25 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS TROOPS HARASSED ADUANA CIFUENTES WITH RIFLE FIRE, WITHOUT ANY REPORTED CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "12."}, {"text": "ON 25 SEPTEMBER 1988, EPS TROOPS SHOT A 120-MM MORTAR THAT FELL 75 METERS FROM CASA DE LADRILLO IN CIFUENTES."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0038", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["21 AUG 88"]}], {"sentences": [{"text": "ATTENTION: THE MANUEL JOSE ARCE URBAN COMMAND HAS BRILLIANTLY SABOTAGED A COMMERCIAL BUILDING BELONGING TO THE BOURGEOISIE IN THE ESCALON NEIGHBORHOOD, CAUSING HEAVY ECONOMIC LOSSES TO THE IDLE CLASS."}, {"text": "AT LEAST 37 BUSINESSES WERE DESTROYED."}, {"text": "THE SAME URBAN COMMAND CARRIED OUT OTHER SABOTAGE AT THE (NAME INDISTINCT) PARKING LOT--SPECIFICALLY, IN THE PINK ZONE, OR ACTUALLY IN WHAT SHOULD BE CALLED THE RED ZONE."}, {"text": "OTHER SABOTAGE TOOK PLACE AT THE LANCER MOTEL NEAR APOPA."}, {"text": "IN A COMMUNIQUE, THE MANUEL JOSE ARCE URBAN COMMAND STATES THAT ON 15 SEPTEMBER, A LENGTHY ORGANIZATIONAL PROCESS TO CREATE A NEW POLITICAL-MILITARY GROUP--IN WHICH 25 DELEGATIONS REPRESENTING NEIGHBORHOOD COMMANDS PARTICIPATED--ENDED WITH THE ESTABLISHMENT OF THE MANUEL JOSE ARCE URBAN COMMAND."}, {"text": "THE COMMUNIQUE WARNS THE ARMY HIGH COMMAND, ITS OFFICERS, CHRISTIAN DEMOCRATIC AND ARENA (NATIONALIST REPUBLICAN ALLIANCE) OFFICIALS, AND U.S. ADVISERS THAT THE MANUEL JOSE ARCE URBAN COMMAND IS A WEAPON THAT WILL BE USED AGAINST THEM WHEREVER THEY MAY BE--AT HOME, WORK, AND AT RECREATION AND CORRUPTION CENTERS."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION, THEIR PROPERTY HAS BEEN DECLARED PERMAMENT MILITARY TARGETS UNTIL THEY STOP THE BLOODSHED AGAINST THE PEOPLE."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED) IN THE PAST FEW HOURS, THE FMLN'S PEDRO PABLO CASTILLO URBAN COMMAND EXECUTED AN AIR FORCE OFFICER AS PART OF THE "MURDER THE CRIMINALS" OPERATION AGAINST REPRESSION, THE MASSACRE IN SAN VICENTE, AND THE PERSECUTION OF THE UNIVERSITY COMMUNITY."}, {"text": "THE EXECUTION OF AN AIR FORCE PILOT OFFICER WAS CARRIED OUT IN SAN SALVADOR'S LAS BRISAS NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "WE CAN IMAGINE THE HAPPINESS OF OUR PEOPLE UPON HEARING THE NEWS THAT ONE OF THE CRIMINALS AMONG CRIMINALS--THAT IS, ONE OF THE PILOTS WHO HAVE BOMBED VILLAGES AND CANTONS THROUGHOUT OUR FATHERLAND--WAS KILLED AS A RESULT OF REVOLUTIONARY JUSTICE."}, {"text": "FROM NOW ON, BOMBS WILL NOT ONLY EXPLODE IN THE VILLAGES OF CHALATENANGO, CABANAS, USULUTAN, MORAZAN, AND NORTHERN SAN MIGUEL; MORE POWERFUL BOMBS WILL NOW EXPLODE MORE FREQUENTLY IN THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS, THAT IS, IN THE NEIGHBORHOODS OF THE RICH, IN THEIR RECREATION CENTERS, MANSIONS, AND WHEREVER ELSE THEY MAY GO."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0040", {"sentences": [{"text": "ACCORDING TO MILITARY SOURCES, A BLOODY GUERRRILLA OFFENSIVE TODAY LEFT 35 GUERRILLAS AND 5 SOLDIERS DEAD, 6 CIVILIANS WOUNDED, AND 5 BRIDGES PARTIALLY DESTROYED."}, {"text": "THE OUTBREAK OF THE VIOLENCE COINCIDED WITH THE REPLY FROM ALL THE REBEL GROUPS TO AN OFFICIAL PEACE PLAN AND WITH THE CONFIRMATION BY THE LABOR FEDERATIONS THAT THEY WILL HOLD A GENERAL STRIKE ON THURSDAY DESPITE GOVERNMENT EFFORTS TO PREVENT IT."}, {"text": "THE SO-CALLED NATIONAL GUERRILLA COORDINATING BOARD (CNG) PROPOSED TO PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO THE HOLDING OF A SUMMIT BETWEEN THE REBEL LEADERS AND THE GOVERNMENT, DEFENSE, AND ENERGY AND MINES MINISTERS AT A PLACE AND DATE TO BE AGREED UPON."}, {"text": "THE DOCUMENT PROPOSED THAT THE MEDIATOR OF THE DIALOGUE BE THE DEMOCRATIC COEXISTENCE COMMISSION (COMISION DE CONVIVENCIA DEMOCRATICA), HEADED BY MSGR DARIO CASTRILLON, PRESIDENT OF THE LATIN AMERICAN BISHOPS CONFERENCE."}, {"text": "THE DOCUMENT IS VIEWED AS THE CNG'S OFFICIAL REPLY TO THE GOVERNMENT'S PEACE PLAN."}, {"text": "GUERRILLAS OF THE FARC AND THE POPULAR LIBERATION ARMY (EPL) ATTACKED FOUR TOWNS IN NORTHERN COLOMBIA, LEAVING 17 GUERRILLAS AND 2 SOLDIERS DEAD AND 3 BRIDGES PARTIALLY DESTROYED."}, {"text": "THE DEFENSE MINISTRY REPORTED THAT FARC GUERRILLAS AMBUSHED A MILITARY CONVOY IN HUILA DEPARTMENT, KILLING THREE SOLDIERS."}, {"text": "IT ALSO REPORTED THAT THREE REBELS WERE KILLED IN CLASHES IN SOUTHERN COLOMBIA."}, {"text": "IT ADDED THAT NINE GUERRILLAS OF THE ARMY OF NATIONAL LIBERATION WERE KILLED IN CLASHES WITH TROOPS OF THE 4TH INFANTRY BRIGADE ON THE BORDER OF ANTIOQUIA AND CHOCO DEPARTMENTS AND THAT SIX FARC REBELS WERE KILLED IN CAQUETA DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "SUSPECTED GUERRILLAS DYNAMITED AT DUSK A BRIDGE IN BOGOTA'S URBAN CENTER, INJURING SIX PEOPLE."}, {"text": "THE BRIDGE DID NOT SUSTAIN MAJOR DAMAGE."}, {"text": "ANOTHER BRIDGE WAS BLOWN UP IN SANTANDER DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "MILITARY SOURCES SAID THESE WERE REBEL ACTIONS IN SUPPORT OF THE STRIKE AND THEY CHARGED THAT WORKERS, PEASANTS, AND BUS DRIVERS ARE BEING THREATENED TO FORCE THEM TO JOIN THE STRIKE."}, {"text": "PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO HEADED A MEETING OF THE NATIONAL SECURITY COUNCIL TO ADOPT MEASURES TO PREVENT DISORDERS DURING THE PLANNED STRIKE AND TO GUARANTEE PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION FOR THE PEOPLE."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT AND THE WORKERS YESTERDAY BROKE OFF THEIR TALKS AFTER BEING UNABLE TO REACH AGREEMENT ON AN INCREASE OF THE MINIMUM WAGE AND ON A FREEZE IN THE PRICES OF STAPLES."}, {"text": "THE STRIKE, CALLED BY THE UNITED WORKERS CONFEDERATION AND THE GENERAL CONFEDERATION OF LABOR, WILL PROTEST THE FACT THAT THE GOVERNMENT HAS NOT REPLIED TO LABOR DEMANDS THEY PRESENTED IN MAY."}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "ACCORDING TO MILITARY SOURCES, A BLOODY GUERRRILLA OFFENSIVE TODAY LEFT 35 GUERRILLAS AND 5 SOLDIERS DEAD, 6 CIVILIANS WOUNDED, AND 5 BRIDGES PARTIALLY DESTROYED."}, {"text": "THE OUTBREAK OF THE VIOLENCE COINCIDED WITH THE REPLY FROM ALL THE REBEL GROUPS TO AN OFFICIAL PEACE PLAN AND WITH THE CONFIRMATION BY THE LABOR FEDERATIONS THAT THEY WILL HOLD A GENERAL STRIKE ON MEETING OF THE NATIONAL SECURITY COUNCIL TO ADOPT MEASURES TO PREVENT DISORDERS DURING THE PLANNED STRIKE AND TO GUARANTEE PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION FOR THE PEOPLE."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT AND THE {"sentences": [{"text": "THE MANUEL RODRIGUEZ PATRIOTIC FRONT (FPMR) WILL DEVELOP A NEW FORM OF STRUGGLE CALLED THE "NATIONAL PATRIOTIC WAR," "WHICH WILL START AT ANY MOMENT.""}, {"text": "THIS INFORMATION WAS DISCLOSED YESTERDAY TO EL MERCURIO BY FPMR SPOKESMAN VICTOR DIAZ CARO, WHO SAID THAT THE TRUCE DURING THE PLEBISCITE WAS TO PREPARE THE PHASE THEY ARE NOW STARTING."}, {"text": "HE ALSO CONFIRMED THE STATEMENT IN BRUSSELS THIS WEEK BY FPMR INTERNATIONAL SPOKESMAN MARCELO REYES."}, {"text": "DIAZ CARO, WHO HAS CONFESSED TO BEING ONE OF THE SNIPERS WHO PARTICIPATED IN THE ATTACK ON PRESIDENT AUGUSTO PINOCHET, IS CURRENTLY UNDER ARREST IN THE SANTIAGO PRISON, AND, TOGETHER WITH VASILY CARILLO NOVA, HE IS NATIONAL SPOKESMAN FOR ONE OF THE FACTIONS OF THIS EXTREMIST ORGANIZATION."}, {"text": "DIAZ CARO, WHO WAS ARRESTED IN LATE 1986 BY THE POLICE, ANNOUNCED THAT IN "A MATTER OF HOURS" THEY WILL START SUBVERSIVE ACTIONS."}, {"text": "HE EXPLAINED THAT THIS NEW PHASE OF ARMED STRUGGLE WILL BE CARRIED OUT "FROM ARICA DOWN TO MAGALLANES.""}, {"text": "AT THE SAME TIME HE REFERRED TO THE RESULTS OF THE PLEBISCITE, STATING THAT ALTHOUGH THEY RESPECT THOSE WHO VOTED "NO," "THE ONLY ASPECT OF THE VICTORY OF THE `NO' WE ACCEPT IS THAT PINOCHET LEAVE POWER.""}, {"text": "IN REFERRING TO THE FPMR'S CHANGE OF STRATEGY, DIAZ CARO DISCLOSED THAT THE DECISION WAS MADE DURING A MEETING OF THE ORGANIZATION'S LEADERS LAST APRIL."}, {"text": "OF THIS OCCASION THEY DISCUSSED THE LINE THAT THE TERRORIST ORGANIZATION SHOULD FOLLOW."}, {"text": "THEY ALSO DECIDED TO GIVE UP THE IDEA OF AN "ARMED REBELLION," WHICH PREVAILED UNTIL THEN."}, {"text": "THE MAIN CHARACTERISTIC OF THAT IDEA WAS THAT THE ORGANIZATION SERVED TO COMPLEMENT CLASS STRUGGLE (AS IT DID IN ITS ORIGIN IN 1983), TO SUPPORT THE PEOPLE'S REBELLION TO PARALYZE THE COUNTRY AND TO PERPETRATE ATTACKS AGAINST THE ESTABLISHED REGIME."}, {"text": "DIAZ CARO DISCLOSED THAT DURING THE MEETING THEY DECIDED TO REPLACE THE REBELLION WITH THE SEARCH FOR A PATRIOTIC UNITY GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT "WE REALIZE THAT OUSTING THE REGIME IS SUBJECT TO NEGOTIATIONS UNDER A PROVINCIAL GOVERNMENT.""}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO DIAZ CARO THIS IS WHEN THEY REALIZED THE "NEED FOR A `TRUCE' BECAUSE THEY NEEDED TO PLAN GREATER STEPS.""}, {"text": "HE ADDED THAT "THIS IS WHEN WHAT WE CALL THE `NATIONAL PATRIOTIC WAR' SURFACED."}, {"text": "THE MAIN ISSUE OF THIS WAR IS THE ARMED STRUGGLE; WE ARE NO LONGER A MERE COMPLEMENT TO THE PEOPLE."}, {"text": "IT REPRESENTS A QUALITATIVE STEP FORWARD AND ENTAILS GREATER RESPONSIBILITIES.""}, {"text": "DIAZ CARO DISCLOSED THAT THIS NEW PHASE WILL REQUIRE A GREATER QUANTITY OF WEAPONS, MORE MEN, AND ALL THE SUPPORT NECESSARY TO OPERATE."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT THE MONTHS OF TRUCE WERE USED TO FULFILL THESE NEEDS."}, {"text": "THE SPOKESMAN ADDED THAT DURING THE MEETING THEY ALSO DECIDED ON THE NEED TO ESTABLISH A NON-ISOLATED ACTION."}, {"text": ""WE THOUGHT THAT ACTIONS IN SANTIAGO, CONCEPCION, AND VALPARAISO WOULD BE THE SOLUTION, BUT THAT WAS NOT THE CASE.""}, {"text": "DIAZ CARO EXPLAINED THAT "THIS IS WHY WE NOW REALIZE THAT THE STRUGGLE SHOULD BE CARRIED OUT FROM ARICA DOWN TO MAGALLANES, THROUGHOUT THE TERRITORY AND IN VARIOUS FORMS.""}, {"text": "(CONTINUED)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0044", {"sentences": [{"text": "DO YOU HAVE ANY COMMENTS ON THE AMNESTY INTERNATIONAL REPORT, WHICH CLAIMS THAT THE ARMED FORCES ARE INVOLVED IN THE MURDER OF CERTAIN SALVADORAN CITIZENS?"}, {"text": "(DUARTE) I UNDERSTAND THAT AMNESTY INTERNATIONAL HAS TO PREPARE A REPORT EVERY YEAR, AND THE ORGANIZATION INCLUDES WHATEVER VIEWS IT CHOOSES IN THE REPORT."}, {"text": "THE ORGANIZATION OBVIOUSLY STATES ITS VIEWS IN THE REPORT."}, {"text": "SALVADORANS DO THINGS ACCORDING TO THE LAW."}, {"text": "IF ANY SALVADORAN OR FOREIGNER HAS EVIDENCE (OF HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATIONS), THEN IT SHOULD BE BROUGHT BEFORE THE COURTS."}, {"text": "THAT IS THE LOGICAL AND LEGAL WAY FOR US TO BEGIN AN INVESTIGATION; THAT IS WHAT WE ALWAYS DO IN ALL SUCH CASES."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "MR PRESIDENT, YOUR GOVERNMENT HAS ISSUED A SPECIAL REPORT CLAIMING THAT SOME DEATH SQUAD MEMBERS HAVE DESERTED AND IMPLICATED SEVERAL RIGHT-WING MEMBERS IN THE MURDER OF MSGR OSCAR ARNULFO ROMERO AND OTHER SALVADORANS."}, {"text": "(DUARTE) WE ARE ANALYZING THE AVAILABLE EVIDENCE IN THOSE CASES."}, {"text": "YOU KNOW THAT I HAVE CAREFULLY ANALYZED THE CASES."}, {"text": "I RELEASED INFORMATION ONLY WHEN THE EVIDENCE WAS DULY INVESTIGATED AND CORROBORATED."}, {"text": "WE ARE PROCESSING A SIZABLE AMOUNT OF INFORMATION, BUT I DO NOT WANT TO DISCUSS IT IN DETAIL BECAUSE I BELIEVE THAT THIS WOULD HINDER THE INVESTIGATION."}, {"text": "(REPORTER) IS IT TRUE THAT YOU HAVE TWO VIDEO RECORDINGS IN WHICH THE TWO DESERTERS GIVE THEIR NAMES AND DETAILS AND THAT THESE RECORDINGS ARE BEING ANALYZED BY MILITARY INTELLIGENCE SERVICES AND THE GOVERNMENT?"}, {"text": "(DUARTE) WE ARE CURRENTLY INVESTIGATING THE CASE."}, {"text": "THAT IS WHY I SAID THAT I WOULD NOT LIKE TO REVEAL ANY DETAILED INFORMATION--BECAUSE THIS MIGHT HINDER THE INVESTIGATION."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "MR PRESIDENT, THE AMNESTY INTERNATIONAL REPORT STATES THAT DEATH SQUADS--WHICH ARE REPORTEDLY COMPOSED OF SOLDIERS AND POLICEMEN--ARE BEING REACTIVATED AT A TIME WHEN THE ARMED FORCES OPPOSE YOUR POLICIES."}, {"text": "(DUARTE) I DO NOT THINK SO."}, {"text": "MY GOVERNMENT'S POLICY REMAINS UNCHANGED."}, {"text": "WE ADVOCATE THE DEFENSE OF HUMAN RIGHTS AND DEMOCRACY."}, {"text": "I THINK THIS IS ALWAYS EVIDENT."}, {"text": "EVERY DAY THIS IS DEMONSTRATED BY EVENTS."}, {"text": "(WORDS INDISTINCT) FILM ABOUT GUERRILLA COMMANDERS, WHICH REPRESENTS SUPPORT FOR THE FMLN AND DISTORTS THE PEOPLE'S VIEWS."}, {"text": "NEVERTHELESS, WE KNOW THAT FREEDOM OF THE PRESS MUST PREVAIL AND THEREFORE WE DO NOT INTERVENE."}, {"text": "YOU WILL NOT FIND ANOTHER COUNTRY THAT DOES THIS, YET WE ARE DOING SO BECAUSE WE BELIEVE THAT WE SHOULD DEFEND FREEDOM OF THE PRESS ABOVE ALL."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "HOW MUCH CREDENCE DO YOU GIVE THE AMNESTY INTERNATIONAL REPORT?"}, {"text": "(DUARTE) THE REPORT IS VALID INSOFAR AS THE FACTS ARE ALL THERE."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, I (WORDS INDISTINCT) THE WAY IN WHICH THE FACTS ARE INTERPRETED."}, {"text": "THE FACTS ARE INTERPRETED ACCORDING TO AMNESTY INTERNATIONAL'S OWN (WORD INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "WE ALSO RECEIVED REPORTS FROM RED CROSS INTERNATIONAL (WORDS INDISTINCT) EACH CASE."}, {"text": "EACH CASE IS INTERPRETED DIFFERENTLY."}, {"text": "THE UNITED NATIONS HAS ITS OWN OPINION; THE OAS HAS ITS OWN OPINION."}, {"text": "EACH ONE ISSUES A REPORT, AND WE USE THAT INFORMATION AS THE BASIS FOR OUR INVESTIGATIONS ON HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATIONS, WHICH IS THE MAIN ISSUE."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "NICARAGUAN PRESIDENT DANIEL ORTEGA TODAY RELEASED A PROVISIONAL REPORT ON THE DAMAGE CAUSED BY HURRICANE JOAN AND ANNOUNCED AN "IMMINENT CONTRA" ATTACK AGAINST NICARAGUA."}, {"text": "ACCOMPANIED BY FIVE FSLN NATIONAL DIRECTORATE COMMANDERS--HUMBERTO ORTEGA, BAYARDO ARCE, VICTOR TIRADO, CARLOS NUNEZ, AND TOMAS BORGE--AND MEMBERS OF HIS CABINET, ORTEGA ADDRESSED MEMBERS OF THE DIPLOMATIC CORPS ACCREDITED IN NICARAGUA AND THE FOREIGN PRESS TO REQUEST MORE INTERNATIONAL AID FOR THE NICARAGUANS AFFECTED BY HURRICANE JOAN."}, {"text": "ORTEGA ALSO ASKED THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY FOR ITS MEDIATION IN LIGHT OF A NEW ATTACK BY 3,000 "CONTRAS" WHO, ACCORDING TO ORTEGA, ARE AT THE HONDURAN BORDER READY TO LAUNCH AN ATTACK AGAINST HIS PEOPLE "IN THIS DIFFICULT TIME.""}, {"text": ""THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY MUST DEMAND THAT THE U.S. GOVERNMENT FORGET ITS PLAN TO ATTACK NICARAGUA."}, {"text": "THE CONTRAS HAVE BEEN EQUIPPED BY THE REAGAN ADMINISTRATION AND ARE READY TO ATTACK AT ANY MOMENT," THE NICARAGUAN PRESIDENT ADDED."}, {"text": ""WE KNOW THAT THE REBELS HAVE BEEN ORDERED TO HINDER THE RECONSTRUCTION WORK THAT IS BEING DONE TO HELP THE PEOPLE AFFECTED BY THE HURRICANE."}, {"text": "THEY HAVE ALSO BEEN ORDERED TO SABOTAGE THE COFFEE HARVEST ACTIVITIES."}, {"text": "THE BIGGEST HELP THE YANKEE GOVERNMENT COULD GIVE THE NICARAGUAN PEOPLE WOULD BE TO STOP THE ATTACK," THE PRESIDENT STRESSED."}, {"text": "ORTEGA ANNOUNCED THAT WHILE HIS COUNTRY WAS BEING HIT BY HURRICANE JOAN, THE CONTRAS CARRIED OUT ATTACKS AND KILLED FIVE CIVILIANS."}, {"text": "REGARDING THE DAMAGE CAUSED BY THE HURRICANE, ORTEGA SAID THAT THIS COMING WEEK, AN ECLA TEAM WILL ARRIVE IN MANAGUA TO MAKE "FINAL" EVALUATIONS ON THE DAMAGE CAUSED BY JOAN LAST WEEK."}, {"text": "INTERNATIONAL AID "IS NECESSARY AND URGENT BECAUSE THE SITUATION IS CHAOTIC," ORTEGA ADDED, STRESSING THE ROLE PLAYED BY CUBA IN HELPING HIS PEOPLE."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT CUBA SENT 24 PLANES TO NICARAGUA WITH FOOD, MEDICINE, AND MEDICAL TEAMS; MEXICO SENT 2 PLANES; AND SPAIN, GREAT BRITAIN, PANAMA, AND BELGIUM EACH SENT ONE; FOR A TOTAL OF 2,052 TONS OF AID."}, {"text": "GIVING A PROVISIONAL REPORT ON THE DAMAGE, ORTEGA SAID THERE WERE 116 DEAD, 178 INJURED, 110 MISSING, AND 29,152 HOUSES DESTROYED AS WELL AS DAMAGE TO AGRICULTURE AND FISHING."}, {"text": "HE STRESSED THE DAMAGE TO THE ECOLOGY BECAUSE THOUSANDS OF HECTARES OF FOREST WERE DESTROYED."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT EUROPEAN TECHNICIANS WILL TRAVEL TO NICARAGUA NEXT WEEK TO EVALUATE THE DAMAGE."}, {"text": "ORTEGA SAID THAT TO FACE THE HURRICANE, THE COUNTRY USED THE DEFENSE SYSTEM IT WOULD USE TO REPEL A MILITARY ATTACK AND THAT THANKS TO THIS, MANY HUMAN LIVES WERE SAVED."}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "THE SECOND MEETING OF THE SO-CALLED GROUP OF EIGHT CONCLUDED TODAY IN PUNTA DEL ESTE, URUGUAY."}, {"text": "AFTER THE URUGUAY DECLARATION WAS SIGNED, THE PRESIDENTS HOSTED A NEWS CONFERENCE."}, {"text": "COLOMBIAN PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO ANSWERED A URUGUAYAN JOURNALIST'S QUESTION ON THE CURRENT SITUATION IN OUR COUNTRY: (BEGIN RECORDING) (REPORTER)"}, {"text": "THE SITUATION IN YOUR COUNTRY IS VERY SERIOUS."}, {"text": "THOUSANDS ARE DEAD, PARAMILITARY DEATH SQUADS GO UNPUNISHED DESPITE THEIR MURDERS OF PATRIOTIC UNION (UP) MEMBERS AND POPULARLY ELECTED {"sentences": [{"text": "THE MOVEMENT OF THE REVOLUTIONARY LEFT (MIR) HAS DECIDED THAT IN THE NEXT FEW MONTHS IT WILL CARRY OUT "A STRUGGLE OF THE MASSES" TO DESTABILIZE THE MILITARY REGIME BY "ALL FORMS OF STRUGGLE.""}, {"text": "THE MIR REJECTED THE STRATEGY OF DIALOGUE ADVOCATED BY THE OPPOSITION'S DEMOCRATIC SECTORS."}, {"text": "THE MIR ADDED THAT IT WILL "TAKE ADVANTAGE OF ANY SITUATION" AND THAT IT WILL USE THE ELECTORAL PROCESS BY REGISTERING A LEFTIST PARTY."}, {"text": "MIR SPOKESMAN JECAR NEGHME TALKED TO THE PRESS YESTERDAY ABOUT THE RESOLUTIONS APPROVED AT THE LATEST MIR CENTRAL COMMITTEE MEETING HELD ON 6 AND 7 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT IT WAS THE FIRST MEETING HELD IN CHILE SINCE JULY 1973."}, {"text": "NEGHME STATED THAT IN ADDITION TO POLITICAL ISSUES, THE CENTRAL COMMITTEE ALSO PAID HOMAGE TO RAUL PELLEGRIN AND CECILIA MAGNI, MEMBERS OF THE MANUEL RODRIGUEZ PATRIOTIC FRONT WHO WERE KILLED RECENTLY."}, {"text": "IN A PUBLIC COMMUNIQUE, THE MIR CRITICIZED THE OPPOSITION PARTIES FOR "NOT LISTENING TO THE NATIONAL CLAMOR FOR PINOCHET'S RESIGNATION" AND FOR GIVING PRIORITY TO "A STRATEGY OF SHADY DEALS AT THE TOP LEVEL.""}, {"text": "THE COMMUNIQUE ADDS: "ALTHOUGH THE DOCUMENT RELEASED BY THE 16 POLITICAL PARTIES FOCUSES ON SOME OF THE PEOPLE'S DEMANDS, ITS MAIN DEFECT IS THAT BY INCLUDING THE DEMANDS AS PART OF A NEGOTIATING STRATEGY AND BY MAKING THE MOBILIZATION TASKS UNCLEAR, THE DEMANDS OF THE CHILEAN PEOPLE WILL NOT BE HEARD.""}, {"text": "THE MIR ALSO SAID THAT NEXT YEAR IT WILL STRUGGLE FOR THE IMMEDIATE END OF THE REGIME AND THE CONSTITUTION, THE CREATION OF A PROVISIONAL GOVERNMENT, THE ELECTION OF A CONSTITUENT ASSEMBLY, THE STRENGTHENING OF THE UNITED LEFT, AND THE PREPARATION OF A "DEMOCRATIC AND POPULAR PROGRAM" FOR THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "THE COMMUNIQUE SAYS THAT TO ACHIEVE THOSE GOALS THE MIR WILL PROMOTE A TACTIC "TO DESTABILIZE THE REGIME, TO MAKE THE INSTITUTIONS ILLEGITIMATE, TO DEMOCRATIZE THE COUNTRY, AND TO ACCUMULATE GREATER FORCE.""}, {"text": "THE COMMUNIQUE ALSO POINTS OUT THAT THE MIR WILL USE "THE LIMITED POSSIBILITY OF PARTICIPATING IN ELECTIONS BEGINNING IN 1988.""}, {"text": REQUESTED COORDINATED ACTIONS BY THE TWO COUNTRIES TO PREVENT SUCH BORDER INCIDENTS."}, {"text": "IT WAS ADMITTED THAT THE REMAINS OF THE FISHERMEN WERE EXHUMED OVER THE WEEKEND."}, {"text": "SEVEN OF THEM WERE EXHUMED ON 26 NOVEMBER AND SIX ON 27 NOVEMBER IN VENEZUELA."}, {"text": "THE JUDICIAL REPORT STATED THAT THERE WERE NO GUERRILLA CLASHES AND THAT EACH WAS KILLED BY A COUP DE GRACE OF THE VENEZUELAN ARMY."}, {"text": "THE VENEZUELAN INVESTIGATIVE COMMISSION ENTRUSTED WITH CLARIFYING THE VENEZUELAN MILITARY AUTHORITIES' REASONS FOR SLAUGHTERING 14 FISHERMEN ON 22 OCTOBER IN EL AMPARO DIRECTLY INVOLVE THE SECURITY ORGANIZATIONS."}, {"text": "THE AUTOPSIES PERFORMED ON NINE BODIES HAVE ESTABLISHED THAT THE PEASANTS OF THE BORDER AREA DID NOT HAVE AN ARMED CLASH WITH THE MILITARY."}, {"text": "ON THE CONTRARY, THEY WERE SHOT AT A DISTANCE LESS THAN 1 METER, WHICH IS WHAT THE TWO SURVIVORS SAID FROM THE BEGINNING."}, {"text": "THOSE SURVIVORS HAVE NOW REQUESTED ASYLUM IN CARACAS FROM THE MEXICAN GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (LONDONO) WE HOPE SUCH INCIDENTS WILL DECREASE AND THAT THE VENEZUELAN AUTHORITIES ALONG THE BORDER WILL COORDINATE WITH THE COLOMBIAN CIVILIAN AND MILITARY AUTHORITIES ANY ACTIONS FOR PRESERVING--NOT ONLY THE LIVES OF THE COLOMBIANS ON EITHER SIDE OF THE BORDER--PEACE AND TRANQUILLITY IN THE BORDER AREA."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) BECAUSE 2 OF THE 14 MURDERED FISHERMEN WERE COLOMBIANS, LONDONO PAREDES STATED THAT THE GOVERNMENT WILL MAINTAIN ITS INITIAL STAND OF DEMANDING COMPENSATION FOR THE RELATIVES OF THE DEAD COLOMBIANS."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT WILL ALSO AWAIT AN OFFICIAL NOTIFICATION FROM VENEZUELA ON THE RESULTS OF THE INVESTIGATIONS ON THE EL AMPARO SLAUGHTER."}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "COLONEL MAURICIO ERNESTO VARGAS, COMMANDER OF THE ARMY'S 3D BRIGADE IN SAN MIGUEL, HAS STATED THAT THE ARMED FORCES IS NOT INVOLVED IN DEATH SQUAD ACTIONS AND THAT SUCH ACTIONS ARE CONTRARY TO THE INSTITUTION'S REGULATIONS."}, {"text": "VARGAS WAS REFERRING SPECIFICALLY TO THE MURDER OF THREE PEASANTS IN MORAZAN, OF WHICH THE ARMY IS BEING ACCUSED: (BEGIN RECORDING) (VARGAS) OUR VALUES AND THE VALUES OF THE SYSTEM WE DEFEND DO NOT ALLOW US TO EXECUTE, KIDNAP, OR STEAL."}, {"text": "THE SYSTEM STATES WE ARE TO COMPLY WITH OUR LAWS AND LET THE RESPONSIBLE INSTITUTIONS DETERMINE GUILT OR INNOCENCE."}, {"text": "WE CANNOT BE JUDGE AND JURY IN SUCH SITUATIONS."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) THE MOST RECENT CASE FOR WHICH THE ARMY IS BEING BLAMED IS THE MURDER OF THREE PEASANTS IN YAMABAL CANTON, MORAZAN, ON 12 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "VARGAS DENIED ARMED FORCES COMPLICITY IN THESE MURDERS AND STATED THAT HUMANITARIAN ORGANIZATIONS MUST INVESTIGATE IN CASES OF THIS NATURE SO THEY CAN PRESENT EVIDENCE AND ACCUSE A SPECIFIC SECTOR."}, {"text": "HE ADDED THAT HE HAS EVIDENCE THE ARMY WAS NOT PRESENT IN YAMABAL CANTON ON THE DAY OF THE TRIPLE MURDER: (BEGIN RECORDING) (VARGAS)"}, {"text": "I DIRECTLY ACCUSE THE FMLN AND TELL THE HUMANITARIAN ORGANIZATIONS THAT ARE ACCUSING THE ARMED FORCES TO INVESTIGATE THE FMLN."}, {"text": "THE HUMANITARIAN ORGANIZATIONS MUST NOT ACCEPT DIALECTIC CONCLUSIONS SUCH AS THE ONES MADE BY THE CRIMINAL JOAQUIN VILLALOBOS, WHO SAID WE EXECUTED AND (WORDS INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "THEY ARE NOT GOD."}, {"text": "THEY TALK AS IF THE WORLD BELONGED TO THEM."}, {"text": "THERE ARE LAWS AND A LEGAL FRAMEWORK IN THIS COUNTRY."}, {"text": "OUR SYSTEM HAS A LEGAL FRAMEWORK, AND WE HAVE TO BASE OURSELVES ON IT."}, {"text": "THERE ARE HUMANITARIAN ORGANIZATIONS THAT HAVE BECOME CORRUPT AND HAVE BECOME ACCOMPLICES OF THE FMLN'S MURDER; THEY REMAIN SILENT AND DO NOT DEFEND JUSTICE, LAWS, AND PRINCIPLES."}, {"text": "REGARDING THIS CASE, I ACCUSE THE FMLN OF THESE DEATHS."}, {"text": "WE HAVE EVIDENCE THE FMLN IS RESPONSIBLE FOR THE ACTS PRESENTLY BEING REPORTED IN THE NORTHWESTERN ZONE."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) COL VARGAS ALSO CRITICIZED THE WORK DONE BY SOME HUMANITARIAN ORGNIZATIONS AND SAID THEY USE HUMAN RIGHTS AS AN EXCUSE TO PROTECT SECTORS THAT SHARE THEIR IDEOLOGY."}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "TWENTY-SIX PEOPLE, FOUR OF WHOM ARE POLICEMEN, WERE INJURED IN A BOMB EXPLOSION THAT OCCURRED BEFORE DAWN ON 30 OCTOBER."}, {"text": "THE BOMB WAS PLACED IN A DANCE HALL IN AYACUCHO, A CITY LOCATED SOUTH OF LIMA."}, {"text": "THE LOCAL PRESS TODAY REPORTED THAT THE POLICE HAVE ATTRIBUTED THE ATTACK TO TERRORISTS WHO USED A HOME-MADE BOMB CALLED "RUSSIAN CHEESE.""}, {"text": "THIS BOMB IS MADE UP OF POWDER, TACKS, PIECES OF IRON, AND STEEL WIRE."}, {"text": "IT EXPLODES WHEN IT TOUCHES THE FLOOR."}, {"text": "AYACUCHO WAS THE SITE OF A SIMILAR EXPLOSION ON 3 JULY WHEN SEVERAL UNIDENTIFIED PEOPLE HURLED EXPLOSIVES AT A DANCE HALL WHERE THE MUSIC GROUP "LOS SHAPIS" WAS PLAYING."}, {"text": "THE "LOS SHAPIS" MUSIC GROUP HAS RECEIVED DEATH THREATS FROM THE "SHINING PATH" GUERRILLA GROUP BECAUSE THE LATTER BELIEVES "LOS SHAPIS" PLAY ALIENATING MUSIC."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO POLICE SOURCES, THE "SHINING PATH," WHICH BEGAN ITS ACTIVITIES IN AYACUCHO IN {"sentences": [{"text": "AT LEAST TWO PEOPLE WERE KILLED AND FOUR WERE WOUNDED EARLY THIS MORNING DURING AN FMLN ATTACK ON THE EL ANGEL SUGAR MILL LOCATED NEAR APOPA."}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLA ACTION {"sentences": [{"text": "A NEW DIPLOMATIC RIFT HAS ARISEN BETWEEN COLOMBIA AND THE NEIGHBORING REPUBLIC OF VENEZUELA FOLLOWING A PROTEST NOTE SENT BY OUR FOREIGN MINISTRY TO THE VENEZUELAN FOREIGN MINISTRY."}, {"text": "THE NOTE DENOUNCES THE MASSACRE OF 14 FISHERMEN, INCLUDING TWO COLOMBIANS WHOM THE VENEZUELAN ARMED FORCES ACCUSED OF BEING SUBVERSIVES."}, {"text": "THE VENEZUELAN GOVERNMENT DECIDED THAT IT WOULD NOT BE SCOLDED BY COLOMBIA, SO THE VENEZUELAN FOREIGN MINISTRY SENT A NOTE TO OUR FOREIGN MINISTRY WHICH SAID THAT VENEZUELA REJECTED THE TERMS USED IN THE COLOMBIAN PROTEST NOTE."}, {"text": "COLOMBIA HAS SENT 17 FOREIGN MINISTRY NOTES TO VENEZUELA IN THE PAST 2 YEARS, ALL CONCERNING INCIDENTS THAT HAVE DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY AFFECTED COLOMBIAN CITIZENS."}, {"text": "ONLY 2 OF THE 17 PROTEST NOTES HAVE RECEIVED A REPLY, AND THEY NEVER INCLUDED THE RESULTS OF THE INVESTIGATIONS REQUESTED BY OUR GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "THE LAST NOTE REPRESENTS A PROTEST FROM OUR GOVERNMENT FOR THE MURDER OF JOSE ANTONIO AREGUA AND JUSTO PASTOR CEBALLOS ON 29 OCTOBER."}, {"text": "THEY WERE ASSASSINATED ALONG WITH 12 VENEZUELAN CITIZENS WHEN THE VENEZUELAN ARMY MISTOOK THEM FOR NATIONAL LIBERATION ARMY REBELS IN CANO COLORADA, ARAUCA DEPARTMENT, ALONG THE VENEZUELAN BORDER."}, {"text": "EVEN THOUGH THERE IS EVIDENCE THAT THE VENEZUELAN AUTHORITIES MADE A MISTAKE, THE COUNTRY'S REPLY TO THE NOTE WAS SPITEFUL AND UNSATISFACTORY."}, {"text": "THIS REPRESENTS THE WORST DIPLOMATIC INCIDENT BETWEEN THE TWO COUNTRIES SO FAR THIS YEAR."}, {"text": "ILDEGAR PEREZ, VENEZUELAN AMBASSADOR TO COLOMBIA, PERSONALLY REFERRED TO THE STATE OF RELATIONS BETWEEN THE TWO COUNTRIES: (BEGIN RECORDING) (PEREZ) LET US SAY THAT RELATIONS AT THIS POINT ARE DELICATE, BUT I WOULD NOT CHARACTERIZE THEM AS CRITICAL OR EXTREMELY DIFFICULT."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) THE VENEZUELAN GOVERNMENT HAS ORDERED THAT THE TWO SURVIVORS OF THE 29 OCTOBER MASSACRE AT THE BORDER BE TRIED."}, {"text": "MOREOVER, THE DISPUTE BETWEEN THE TWO COUNTRIES IS BEING EXPLOITED IN THE VENEZUELAN PRESIDENTIAL CAMPAIGN."}, {"text": "VERY FEW, HOWEVER, DARE TO SPEAK THE TRUTH ABOUT THE SITUATION."}, {"text": "(VENEZUELAN DEPUTY JUVENCIO PULGAR) (BEGIN RECORDING)"}, {"text": "WE HAVE DISPUTES AND WE SHOULD NOT COVER THEM UP."}, {"text": "COLOMBIA AND VENEZUELA HAVE THINGS TO PROTEST ABOUT, BUT ONLY A DIALOGUE WILL LEAD TO AN AGREEMENT TO SETTLE THESE DISPUTES."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0071", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": {"sentences": [{"text": "PRESUMED SHINING PATH MAOIST EXTREMISTS AMBUSHED AND KILLED 68 PEASANTS IN THE LOCALITY OF BALCON, 200 KM NORTH OF THE SOUTHERN CITY OF AYACUCHO."}, {"text": "A PEASANT DEFENSE PATROL UNIT WAS COMBING THE AREA IN SEARCH OF GUERRILLAS WHEN IT WAS AMBUSHED ON 22 NOVEMBER, THE NEWSPAPER EXPRESO REPORTED TODAY."}, {"text": "THE WAVE OF VIOLENCE HAS HIT PERUVIAN TOURIST ESTABLISHMENTS IN THE CITY OF HUARAZ, CAPITAL OF THE ANCASH DEPARTMENT, WHERE FOUR INNS AND HOTELS WERE BOMBED LAST NIGHT, DAMAGING THE BUILDINGS AND INJURING AN 18 YEAR-OLD GIRL."}, {"text": "IN CUSCO, 1,000 KM SOUTHEAST OF LIMA, A BUS (AS RECEIVED) HEADING TOWARD MACHU PICHU WENT OUT OF CONTROL AS THE RESULT OF SABOTAGE AND FELL INTO A 60-METER RAVINE."}, {"text": "THE WIVES OF THE JERSEY CITY, UNITED STATES, AND CUSCO MAYORS DIED IN THIS ACCIDENT."}, {"text": "LEFTIST SENATOR ENRIQUE BERNALES BALLESTEROS, PRESIDENT OF THE SPECIAL COMMISSION FOR THE INVESTIGATION AND STUDY OF TERRORISM AND VIOLENCE, HAS NOTED THAT THE ESCALATION OF VIOLENCE HAS CLAIMED THE LIVES OF 21 PEOPLE PER DAY DURING THE MONTH OF NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT THE INCREASED VIOLENCE CAN BE TRACED TO ACTIONS BY THE TERRORIST GROUPS SHINING PATH AND TUPAC AMARU REVOLUTIONARY MOVEMENT (MRTA)."}, {"text": "THESE ATTACKS WERE REPRESSED BY THE FORCES OF ORDER."}, {"text": "SENATOR BERNALES REPORTED THAT 630 PEOPLE WERE KILLED IN VIOLENT ACTS IN NOVEMBER AND THAT 1,775 HAVE BEEN KILLED OVER THE PAST 12 MONTHS."}, {"text": "BERNALES SAID THAT 403 PEOPLE WERE KILLED IN NOVEMBER AS A RESULT OF VIOLENT ACTS, INCLUDING 147 CIVILIANS, 165 PRESUMED TERRORISTS, 65 ARMED FORCES MEMBERS, AND 26 DRUG TRAFFICKERS."}, {"text": "A TOTAL OF 227 PEOPLE WERE KILLED IN URBAN VIOLENT ACTS."}, {"text": "SENATOR BERNALES ADDED THAT A TOTAL OF NEARLY 13,000 PEOPLE HAVE BEEN KILLED SINCE THE TERRORIST VIOLENCE BEGAN IN 1980."}, {"text": "BERNALES EXPRESSED HIS CONCERN OVER THE FACT THAT 67 PERCENT OF THE PEOPLE KILLED IN VIOLENT ACTS INVOLVED YOUTHS WHO WERE BETWEEN 15 AND 29 YEARS OF AGE."}, {"text": "HE ASKED THE GOVERNMENT TO ESTABLISH GUIDELINES TO COUNTER THIS SOCIAL PHENOMENON."}, {"text": "AMID THIS BLOODY AND DESTRUCTIVE SITUATION, THE PERUVIAN EPISCOPAL CONFERENCE HAS MADE A CHRISTMAS APPEAL, ASKING THAT--WITHOUT IGNORING "THE SERIOUSNESS OF THE SITUATION"--FOR A TRUCE "FOR PEACE, RECONCILIATION, AND TRANQUILLITY" TO PREVAIL IN THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "THE BISHOPS SAID: "RECALLING HE WHO PREVAILED OVER DEATH, WE CALL UPON THOSE WHO HAVE RESORTED TO VIOLENCE AND KILLINGS AS A {"sentences": [{"text": "THE ARMY HAS REPORTED THAT IT INFLICTED 208 GUERRILLA CASUALTIES DURING CLASHES IN NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, THE FMLN REBELS HAVE SAID THEY INFLICTED 991 CASUALTIES ON THE ARMY--INCLUDING DEAD AND WOUNDED--AS A RESULT OF THEIR ATTACKS, HARASSMENT, AND AMBUSHES DURING THE SAME PERIOD."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY REPORT SAYS 93 FMLN GUERRILLAS WERE KILLED AND 115 WOUNDED AS A RESULT OF NATIONWIDE COUNTERINSURGENCY MILITARY OPERATIONS DURING THE MONTH OF NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THE REPORT ADDED THAT DURING THE SAME PERIOD, THE ARMY CONFISCATED 105 HIGH-CALIBER RIFLES, 2 M-60 MACHINEGUNS, 20 REVOLVERS OF VARIOUS CALIBERS, MORE THAN 55,000 CARTRIDGES, 168 FRAGMENTATION GRENADES, 236 MINES, 9 COMMUNICATION RADIOS, AND A LARGE AMOUNT OF MATERIAL FOR HOMEMADE BOMBS."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY REPORT ADDED THAT DURING THE MONTH OF NOVEMBER, GUERRILLAS KILLED 43 PEASANTS, KIDNAPPED 32, AND CAUSED THE DEATH OF 6 PEOPLE AND CRIPPLED 23 OTHERS AS A RESULT OF MINE EXPLOSIONS."}, {"text": "IN THE WAR AGAINST PUBLIC PROPERTY--THE PILLAR OF A WAR ECONOMY--THE MILITARY SOURCE REPORTED THAT SIX MAYORIAL OFFICES AND SIX NATIONAL ADMINISTRATION FOR TELECOMMUNICATIONS OFFICES WERE DAMAGED IN VARIOUS TOWNS AND SIX JUNCTION BOXES WERE SABOTAGED."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION, 4 TRAINS BELONGING TO THE SALVADORAN NATIONAL RAILROAD, FENADESAL, WERE BLOWN UP, AND 10 VEHICLES AND 5 BUSES WERE PARTIALLY DAMAGED."}, {"text": "REGARDING DAMAGE TO THE ELECTRICITY SYSTEM, THE FMLN KNOCKED DOWN 46 TOWERS AND 136 HIGH-TENSION POWER POLES AND DAMAGED 11 {"sentences": [{"text": "THE ARMY HAS REPORTED THAT IT INFLICTED 208 GUERRILLA CASUALTIES DURING CLASHES IN NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, THE FMLN REBELS HAVE SAID THEY INFLICTED 991 CASUALTIES ON THE ARMY--INCLUDING DEAD AND WOUNDED--AS A RESULT OF THEIR ATTACKS, HARASSMENT, AND AMBUSHES DURING THE SAME PERIOD."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY REPORT SAYS 93 FMLN GUERRILLAS WERE KILLED AND 115 WOUNDED AS A RESULT OF NATIONWIDE COUNTERINSURGENCY MILITARY OPERATIONS DURING THE MONTH OF NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THE REPORT ADDED THAT DURING THE SAME PERIOD, THE ARMY CONFISCATED 105 HIGH-CALIBER RIFLES, 2 M-60 MACHINEGUNS, 20 REVOLVERS OF VARIOUS CALIBERS, MORE THAN 55,000 CARTRIDGES, 168 FRAGMENTATION GRENADES, 236 MINES, 9 COMMUNICATION RADIOS, AND A LARGE AMOUNT OF MATERIAL FOR HOMEMADE BOMBS."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY REPORT ADDED THAT DURING THE MONTH OF NOVEMBER, GUERRILLAS KILLED 43 PEASANTS, KIDNAPPED 32, AND CAUSED THE DEATH OF 6 PEOPLE AND CRIPPLED 23 OTHERS AS A RESULT OF MINE EXPLOSIONS."}, {"text": "IN THE WAR AGAINST PUBLIC PROPERTY--THE PILLAR OF A WAR ECONOMY--THE MILITARY SOURCE REPORTED THAT SIX MAYORIAL OFFICES AND SIX NATIONAL ADMINISTRATION FOR TELECOMMUNICATIONS OFFICES WERE DAMAGED IN VARIOUS TOWNS AND SIX JUNCTION BOXES WERE SABOTAGED."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION, 4 TRAINS BELONGING TO THE SALVADORAN NATIONAL RAILROAD, FENADESAL, WERE BLOWN UP, AND 10 VEHICLES AND 5 BUSES WERE PARTIALLY DAMAGED."}, {"text": "REGARDING DAMAGE TO THE ELECTRICITY SYSTEM, THE FMLN KNOCKED DOWN 46 TOWERS AND 136 HIGH-TENSION POWER POLES AND DAMAGED 11 TRANSFORMERS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0078", "message_template": 2, "message_template_optional": true, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["01 NOV 88 - {"sentences": [{"text": "IT WAS BARELY NOON WHEN A MAN WHO HAD JUST ARRIVED ON A FLIGHT FROM MEDELLIN WENT INTO THE NATIONAL BOOKSTORE TO BUY SOME NEWSPAPERS."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, HIS BODYGUARD-CHAUFFEUR WAITED FOR HIM IN THE LOBBY."}, {"text": "THE MAN WITH THE NEWSPAPERS, A CATTLEMAN NAMED GUSTAVO DE JESUS ESCOBAR FERNANDEZ, HAD JUST LEFT THE BOOKSTORE WHEN THE TROUBLE STARTED."}, {"text": "ESCOBAR WAS PREPARING TO GO TO HIS CAR WHEN A MAN APPROACHED HIM."}, {"text": "THE MAN, AROUND 35 YEARS OLD AND 5 FEET 9 INCHES TALL, TOOK OUT A 7.65 CALIBER PISTOL AND BEGAN FIRING."}, {"text": "PANIC SPREAD THROUGHOUT THE TERMINAL AS PEOPLE THREW THEMSELVES ON THE FLOOR TO AVOID BEING SHOT."}, {"text": "ESCOBAR IMMEDIATELY FELL TO THE FLOOR AS HIS ATTACKER TRIED TO ESCAPE THROUGH ONE OF THE EXITS."}, {"text": "APPARENTLY, HE DID NOT TAKE INTO ACCOUNT THE PRESENCE OF THE BODYGUARD, WHO HAD ENOUGH TIME TO DRAW HIS GUN AND SHOOT THE AGGRESSOR, WHO DIED AT THE SCENE."}, {"text": "ESCOBAR FERNANDEZ WAS TAKEN TO THE SAN PEDRO CLAVER CLINIC, WHERE HE WAS PRONOUNCED DEAD ON ARRIVAL."}, {"text": "BUT THE TRAGIC EVENT DID NOT END THERE."}, {"text": "A 20-YEAR-OLD WOMAN WHO WAS AT THE AIRPORT, MARIA FLOREZ GUTIERREZ, WAS SERIOUSLY WOUNDED AND HER CONDITION WAS LISTED AS SERIOUS WHEN THIS EDITION WENT TO PRINT."}, {"text": "EARLY DETAILS DID NOT CLARIFY THE MOTIVATION FOR THE ATTACK."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO DOCUMENTS FOUND IN HIS CLOTHING, IN ADDITION TO HIS ACTIVITIES AS A CATTLEMAN, GUSTAVO DE JESUS ESCOBAR WAS A LEGAL ADVISOR IN CONGRESS, ALTHOUGH THIS WAS DENIED BY SPOKESMEN FROM THAT INSTITUTION."}, {"text": "THINGS TOOK ANOTHER TURN THAT EVENING, WHEN THE TELEVISION NEWS PROGRAM 24 HOURS REPORTED THAT ESCOBAR FERNANDEZ WAS THE COUSIN OF PABLO ESCOBAR GAVIRIA."}, {"text": "THIS GAVE RISE TO THE SUPPOSITION THAT THE ATTACK WAS LINKED TO THE SERIES OF KILLINGS IN THE SO-CALLED "CARTEL WAR.""}, {"text": "AS TO THE ATTACKER, NEITHER HIS REAL MOTIVES NOR HIS IDENTITY WERE KNOWN AT THE END OF THE WEEK."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0080", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": "IT WAS OFFICIALLY ANNOUNCED TODAY THAT MAYOR HECTOR AREVALO OF THE RULING CHRISTIAN DEMOCRATIC PARTY (PDC), WHO WAS ELECTED MAYOR IN A TOWN IN SAN VICENTE DEPARTMENT LAST MARCH, RESIGNED BECAUSE OF DEATH THREATS FROM SALVADORAN GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "AREVALO IS THE FIRST MAYOR TO RESIGN AS A RESULT OF FMLN THREATS."}, {"text": "THE FMLN CLAIMS MAYORS ARE PART OF THE COUNTERINSURGENCY PLAN CONDUCTED BY THE SALVADORAN ARMY."}, {"text": "AREVALO, 39, WAS REPORTEDLY THREATENED WITH DEATH BY THE GUERRILLAS, WHO ALSO ORDERED HIM TO LEAVE THE TOWN OF SANTA CLARA, 65 KM EAST OF SAN SALVADOR."}, {"text": "AFTER ANNOUNCING HIS RESIGNATION, AREVALO SAID: "I WANT TO LIVE AND TO FEEL UNTAINTED."}, {"text": "I DO NOT WANT TO HAVE ENEMIES."}, {"text": "I HAVE A WIFE AND CHILDREN WHO NEED ME.""}, {"text": "AREVALO SAID, HOWEVER, THAT HE CANNOT LEAVE SANTA CLARA, A TOWN OF APPROXIMATELY 10,000 PEOPLE, BECAUSE HE CANNOT AFFORD TO DO SO."}, {"text": "THE FMLN ALSO CLAIMS THAT IN MANY TOWNS IN NORTHERN AND EASTERN EL SALVADOR, AN AREA OVER WHICH IT CLAIMS TO HAVE MORE CONTROL THAN THE ARMY, THERE ARE TWO POWER CENTERS: ONE IS THE GUERRILLA MOVEMENT, AND THE OTHER IS THE GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "THE FMLN HAS STATED THAT IT WILL NOT ALLOW THE GOVERNMENT TO CONTROL THAT REGION."}, {"text": "THUS FAR THIS YEAR, THE FMLN HAS KILLED EIGHT PDC AND RIGHTIST NATIONALIST REPUBLICAN ALLIANCE MAYORS IN SANTA ANA, MORAZAN, SAN MIGUEL, AND USULUTAN DEPARTMENTS."}, {"text": "THE CATHOLIC CHURCH AND THE SALVADORAN POLITICAL PARTIES HAVE CONDEMNED THE MURDER OF THESE {"sentences": [{"text": "FOUR ALLEGED TERRORISTS, ALL WEARING SKI MASKS, MURDERED MAYOR ALFREDO CHAMORRO IN THE SMALL TOWN OF PALLANCHACRA."}, {"text": "CHAMORRO WAS A MEMBER OF THE GOVERNING APRA."}, AN ALLEGED MEMBER OF THE PERUVIAN COMMUNIST PARTY, WITH ENTRIES IN POLICE RECORDS."}, {"text": "A POSTER WHICH READ "AN EYE FOR AN EYE."}, {"text": "FOR WHAT THE WORKERS REVOLUTIONARY MOVEMENT (MOR) {"sentences": [{"text": "THE TERRORIST MANUEL RODRIGUEZ PATRIOTIC FRONT (FPMR) IN THE LATEST ISSUE OF ITS OFFICIAL PUBLICATION HAS REPORTED ON THE FAILURE LAST MAY OF ITS OPERATION AIMED AT MURDERING MILITARY JUDGE FERNANDO TORRES SILVA."}, {"text": "THE ARTICLE JUSTIFIES THE OPERATION AND REITERATES THAT "THE FPMR HAS NOT GIVEN UP ITS DECISION TO CARRY OUT ITS SENTENCE OF CAPITAL PUNISHMENT FOR THIS INDIVIDUAL.""}, {"text": "THE ISSUE ALSO PUBLISHES AN EDITORIAL CONFIRMING THE NEED TO REINVIGORATE THE "NATIONAL PATRIOTIC WAR.""}, {"text": "REMEMBERING THE FPMR FIFTH ANNIVERSARY, THE EDITORIAL URGES THE MILITANTS "TO CONTINUE THE ARMED FIGHT AGAINST TYRANNY.""}, {"text": "A REPORT THEN REVIEWS THE MOST IMPORTANT TERRORIST ATTACKS PERPETRATED IN 1988."}, {"text": "THE REPORT EMPHASIZES THE AMBUSH ON CARABINEROS PATROLS, THE OCCUPATION OF LO QUENES AND AGUA GRANDE VILLAGE, AND RETIRED COLONEL ROJAS LOBOS' EXECUTION."}, {"text": "SOME PAGES ARE DEDICATED TO RAUL PELLEGRINI, ALIAS "COMMANDER RODRIGO," AND OTHER FPMR "HEROES," INCLUDING CECILIA MAGNI, ALIAS "COMMANDER TAMARA.""}, {"text": "THE ISSUE, WHICH WAS DISTRIBUTED A FEW DAYS BEFORE CHRISTMAS, INCLUDES A PAMPHLET WITH INSTRUCTIONS ON HOW TO MANUFACTURE BOMBS, AND POEMS URGING THE PEOPLE TO JOIN THE SUBVERSION AND THE ARMED FIGHT."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST4-MUC4-0099", "message_template": 1, "message_template_optional": true, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["01 MAY 88 - {"sentences": [{"text": "WE ARE NOT DEMANDING THAT THEY STOP THEIR OPERATIONS AS A PRECONDITION FOR NEGOTIATING."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, IT SHOULD BE CLEAR THAT WE ARE FACING THE SAME SITUATION AS BEFORE, THEREFORE, WE HAVE THE SAME RIGHTS AND WILL CONTINUE OUR OPERATIONS UNTIL A CEASE-FIRE IS AGREED."}, {"text": "IN CARACAS WE COMMITTED OURSELVES TO NEGOTIATING AND HOLDING TALKS IN ORDER TO OBTAIN A CEASE-FIRE AND THE NECESSARY AGREEMENTS FOR THE BENEFIT OF THE COUNTRY AND THE ENTIRE NATION."}, {"text": "THAT IS THE IMPORTANT ISSUE RIGHT NOW."}, {"text": "WE HAVE BEEN FIGHTING WITHOUT THAT GOAL, WITHOUT HAVING ANY COMMITMENT TO NEGOTIATE ANYTHING."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, THAT DOES NOT MEAN THAT THE SITUATION SHOULD REMAIN THE SAME."}, {"text": "NOW THERE IS A NEW FACTOR, A COMMITMENT TO NEGOTIATE AND REACH AGREEMENTS ON ALL THOSE TOPICS."}, {"text": "IT IS VERY IMPORTANT THAT THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE KNOW THE CONTENTS OF THE AGENDA, THAT THEY ARE FULLY AWARE OF ALL THE TOPICS TO BE DISCUSSED, AND THAT THEY KNOW THE IMPORTANCE OF THE TIMETABLE AGREEMENT FOR DISCUSSIONS AND NEGOTIATIONS."}, {"text": "YOU JOURNALISTS CAN HELP THE PEOPLE UNDERSTAND PROBLEM."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "(WORDS INDISTINCT) COMMANDER, WHEN DO YOU EXPECT THE FMLN TO JOIN THE PROCESS?"}, {"text": "(HANDAL) LOOK, DEADLINES ARE NOT THE MOST IMPORTANT THING RIGHT NOW."}, {"text": "WHAT IS IMPORTANT NOW IS COMPLYING WITH THE AGREEMENTS TO REACH POLITICAL AGREEMENTS."}, {"text": "THAT IS THE MAIN ASPECT OF THE GENEVA AGREEMENT."}, {"text": "IT IS POSSIBLE THAT SOME DEADLINES WILL NOT BE MET."}, {"text": "IF DEADLINES ARE SET AND THE TIME FOR IMPLEMENTING THEM EXPIRES, THEN THIS IS TANTAMOUNT TO WASTING TIME."}, {"text": "THIS THEN LEADS TO STEPS BEING DEMANDED THAT IN REALITY DEPEND ON THE POLITICAL AGREEMENTS THAT ARE REACHED AND NOT THE DEADLINES FOR REACHING THEM."}, {"text": "THEREFORE, ACCORDING TO THE AGENDA AND THE TIMETABLE AGREED TO HERE IN CARACAS, THE ACCENT IS ON THE POLITICAL AGREEMENTS."}, {"text": "THOSE AGREEMENTS HAVE TO DO WITH CHANGES WITHIN THE ARMED FORCES."}, {"text": "EVERYTHING RELATED TO THE ARMED FORCES MUST BE CHANGED."}, {"text": "EVERY FACTOR CONCERNING THE ARMED FORCES MUST BE REVIEWED FROM A CERTAIN POINT OR PERSPECTIVE."}, {"text": "CHANGES ARE NECESSARY; CHANGES MUST BE MADE AND THOSE CHANGES MUST BE SIGNIFICANT."}, {"text": "THESE CHANGES MUST COMPLETELY TRANSFORM THE ARMED FORCES, BEGINNING WITH ITS ROLE AND INFLUENCE IN DETERMINING THE COUNTRY'S POLICIES AND GUIDELINES."}, {"text": "WE HAVE BEEN PRESENTING PROPOSALS IN THIS REGARD FOR SOME TIME."}, {"text": "THE TOPIC OF DEMOCRATIZATION IS CLOSELY LINKED TO THE TOPIC OF THE ARMED FORCES, TO ITS PURGING, ITS REDUCTION, AND IN SUM, ITS END."}, {"text": "WE BELIEVE THAT THE COUNTRY WILL NOT ALWAYS NEED THE ARMED FORCES."}, {"text": "AS WITH ANY INSTITUTION OR HISTORICAL FACTOR, IT EMERGES, IT IS MAINTAINED FOR A CERTAIN TIME, AND THEN IT TENDS TO DISAPPEAR."}, {"text": "THE COUNTRY MUST HAVE THE OPPORTUNITY TO DEVELOP."}, {"text": "IT CANNOT CONTINUE ALONG THE SAME PATH BECAUSE THIS WOULD ONLY REPRESENT EXPENSES AND A HEAVY BURDEN FOR THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "FOR SEVERAL DECADES, THE ARMED FORCES HAVE MEANT ABSENCE OF LIBERTY, REAL SECURITY, AND THE IMPOSSIBILITY OF THE CIVILIAN SOCIETY TO DECIDE THE COUNTRY'S PATH."}, {"text": "ELECTIONS HAVE BEEN TURNED INTO A MERE FORMALITY, WHERE THOSE WHO WERE NOT ELECTED RUN THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "THE COUNTRY IS NOW GOING THROUGH A DRAMA THAT HAS ALSO SHOCKED THE INTERNATIONAL PUBLIC, THE MURDER OF THE JESUIT PRIESTS."}, {"text": "EVERYONE IS AWAITING THE RESULTS OF THE INVESTIGATIONS AND HOPING THAT THOSE WHO WERE RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS CRIME WILL BE PUNISHED."}, {"text": "WE BELIEVE THAT THE CASE OF JESUIT PRIESTS IS REALLY GRAVE; IT IS A DRAMA THAT REFLECTS THE DRAMA OF THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE'S HISTORY IN THE CURRENT CENTURY."}, {"text": "(CONTINUED)"}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "THOSE ACCUSED OF THE ASSASSINATION OF SIX JESUITS WILL HAVE A "FAIR TRIAL" AND IF FOUND GUILTY, WILL BE PUNISHED WHETHER THEY ARE CIVILIANS, MILITARY, OR INFLUENTIAL PEOPLE, SUPREME COURT PRESIDENT DR MAURICIO GUTIERREZ CASTRO SAID."}, {"text": "THE TECHNICAL INVESTIGATION COMMISSION HAS DETERMINED THAT SOME MILITARY WERE REPORTEDLY INVOLVED IN THE ASSASSINATION OF THE SIX JESUITS AND THEIR TWO MAIDS, WHICH TOOK PLACE AT DAYBREAK ON 16 NOVEMBER, AS REPORTED BY PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI ON 7 JANUARY."}, {"text": ""THE LOCAL AND INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY CAN REST ASSURED THE SALVADORAN JUDICIARY SYSTEM WILL NOT HESITATE TO ENFORCE THE LAW UPON THE AUTHORS OF THIS HORRIBLE CRIME," DR GUTIERREZ POINTED OUT."}, {"text": "GUTIERREZ SAID HE DOES NOT KNOW HOW MANY PEOPLE ARE INVOLVED OR THEIR MILITARY RANKS, BECAUSE THE COMMISSION TO INVESTIGATE CRIMINAL ACTIONS IS STILL CONDUCTING INVESTIGATIONS AND HAS NOT PRESENTED ITS REPORT TO THE TRIBUNAL."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, GENERAL PROSECUTOR DR MAURICIO EDUARDO COLORADO MAINTAINED THAT THE MILITARY SUSPECTS "ARE REGROUPED AND HAVE BEEN PUT IN CUSTODY.""}, {"text": "HOWEVER, HE DID NOT REVEAL THE NAMES OR THE MILITARY RANKS OF THE SUSPECTS."}, {"text": "THE PROSECUTOR SAID THAT THE SCIENTIFIC TEST CONDUCTED BY THE COMMISSION TO INVESTIGATE CRIMINAL ACTIONS AND THE SPECIALIZED POLICE WORKING ON THIS CASE HAVE DETERMINED THAT THE CRIME COULD HAVE BEEN PERPETRATED BY ARMED FORCES MEMBERS."}, {"text": ""THE ATTORNEY GENERAL OFFICE WILL PROCEED ACCORDING TO THE LAW AND AGAINST WHOEVER TURNS OUT TO BE GUILTY, BECAUSE IT IS THE CONSTITUTIONAL DUTY OF THE ATTORNEY GENERAL'S OFFICE," COLORADO SAID."}, {"text": "ASKED ABOUT THIS ISSUE, JUSTICE MINISTER DR OSCAR ALFREDO SANTAMARIA, PRESIDENT OF THE COMMISSION TO INVESTIGATE CRIMINAL ACTIONS SAID: "WE UNDERSTAND THAT THE MOST RECENT INFORMATION ON THIS CASE WAS ANNOUNCED BY THE PRESIDENT OF THE REPUBLIC A FEW DAYS AGO.""}, {"text": "HE REFUSED TO MAKE ANY FURTHER STATEMENTS."}, {"text": "NEW UCA (CENTRAL AMERICAN UNIVERSITY) RECTOR JESUIT FRANCISCO ESTRADA ADMITTED PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI HAS TAKEN "A STEP FORWARD" BY UNMASKING THE SUSPECTS IN THIS CRIME, "BECAUSE HIS ETHIC PRINCIPLES DO NOT TOLERATE SUCH ATROCITIES.""}, {"text": "ESTRADA SAID HE UNDERSTANDS WHY CRISTIANI, DURING HIS 7 JANUARY SPEECH, DID NOT GIVE ANY NAMES, "BECAUSE THE INVESTIGATIONS ARE STILL BEING CONDUCTED.""}, {"text": "MOREOVER, THERE MUST NOT ONLY BE ONE SUSPECT, BUT RATHER SEVERAL.""}, {"text": "BEFORE MEETING WITH THE REPORTERS, THE UCA RECTOR MET WITH OFFICIALS FROM SCOTLAND YARD."}, {"text": "A FEW DAYS AGO, HE ALSO MET SPANISH, CANADIAN, AND U.S. POLICEMEN WHO, AT THE GOVERNMENT'S REQUEST, ARE ASSISTING THE SALVADORAN COMMISSION IN CHARGE OF CLARIFYING THIS CASE."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0002", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["16 NOV 89"]}], "incident_location": {"sentences": [{"text": "THE NATIONAL POLICE REPORTED TODAY THAT OVER 15,000 PEOPLE HAVE BEEN ARRESTED IN LIMA OVER THE PAST FEW HOURS IN A DRAGNET AIMED AT UNCOVERING THE ASSASSINS OF FORMER DEFENSE MINISTER ENRIQUE LOPEZ ALBUJAR TRINT, WHO WAS MURDERED IN A TERRORIST ATTACK YESTERDAY."}, {"text": "THE POLICE ALSO STOPPED 8,000 CARS IN THE SEARCH FOR ASSASSINS, WHO ARE PRESUMABLY MEMBERS OF THE MAOIST TERRORIST ORGANIZATION SHINING PATH."}, {"text": "LOPEZ ALBUJAR, WHO LEFT HIS POST AT THE MINISTRY IN MAY 1989, WAS RIDDLED WITH BULLETS AS HE WAS GETTING OUT OF HIS CAR IN THE LIMA RESIDENTIAL DISTRICT OF SAN ISIDRO."}, {"text": "LOPEZ ALBUJAR, 63, WAS RETIRED."}, {"text": "HE WAS DRIVING WITHOUT AN ESCORT."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE SOURCES, THE CAR IN WHICH THE CRIMINALS FLED WAS ABANDONED IN SURQUILLO DISTRICT."}, {"text": "THE DIRCOTE (COUNTERTERRORISM DIVISON) HAS IDENTIFIED ONE OF THE TERRORISTS AS GERARDO OLIVOS SILVA THROUGH A COMPOSITE MADE FROM WITNESS' REPORTS."}, {"text": "THE POLICE SAY THAT OLIVOS SILVA, A FORESTRY ENGINEER, HAS PARTICIPATED IN OTHER ATTACKS AGAINST ARMED FORCES PERSONNEL IN THE PAST."}, {"text": "LOPEZ ALBUJAR'S MURDER HAS MADE A GREAT IMPRESSION IN PERU."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO POLITICAL OBSERVERS, THE INCIDENT IS BEING REGARDED AS AN INDICATION THAT THE SHINING PATH INTENDS TO CONTINUE ITS TERRORIST ATTACKS TO INTIMIDATE THE {"sentences": [{"text": "THE BODIES OF HECTOR OQUELI, UNDERSECRETARY OF THE NATIONAL REVOLUTIONARY MOVEMENT (MNR) OF EL SALVADOR, AND GILDA FLORES, A MEMBER OF GUATEMALA'S SOCIAL DEMOCRATIC PARTY, WERE FOUND IN CUILAPA, GUATEMALA, NEAR THE BORDER WITH EL SALVADOR, THE RELATIVES OF ONE OF THE VICTIMS HAVE REPORTED."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE REPORTS, THE TWO BODIES APPEARED TO HAVE BEEN SHOT IN THEIR TEMPLES."}, {"text": "ONE OF OQUELI'S RELATIVES, WHO ASKED TO REMAIN ANONYMOUS, TOLD ACAN-EFE THAT THE SALVADORAN POLITICIAN STILL HAD HIS PERSONAL PAPERS, INCLUDING HIS PASSPORT, IN ONE OF HIS POCKETS."}, {"text": "THE MNR REPORTED ON 12 JANUARY THAT HEAVILY ARMED MEN IN CIVILIAN CLOTHES HAD INTERCEPTED A VEHICLE WITH OQUELI AND FLORES ENROUTE FOR LA AURORA AIRPORT AND THAT THE TWO POLITICAL LEADERS HAD BEEN KIDNAPPED AND WERE REPORTED MISSING."}, {"text": "OQUELI WAS TO FLY TO NICARAGUA TO JOIN AN INTERNATIONAL SOCIALIST DELEGATION WHICH WILL OBSERVE THE NICARAGUAN ELECTORAL CAMPAIGN."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE RELATIVE, GUATEMALAN CIVILIAN SOURCES REPORTED FINDING THE BODIES TO HIM EARLIER TODAY, OQUELI DEPARTED EL SALVADOR ON 13 NOVEMBER, 2 DAYS AFTER THE GUERRILLAS LAUNCHED THEIR LARGEST OFFENSIVE IN THE RECENT DECADE."}, {"text": "REPORTEDLY, OQUELI HAD BEEN THREATENED WITH DEATH BY SEVERAL PEOPLE WHO, THROUGH A GOVERNMENT RADIO NETWORK, HAD ACCUSED HIM OF BEING AN "ACCOMPLICE" OF THE REBELS."}, {"text": "THE MNR, WHOSE SECRETARY GENERAL IS GUILLERMO UNGO, IS A LEGALLY REGISTERED PARTY WHICH FORMS THE DEMOCRATIC CONVERGENCE TOGETHER WITH THE SOCIAL CHRISTIAN MOVEMENT AND THE SOCIAL DEMOCRATIC PARTY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0006", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["12 JAN 90"]}], {"sentences": [{"text": "THE BODIES OF HECTOR OQUELI, UNDERSECRETARY OF THE NATIONAL REVOLUTIONARY MOVEMENT (MNR) OF EL SALVADOR, AND GILDA FLORES, A MEMBER OF GUATEMALA'S SOCIAL DEMOCRATIC PARTY, WERE FOUND IN CUILAPA, GUATEMALA, NEAR THE BORDER WITH EL SALVADOR, THE RELATIVES OF ONE OF THE VICTIMS HAVE REPORTED."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE REPORTS, THE TWO BODIES APPEARED TO HAVE BEEN SHOT IN THEIR TEMPLES."}, {"text": "ONE OF OQUELI'S RELATIVES, WHO ASKED TO REMAIN ANONYMOUS, TOLD ACAN-EFE THAT THE SALVADORAN POLITICIAN STILL HAD HIS PERSONAL PAPERS, INCLUDING HIS PASSPORT, IN ONE OF HIS POCKETS."}, {"text": "THE MNR REPORTED ON 12 JANUARY THAT HEAVILY ARMED MEN IN CIVILIAN CLOTHES HAD INTERCEPTED A VEHICLE WITH OQUELI AND FLORES ENROUTE FOR LA AURORA AIRPORT AND THAT THE TWO POLITICAL LEADERS HAD BEEN KIDNAPPED AND WERE REPORTED MISSING."}, {"text": "OQUELI WAS TO FLY TO NICARAGUA TO JOIN AN INTERNATIONAL SOCIALIST DELEGATION WHICH WILL OBSERVE THE NICARAGUAN ELECTORAL CAMPAIGN."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE RELATIVE, GUATEMALAN CIVILIAN SOURCES REPORTED FINDING THE BODIES TO HIM EARLIER TODAY, OQUELI DEPARTED EL SALVADOR ON 13 NOVEMBER, 2 DAYS AFTER THE GUERRILLAS LAUNCHED THEIR LARGEST OFFENSIVE IN THE RECENT DECADE."}, {"text": "REPORTEDLY, OQUELI HAD BEEN THREATENED WITH DEATH BY SEVERAL PEOPLE WHO, THROUGH A GOVERNMENT RADIO NETWORK, HAD ACCUSED HIM OF BEING AN "ACCOMPLICE" OF THE REBELS."}, {"text": "THE MNR, WHOSE SECRETARY GENERAL IS GUILLERMO UNGO, IS A LEGALLY REGISTERED PARTY WHICH FORMS THE DEMOCRATIC CONVERGENCE TOGETHER WITH THE SOCIAL CHRISTIAN MOVEMENT AND THE SOCIAL DEMOCRATIC PARTY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0006", "message_template": 2, "message_template_optional": true, "incident_date": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": "IN THE ABSENCE OF NICARAGUAN AMBASSADOR FRANCISO LACAYO PARAJON, JUAN JOSE MEMBRENO, COUNSELOR TO THE NICARAGUAN EMBASSY IN HONDURAS, CHARACTERIZED AS RIDICULOUS, STATEMENTS MADE YESTERDAY BY LUIS FRANCISCO ORDONEZ REYES, WHO, ACCORDING TO POLICE, IS OF NICARAGUAN ORIGIN."}, {"text": "ORDONEZ REYES ACCUSED JOSE JESUS PENA--ALLEGED CHIEF OF SECURITY FOR THE NICARAGUAN EMBASSY IN TEGUCIGALPA--OF MASTERMINDING THE 7 JANUARY ASSASSINATION OF CONTRA COMMANDER MANUEL ANTONIO RUGAMA."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (MEMBRENO) WE CATEGORICALLY DENY THAT ALLEGATION."}, {"text": "THESE ACCUSATIONS AGAINST THE EMBASSY ARE RIDICULOUS."}, {"text": "THE EMBASSY HAS NO OFFICER OR EMPLOYEE WITH THE NAME OF THE MAN IDENTIFIED IN THE NEWS CONFERENCE."}, {"text": "THERE HAVE ALREADY BEEN MANY ACCOUNTS OF THIS INCIDENT THAT POINT TO THE COUNTERREVOLUTION."}, {"text": "WE CATEGORICALLY DENY THESE ACCUSATIONS AND CHARACTERIZE THEM AS RIDICULOUS."}, {"text": "WE HAVE NO SECURITY OFFICERS AT THIS EMBASSY, ONLY DIPLOMATIC AND SUPPORT PERSONNEL."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) (ALVAREZ) ALL THE PERSONNEL WHO WORK AT THE NICARAGUAN EMBASSY IN TEGUCIGALPA ARE APPOINTED BY THE FOREIGN MINISTRY, ACCORDING TO THE COUNSELOR."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (MEMBRENO) ALL OUR PERSONNEL ARE NICARAGUANS."}, {"text": "IN REGARD TO WHAT HE (ORDONEZ REYES) HAS INVENTED, WE THINK IT IS RIDICULOUS."}, {"text": "WE ONLY HAVE NICARAGUAN GOVERNMENT PERSONNEL WORKING AT THE EMBASSY."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) (ALVAREZ) REGARDING THE POSSIBILITY THAT COUNTERREVOLUTIONARY AGENTS INFILTRATED THE NICARAGUAN EMBASSY IN TEGUCIGALPA, COUNSELOR JUAN JOSE MEMBRENO REPLIED: (BEGIN RECORDING) (MEMBRENO) THIS HAPPENED AT THE AMBASSADOR'S RESIDENCE."}, {"text": "THE AMBASSADOR LEARNED BY CHANCE THAT ONE OF THE RESIDENCE GUARDS WAS OF NICARAGUAN ORIGIN WITH ALLEDGED COUNTERREVOLUTIONARY LINKS."}, {"text": "THIS IS WHAT HAPPENED."}, {"text": "THIS CASE DID NOT OCCUR AT THE EMBASSY."}, {"text": "(ALVAREZ) IS MANAGUA INTERESTED IN ELIMINATING ALL THE CONTRA LEADERS LIVING IN HONDURAS OR ALL PEOPLE WHO ARE LINKED TO THE COUNTERREVOLUTION?"}, {"text": "(MEMBRENO) ON THE CONTRARY, WE RESPECT PEOPLES' LIVES AND THAT IS WHY WE HAVE ALWAYS BEEN WILLING TO RECEIVE IN NICARAGUA ALL NICARAGUANS WHO WANT TO ACCEPT AMNESTY AND ALL THOSE WHO HAVE IN ONE WAY OR OTHER BEEN INVOLVED IN THE COUNTERREVOLUTIONARY CAMPAIGN."}, {"text": "(ALVAREZ) HAVE THERE BEEN ANY MORE ATTACKS AGAINST THIS EMBASSY OR ANY OTHER TYPE OF THREAT, AS OCCURRED A FEW DAYS AGO?"}, {"text": "(MEMBRENO) NO, AFTER THE SHOOTING INCIDENT AT THE AMBASSADOR'S RESIDENCE, WHAT HAPPENED A FEW DAYS LATER--HERE AT THE EMBASSY--WAS THAT A CAR DROVE PAST THE EMBASSY AT NIGHT AND KNOCKED DOWN SOME SECURITY RAILS ON THE SIDEWALK."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0007", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["07 JAN {"sentences": [{"text": "THE GOVERNMENT OF EL SALVADOR STRONGLY CONDEMNS THE TERRORIST ATTACKS CARRIED OUT WITH EXPLOSIVES TODAY AGAINST THE COMMITTEE OF MOTHERS OF POLITICAL PRISONERS AND MISSING IN EL SALVADOR AND AGAINST THE SALVADORAN WORKERS NATIONAL UNION FEDERATION."}, {"text": "AS A RESULT OF THESE ATTACKS, SEVERAL PERSONS WERE WOUNDED AND OTHERS DIED."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT OFFERS ITS CONDOLENCES."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT REPUDIATES THESE IRRATIONAL AND CRIMINAL ACTIONS AND THE TERRORIST ATTACK CARRIED OUT ON 30 OCTOBER BY THE FMLN AGAINST THE ARMED FORCES STAFF INSTALLATIONS, WHERE 1 CIVILIAN DIED AND 14 OTHERS WERE WOUNDED."}, {"text": "IT IS EVIDENT THAT THESE ACTIONS ARE PART OF A PLOT WHOSE OBJECTIVE IS TO BLOCK THE DIALOGUE INITIATED BY PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT HAS ORDERED A CAREFUL INVESTIGATION TO DETERMINE WHAT HAPPENED AND TO FILE CHARGES AGAINST CRIMINAL GROUPS THAT HAVE UNLEASHED THIS INCREASED WAVE OF TERRORIST VIOLENCE TO CREATE A CLIMATE OF UNREST AND TO BLOCK THE ROAD TO PEACE."}, {"text": "FINALLY, THE GOVERNMENT OF EL SALVADOR REAFFIRMS ITS DETERMINATION TO CONTINUE THE SEARCH FOR PEACE THROUGH THE DIALOGUE, AND IT STATES THAT IN SPITE OF THESE BLOODY EVENTS, SALVADORANS MUST REMAIN CALM AND NOT GIVE UP HOPES TO FIND A SOLUTION TO THE CONFLICT THROUGH CIVILIZED MEANS."}, {"text": "31 OCTOBER 1989, NATIONAL SECRETARIAT OF COMMUNICATIONS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0010", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["01 NOV 89"]}], {"sentences": [{"text": "THE DISSEMINATION OF A DOCUMENT QUESTIONING COLOMBIA'S OIL POLICY, ESPECIALLY THE PARTICIPATION OF FOREIGN COMPANIES, IS REPORTEDLY THE AIM OF THE PUBLICITY STUNT CARRIED OUT BY THE PRO-CASTRO ELN (ARMY OF NATIONAL LIBERATION), WHICH KIDNAPPED SEVERAL HONORARY CONSULS, NEWSMEN, AND POLITICAL LEADERS."}, {"text": "ANONYMOUS SOURCES OF THE LEFTIST GROUP HEADED BY SPANISH PRIEST MANUEL PEREZ CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE KIDNAPPINGS."}, {"text": "THEY IDENTIFIED THEMSELVES AS MEMBERS OF THE MANUEL GUSTAVO CHACON SOVEREIGNTY OPERATION, WHICH WAS NAMED IN HONOR OF THE LEADER OF THE POWERFUL (NAME INDISTINCT) LABOR UNION OF ECOPETROL (COLOMBIAN PETROLEUM ENTERPRISE), MURDERED IN BARRANCABERMEJA IN FEBRUARY."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE TERRORIST GROUP, THE HOSTAGES WILL BE TAKEN TO UNDISCLOSED LOCATIONS AND WILL BE GIVEN A DOCUMENT ADDRESSED TO THE COLOMBIAN GOVERNMENT AND THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY."}, {"text": "THE DOCUMENT WILL REITERATE THE INSURGENT GROUP'S CRITICISM OF COLOMBIA'S OIL PRODUCTION INFRASTRUCTURE, WHICH INCLUDES SEVERAL FOREIGN COMPANIES, MANY OF THEM EUROPEAN."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0011", "message_template": 1, {"sentences": [{"text": "THE FMLN REPORTS TO OUR PEOPLE AND THE PEOPLE OF THE WORLD THE FOLLOWING: 1. THE MASSACRE AGAINST THE SALVADORAN WORKERS NATIONAL UNION FEDERATION (FENASTRAS) WAS PLANNED IN COLD BLOOD."}, {"text": "THE SITE AND THE MOMENT WHEN THE FENASTRAS LEADERS WERE MEETING HAD BEEN SELECTED."}, {"text": "2. WE HAVE TRUSTWORTHY INFORMATION FROM OUR INTELLIGENCE ORGANS THAT THIS ACTION WAS ORDERED BY COLONEL PONCE, THAT CRISTIANI KNEW ABOUT IT AND APPROVED IT, AND THAT IT WAS CARRIED OUT BY COLONEL ELENA FUENTE AS THE HEAD OF THE MORBID DEATH SQUAD OF THE ARMY'S 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE IN RESPONSE TO OUR MILITARY ATTACK ON THE ARMY STAFF."}, {"text": "THIS BEHAVIOR BY CRISTIANI SHOULD SURPRISE NO ONE."}, {"text": "TERRORISM IS AN OLD PRACTICE OF THE NATIONALIST REPUBLICAN ALLIANCE (ARENA)."}, {"text": "ONLY A FEW DAYS AGO, ARENA ASSASSINS TRIED TO KILL THE PRESIDENT OF THE MORTGAGE BANK, MR MASON, FOR NOT FOLLOWING THEIR ORDERS."}, {"text": "3. THE PEOPLE DEMAND THE RESIGNATION OF CHIEF OF STAFF COL EMILIO PONCE BECAUSE HIS RESPONSIBILITY IN THIS CRIMINAL ACTION IS REAL."}, {"text": "4. THE FMLN HAS PRUDENTLY TAKEN TIME BEFORE ADOPTING A DEFINITE POSITION."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT AND THE ARMED FORCES HAVE ADOPTED AN IRRESPONSIBLE ATTITUDE AND HAVE BRAZENLY ACCUSED THE FMLN OF THE CRIMES THEY COMMIT."}, {"text": "IN VIEW OF THIS ATTITUDE AND OF THE PEOPLE'S INDIGNATION, WE HAVE TO PREVENT OUR PRESENCE AT THE DIALOGUE FROM BEING USED TO COVER UP THE GOVERNMENT'S RESPONSIBILITY IN THIS MASSACRE AND TO ENHANCE THE MASK OF MODERATOR AND NEGOTIATOR THAT CRISTIANI HAS BEEN USING TO SECURE POLITICAL SUPPORT AND U.S. FINANCIAL SUPPORT TO EXTEND THE WAR."}, {"text": "IN SAN JOSE, SPEAKING ON ITS VIEW OF THE WAR, THE GOVERNMENT SAID THAT IT CONSIDERS POPULAR MOVEMENTS AS SUPPORT ORGANIZATIONS OF THE FMLN, AND THEREFORE, AS ENEMIES OF THE GOVERNMENT IN THE ARMED CONFLICT."}, {"text": "WE DEMANDED THAT THE GOVERNMENT DELEGATION GIVE US A LIST OF THOSE ORGANIZATIONS, BUT TO NO AVAIL."}, {"text": "THE TERRORIST ATTACKS AND MASSACRES ARE NOW YIELDING THE LISTS THAT WERE DENIED TO US AT THE DIALOGUE TABLE."}, {"text": "EVEN BEFORE THE SAN JOSE MEETING, THE GOVERNMENT HAD GREATLY INCREASED ITS REPRESSION."}, {"text": "SINCE THE MEETING, IT HAS INCREASED ITS DETENTIONS AND ATTACKED THE RESIDENCES OF LEADERS OF THE SOCIAL CHRISTIAN PEOPLE'S MOVEMENT AND THE UDN (NATIONALIST DEMOCRATIC UNION), UNIVERSITY, FECMASAN (MSGR OSCAR ARNULFO ROMERO FEDERATION OF COMMITTEES OF MOTHERS AND RELATIVES), AND FENASTRAS."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, CRISTIANI IS MAINTAINING HIS HYPOCRITICAL POSITION OF MODERATION."}, {"text": "THE MASSACRES, DETENTIONS, AND REPRESSION OF EARTHQUAKE VICTIMS, THE REPATRIATED, UNIVERSITIES, LABOR UNIONS, PEASANT COOPERATIVES, MOTHERS' ORGANIZATIONS, AND OTHER SEGMENTS OF THE POPULATION SHOW THAT THE WAR OF THE ARMED FORCES, GOVERNMENT, AND ARENA IS AIMED AGAINST THE PEOPLE AND, THEREFORE, THESE GROUPS CANNOT AND WILL NOT REMAIN IDLE."}, {"text": "THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE HAVE THE RIGHT TO TAKE UP ARMS AND EXERCISE THEIR LEGITIMATE DEFENSE."}, {"text": "THE ARMED PEOPLE'S AND REVOLUTIONARY STRUGGLE HEADED BY THE FMLN IS JUST, LEGITIMATE, AND NECESSARY."}, {"text": "(WORDS INDISTINCT) TWO-FACED CRISTIANI ADMINISTRATION, THE FMLN HAS DECIDED TO IMMEDIATELY CONTACT THE DIALOGUE OBSERVERS AND THE CHURCH, WHICH IS THE MEDIATOR, TO DEMAND THROUGH THEM GUARANTEES FOR OPPOSITION CIVIC AND LABOR GROUPS AND A REVIEW OF THE CURRENT CONDITIONS OF THE DIALOGUE, NEGOTIATION PROCESS, AND ITS PROSPECTS."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, WE BELIEVE THAT IT IS NECESSARY TO SUSPEND OUR PARTICIPATION IN THE CARACAS MEETING."}, {"text": "(SIGNED) FMLN GENERAL COMMAND: COMMANDERS SALVADOR SANCHEZ CEREN, FRANCISCO JOVEL, SHAFIK JORGE HANDAL, EDUARDO SANCHO, AND JOAQUIN VILLALOBOS EL SALVADOR, 2 NOVEMBER 1989"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0013",
