{"sentences": [{"text": "THE FMLN REPORTS TO OUR PEOPLE AND THE PEOPLE OF THE WORLD THE FOLLOWING: 1. THE MASSACRE AGAINST THE SALVADORAN WORKERS NATIONAL UNION FEDERATION (FENASTRAS) WAS PLANNED IN COLD BLOOD."}, {"text": "THE SITE AND THE MOMENT WHEN THE FENASTRAS LEADERS WERE MEETING HAD BEEN SELECTED."}, {"text": "2. WE HAVE TRUSTWORTHY INFORMATION FROM OUR INTELLIGENCE ORGANS THAT THIS ACTION WAS ORDERED BY COLONEL PONCE, THAT CRISTIANI KNEW ABOUT IT AND APPROVED IT, AND THAT IT WAS CARRIED OUT BY COLONEL ELENA FUENTE AS THE HEAD OF THE MORBID DEATH SQUAD OF THE ARMY'S 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE IN RESPONSE TO OUR MILITARY ATTACK ON THE ARMY STAFF."}, {"text": "THIS BEHAVIOR BY CRISTIANI SHOULD SURPRISE NO ONE."}, {"text": "TERRORISM IS AN OLD PRACTICE OF THE NATIONALIST REPUBLICAN ALLIANCE (ARENA)."}, {"text": "ONLY A FEW DAYS AGO, ARENA ASSASSINS TRIED TO KILL THE PRESIDENT OF THE MORTGAGE BANK, MR MASON, FOR NOT FOLLOWING THEIR ORDERS."}, {"text": "3. THE PEOPLE DEMAND THE RESIGNATION OF CHIEF OF STAFF COL EMILIO PONCE BECAUSE HIS RESPONSIBILITY IN THIS CRIMINAL ACTION IS REAL."}, {"text": "4. THE FMLN HAS PRUDENTLY TAKEN TIME BEFORE ADOPTING A DEFINITE POSITION."}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT AND THE ARMED FORCES HAVE ADOPTED AN IRRESPONSIBLE ATTITUDE AND HAVE BRAZENLY ACCUSED THE FMLN OF THE CRIMES THEY COMMIT."}, {"text": "IN VIEW OF THIS ATTITUDE AND OF THE PEOPLE'S INDIGNATION, WE HAVE TO PREVENT OUR PRESENCE AT THE DIALOGUE FROM BEING USED TO COVER UP THE GOVERNMENT'S RESPONSIBILITY IN THIS MASSACRE AND TO ENHANCE THE MASK OF MODERATOR AND NEGOTIATOR THAT CRISTIANI HAS BEEN USING TO SECURE POLITICAL SUPPORT AND U.S. FINANCIAL SUPPORT TO EXTEND THE WAR."}, {"text": "IN SAN JOSE, SPEAKING ON ITS VIEW OF THE WAR, THE GOVERNMENT SAID THAT IT CONSIDERS POPULAR MOVEMENTS AS SUPPORT ORGANIZATIONS OF THE FMLN, AND THEREFORE, AS ENEMIES OF THE GOVERNMENT IN THE ARMED CONFLICT."}, {"text": "WE DEMANDED THAT THE GOVERNMENT DELEGATION GIVE US A LIST OF THOSE ORGANIZATIONS, BUT TO NO AVAIL."}, {"text": "THE TERRORIST ATTACKS AND MASSACRES ARE NOW YIELDING THE LISTS THAT WERE DENIED TO US AT THE DIALOGUE TABLE."}, {"text": "EVEN BEFORE THE SAN JOSE MEETING, THE GOVERNMENT HAD GREATLY INCREASED ITS REPRESSION."}, {"text": "SINCE THE MEETING, IT HAS INCREASED ITS DETENTIONS AND ATTACKED THE RESIDENCES OF LEADERS OF THE SOCIAL CHRISTIAN PEOPLE'S MOVEMENT AND THE UDN (NATIONALIST DEMOCRATIC UNION), UNIVERSITY, FECMASAN (MSGR OSCAR ARNULFO ROMERO FEDERATION OF COMMITTEES OF MOTHERS AND RELATIVES), AND FENASTRAS."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, CRISTIANI IS MAINTAINING HIS HYPOCRITICAL POSITION OF MODERATION."}, {"text": "THE MASSACRES, DETENTIONS, AND REPRESSION OF EARTHQUAKE VICTIMS, THE REPATRIATED, UNIVERSITIES, LABOR UNIONS, PEASANT COOPERATIVES, MOTHERS' ORGANIZATIONS, AND OTHER SEGMENTS OF THE POPULATION SHOW THAT THE WAR OF THE ARMED FORCES, GOVERNMENT, AND ARENA IS AIMED AGAINST THE PEOPLE AND, THEREFORE, THESE GROUPS CANNOT AND WILL NOT REMAIN IDLE."}, {"text": "THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE HAVE THE RIGHT TO TAKE UP ARMS AND EXERCISE THEIR LEGITIMATE DEFENSE."}, {"text": "THE ARMED PEOPLE'S AND REVOLUTIONARY STRUGGLE HEADED BY THE FMLN IS JUST, LEGITIMATE, AND NECESSARY."}, {"text": "(WORDS INDISTINCT) TWO-FACED CRISTIANI ADMINISTRATION, THE FMLN HAS DECIDED TO IMMEDIATELY CONTACT THE DIALOGUE OBSERVERS AND THE CHURCH, WHICH IS THE MEDIATOR, TO DEMAND THROUGH THEM GUARANTEES FOR OPPOSITION CIVIC AND LABOR GROUPS AND A REVIEW OF THE CURRENT CONDITIONS OF THE DIALOGUE, NEGOTIATION PROCESS, AND ITS PROSPECTS."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, WE BELIEVE THAT IT IS NECESSARY TO SUSPEND OUR PARTICIPATION IN THE CARACAS MEETING."}, {"text": "(SIGNED) FMLN GENERAL COMMAND: COMMANDERS SALVADOR SANCHEZ CEREN, FRANCISCO JOVEL, SHAFIK JORGE HANDAL, EDUARDO SANCHO, AND JOAQUIN VILLALOBOS EL SALVADOR, 2 NOVEMBER 1989"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0013", {"sentences": [{"text": "FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN) URBAN COMMANDOS HAVE DENIED REPORTS THEY PARTICIPATED IN AN ATTACK ON VICE PRESIDENT-ELECT FRANCISCO MERINO'S HOME."}, {"text": "AT 0530 THIS MORNING, UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS PLACED THREE EXPLOSIVE DEVICES AT THE MAIN ENTRANCE OF MERINO'S HOME IN THE MACHILIGUAS NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "TWO OF THE DEVICES EXPLODED."}, {"text": "REPORTS INDICATE THAT THE PERPETRATORS, WHO ARRIVED IN A VEHICLE, ALSO FIRED AT THE GUARDS PROTECTING MERINO'S RESIDENCE."}, {"text": "EARLY REPORTS POINTED TO URBAN COMMANDOS AS THE PRESUMED PERPETRATORS, BUT A SPOKESMAN FOR THE MODESTO RAMIREZ CENTRAL FRONT, IN A TELEPHONE CALL, DENIED THE REPORT."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (UNIDENTIFIED FMLN SPOKESMAN) ON THIS OCCASION, THE FMLN MUST EXPLAIN THAT OUR FORCES DID NOT PARTICIPATE IN THE ATTACK IN QUESTION."}, {"text": "THE FMLN WARNS THAT THE ARMED FORCES ARE TAKING ADVANTAGE OF THE SITUATION TO CREATE CONFUSION AND PROMOTE TRUE STATE TERRORISM."}, {"text": "THE FMLN CONDEMNS THE (WORD INDISTINCT) AGAINST OUR PEOPLE AND WARNS THAT THESE ACTIONS WILL NOT BE ALLOWED TO TAKE PLACE WITHOUT THE APPROPRIATE RESPONSE."}, {"text": "THE FMLN CLAIMS RESPONSIBILITY FOR ACTIONS IN WHICH IT IS DIRECTLY INVOLVED."}, {"text": "IN THIS CASE, WE WERE NOT DIRECTLY INVOLVED."}, {"text": "THE FMLN WARNS THAT THE ARMED FORCES ARE TAKING ADVANTAGE OF THIS SITUATION TO PERPETRATE ATTACKS ON INDIVIDUALS AND INSTITUTIONS WHICH CAN BE EASILY ATTRIBUTED TO THE FMLN."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) THE FMLN DESCRIBED STATEMENTS MADE BY PRESIDENT-ELECT ALFREDO CRISTIANI AS IRRESPONSIBLE."}, {"text": "THE PRESIDENT-ELECT IMMEDIATELY CONDEMNED THE ATTACK AND ATTRIBUTED IT TO THE URBAN COMMANDOS."}, {"text": "AS A RESULT OF THE ATTACK, A 15-YEAR-OLD GIRL WAS WOUNDED AND CONSIDERABLE DAMAGE WAS REPORTED."}, {"text": "MERINO IS CURRENTLY OUT OF THE COUNTRY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0017", {"sentences": [{"text": "FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN) URBAN COMMANDOS HAVE DENIED REPORTS THEY PARTICIPATED IN AN ATTACK ON VICE PRESIDENT-ELECT FRANCISCO MERINO'S HOME."}, {"text": "AT 0530 THIS MORNING, UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS PLACED THREE EXPLOSIVE DEVICES AT THE MAIN ENTRANCE OF MERINO'S HOME IN THE MACHILIGUAS NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "TWO OF THE DEVICES EXPLODED."}, {"text": "REPORTS INDICATE THAT THE PERPETRATORS, WHO ARRIVED IN A VEHICLE, ALSO FIRED AT THE GUARDS PROTECTING MERINO'S RESIDENCE."}, {"text": "EARLY REPORTS POINTED TO URBAN COMMANDOS AS THE PRESUMED PERPETRATORS, BUT A SPOKESMAN FOR THE MODESTO RAMIREZ CENTRAL FRONT, IN A TELEPHONE CALL, DENIED THE REPORT."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (UNIDENTIFIED FMLN SPOKESMAN) ON THIS OCCASION, THE FMLN MUST EXPLAIN THAT OUR FORCES DID NOT PARTICIPATE IN THE ATTACK IN QUESTION."}, {"text": "THE FMLN WARNS THAT THE ARMED FORCES ARE TAKING ADVANTAGE OF THE SITUATION TO CREATE CONFUSION AND PROMOTE TRUE STATE TERRORISM."}, {"text": "THE FMLN CONDEMNS THE (WORD INDISTINCT) AGAINST OUR PEOPLE AND WARNS THAT THESE ACTIONS WILL NOT BE ALLOWED TO TAKE PLACE WITHOUT THE APPROPRIATE RESPONSE."}, {"text": "THE FMLN CLAIMS RESPONSIBILITY FOR ACTIONS IN WHICH IT IS DIRECTLY INVOLVED."}, {"text": "IN THIS CASE, WE WERE NOT DIRECTLY INVOLVED."}, {"text": "THE FMLN WARNS THAT THE ARMED FORCES ARE TAKING ADVANTAGE OF THIS SITUATION TO PERPETRATE ATTACKS ON INDIVIDUALS AND INSTITUTIONS WHICH CAN BE EASILY ATTRIBUTED TO THE FMLN."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) THE FMLN DESCRIBED STATEMENTS MADE BY PRESIDENT-ELECT ALFREDO CRISTIANI AS IRRESPONSIBLE."}, {"text": "THE PRESIDENT-ELECT IMMEDIATELY CONDEMNED THE ATTACK AND ATTRIBUTED IT TO THE URBAN COMMANDOS."}, {"text": "AS A RESULT OF THE ATTACK, A 15-YEAR-OLD GIRL WAS WOUNDED AND CONSIDERABLE DAMAGE WAS REPORTED."}, {"text": "MERINO IS CURRENTLY OUT OF THE COUNTRY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0017", {"sentences": [{"text": "GUERRILLAS ATTACKED THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE GARRISON AND THE NATIONAL POLICE STATION IN SAN SALVADOR'S SACAMIL NEIGHBORHOOD TONIGHT."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO PRELIMINARY REPORTS, AT LEAST SIX FMLN GUERRILLAS WERE KILLED DURING THE ATTACK."}, {"text": "THREE POLICEMEN, A SOLDIER OF THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE, AND FOUR CIVILIANS WERE WOUNDED AND TAKEN BY THE RED CROSS TO THE LOCAL HOSPITAL."}, {"text": "URBAN GUERRILLAS BEGAN THE ATTACK AT 1805."}, {"text": "THEY STRUCK BOTH THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE AND THE NATIONAL POLICE STATION IN THE SACAMIL NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (UNIDENTIFIED MILITARY OFFICER) THE GUERRILLAS USED 60-MM MORTARS AND RPG-18 ROCKET LAUNCHERS."}, {"text": "THE TERRORISTS TRAVELED IN CARS."}, {"text": "THEY DESTROYED SEVERAL POWER POLES ON 29TH STREET AND MACHINEGUNNED SEVERAL TRANSFORMERS."}, {"text": "THE ATTACK CAME MAINLY FROM THE SOUTH, WHERE THE COHACHE ORGANIZATION IS LOCATED, AND FROM THE HONDUA CHURCH HERE."}, {"text": "THEY ALSO ATTACKED FROM THE NORTHEAST, BUT MOST OF THE ATTACKERS CAME FROM THE DIRECTION OF THE NATIONAL UNIVERSITY, FIRING FROM THERE AT SOME (WORD INDISTINCT) WE HAVE IN THE AREA."}, {"text": "WE HAD REMOVED THE CORDON AROUND THE UNIVERSITY 4 OR 5 DAYS AGO, AND (WORDS INDISTINCT) FIRED FROM THERE."}, {"text": "THE WOUNDED INCLUDE AT LEAST THREE CIVILIANS, ONE OF WHOM IS IN SERIOUS CONDITION AND HAS ALREADY BEEN TAKEN BY OUR TROOPS TO THE MILITARY HOSPITAL; PERHAPS FIVE TRAFFIC POLICEMEN, ALTHOUGH THIS HAS NOT BEEN CONFIRMED; AND A SOLDIER OF THE BELLOSO BATTALION."}, {"text": "NO DAMAGE WAS CAUSED HERE AT THE GARRISON."}, {"text": "ONLY A FEW SHELLS HIT THE GARRISON, AND THESE WERE 60-MM MORTAR SHELLS, WHICH ARE NOT POWERFUL ENOUGH TO CAUSE DAMAGE."}, {"text": "WE FOUND SIX (WORDS INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "AS FOR THE RPG'S, WE FOUND ONLY ONE (WORDS INDISTINCT) BEHIND THE ANTEL (NATIONAL ADMINISTRATION FOR TELECOMMUNICATIONS) OFFICE (WORDS INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "WE FOUND SIX HOLES FROM M-79 SHELLS, BUT THEY DID NOT CAUSE GREAT DAMAGE."}, {"text": "ONE OF OUR CIVILIAN EMPLOYEES CAME OUT SLIGHTLY WOUNDED FROM THE (WORD INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "(REPORTER) COLONEL, OUR COUNTRY WILL HAVE A NEW PRESIDENT IN A FEW DAYS."}, {"text": "THE FMLN HAS CALLED A NEW TRANSPORTATION STOPPAGE BEGINNING ON 31 MAY AND HAS NOW ATTACKED THE 1ST BRIGADE."}, {"text": "BASED ON THIS EVIDENCE, DO YOU FEEL THE FMLN WILL INTENSIFY ITS MILITARY ACTIONS IN SAN SALVADOR?"}, {"text": "(MILITARY OFFICER) OF COURSE, WE ARE EXPECTING THIS."}, {"text": "CHANNEL 12 HAS ALREADY REPORTED THAT A TRANSPORTATION STOPPAGE WILL BEGIN ON 31 MAY."}, {"text": "THEREFORE, WE BELIEVE VIGILANCE MUST BE INCREASED."}, {"text": "WE EXPECTED THIS KIND OF ATTACK."}, {"text": "WE HAVE ALWAYS SAID WE ARE PREPARED TO REPEL ANY TERRORIST ATTACK, AND THIS WAS A TYPICAL TERRORIST ATTACK."}, {"text": "FROM A MILITARY STANDPOINT, I DO NOT THINK THE ATTACK WAS VERY EFFECTIVE."}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLAS USED MORTARS BUT MOSTLY HURT CIVILIANS."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0018", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": "LA PAZ DEPARTMENT POLICE AUTHORITIES HAVE DISCLOSED THAT INVESTIGATIONS INTO THE MURDER OF TWO YOUNG U.S. CITIZENS ARE BEING CONDUCTED BY A SPECIALIZED GROUP (NOT FURTHER IDENTIFIED) SUMMONED SPECIALLY TO CLARIFY THIS CRIME."}, {"text": "COLONEL ARMANDO SANTAGORDA, IN A STATEMENT TO PANAMERICANA, SAID THAT HIS GROUP IS SUPPORTED BY THE CHIEF OF POLICE, WHO HAS GIVEN PRECISE INSTRUCTIONS FOR ALL POLICEMEN TO COOPERATE IN THE INVESTIGATIONS."}, {"text": "MOREOVER, HE SAID THAT HE KNEW NOTHING ABOUT THE ARRIVAL IN THE PAST FEW HOURS OF SPECIALIZED U.S. POLICEMEN, ALLEGEDLY HERE TO COOPERATE IN THE INVESTIGATIONS THAT, SO FAR, ARE UNDER THE COMMAND AND RESPONSIBILITY OF THE BOLIVIAN POLICE FORCES."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, SANTAGORDA ASSERTED THAT THE INSTITUTION, IN COMPLIANCE WITH INTERNATIONAL AGREEMENTS, IS IN PERMANENT CONTACT WITH POLICE FORCES OF OTHER COUNTRIES THROUGH INTERPOL."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT REGARDING THE CASE OF THE MURDERED U.S. CITIZENS, THE POLICE ARE ALSO EXCHANGING INFORMATION BECAUSE THE INCIDENT IS OF AN INTERNATIONAL NATURE."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT HE BASED HIS DECLARATIONS ON THE PRELIMINARY INFORMATION OBTAINED SHORTLY AFTER {"sentences": [{"text": "BLOOD IS FLOWING IN COLUMBIA, MORE ABUNDANTLY EVERY YEAR."}, {"text": "LAST YEAR, ACCORDING TO OFFICIAL STATISTICS, THERE WERE 4,600 VICTIMS OF POLITICAL VIOLENCE."}, {"text": "ABOUT HALF OF THOSE KILLED WERE PEASANTS."}, {"text": "AN "INTERNAL WAR," UNLEASHED BY THE OLIGARCHY MANY YEARS AGO, IS BEING WAGED AGAINST THEM."}, {"text": "THE ACTIVISTS OF THE COALITION OF LEFT-WING PARTIES AND ORGANIZATIONS, WITH THE PARTICIPATION OF THE COMMUNISTS -- THE PATRIOTIC UNION -- COME NEXT, AFTER THE PEASANTS."}, {"text": "THE PEOPLE KILLED INCLUDE JAIME PARDO LEAL, PRESIDENT OF ITS NATIONAL COORDINATION COMMITTEE, AROUND 30 DEPUTIES, AND MANY MUNICIPAL ADVISORS AND MAYORS."}, {"text": "THE ORGANIZERS OF THE "DIRTY WAR" AND THE LEADERS OF THE "DEATH SQUADS," AND OTHER ULTRA-RIGHT-WING FORMATIONS AND THEIR HIRED KILLERS, FEEL THAT THEY CAN GO UNPUNISHED."}, {"text": "THE RESPONSE TO THE TERROR OF THE RIGHT HAS THE ARMED STRUGGLE WHICH HAS CONTINUED FOR MANY YEARS AND LEFT-WING EXTREMISM."}, {"text": "IN THE PAST FEW YEARS, VICTIMS OF POLITICAL TERROR ALSO INCLUDED REPRESENTATIVES OF THE RULING CIRCLES AND THEIR LAW-ENFORCEMENT ORGANS, WAGING AN UNEQUAL STRUGGLE AGAINST THE POWERFUL NARCOTICS MAFIA."}, {"text": "AS A "SHADOW ECONOMY," IT IS TRYING TO BECOME PART OF THE STATE STRUCTURE."}, {"text": "IN THE PAST YEAR THE NARCOTICS BUSINESS HAS "ENRICHED" THE COUNTRY'S ECONOMY WITH $2 BILLION AND EVEN PROPOSED THAT IT WOULD PAY OFF THE GIGANTIC FOREIGN DEBT."}, {"text": "THE NARCOTICS MAFIA CARRIES OUT REPRISALS AGAINST ITS OPPONENTS."}, {"text": "THE MINISTER OF JUSTICE, A MEMBER OF THE SUPREME COURT, A DIRECTOR OF THE BIGGEST NEWSPAPER ESPECTADOR, AND, A FEW DAYS AGO, ANTONIO ROLDAN BETANCUR, GOVERNOR OF THE DEPARTMENT OF ANTIOQUIA WERE KILLED."}, {"text": "MANY PROSECUTORS AND JUDGES ARE LEAVING THE COUNTRY THROUGH FEAR FOR THEIR OWN LIVES AND THOSE OF THEIR RELATIVES."}, {"text": "THE VIOLENCE IS ESCALATING AND THE IMPRESSION IS BEING FORMED THAT CERTAIN FORCES ARE TRYING TO TAKE THE ATTENTION OF THE 30 MILLION STRONG POPULATION OF COLOMBIA AWAY FROM THE URGENT RESOLUTION OF PRESSING SOCIAL PROBLEMS BY DESTABILIZING INTERNAL LIFE."}, {"text": "SOVIET SOCIETY, IN THE NAME OF OBSERVING BASIC HUMAN RIGHTS AND CHARITY, CONSIDERS THAT OUR CONSCIENCE CANNOT BE RECONCILED WITH THE ORGY OF POLITICAL TERROR OVERWHELMING COLOMBIA."}, {"text": "WE APPEAL TO THE PUBLIC OF THE WORLD TO RAISE THEIR VOICES AGAINST THIS EVIL IN THE NAME OF THE COMMON SOLIDARITY OF MANKIND."}, {"text": "DRASTIC ACTIONS ARE NEEDED PARTICULARLY ON BEHALF OF INTERNATIONAL AND NATIONAL LAW ENFORCEMENT ORGANIZATIONS."}, {"text": "WE CONSIDER THAT IN COLOMBIA ITSELF, DIALOGUE BETWEEN OPPOSING SIDES THAT ARE TAKING THE STAND OF PATRIOTISM AND POLITICAL REALISM IS NECESSARY."}, {"text": "THE FRUITFULNESS OF NATIONAL DIALOGUE HAS BEEN PROVED IN PRACTICE IN THE PAST FEW YEARS BY MANY COUNTRIES."}, {"text": "THE VITAL INTERESTS OF THE TORMENTED COLOMBIAN PEOPLE CALL FOR CIVIL PEACE."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0023", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 12 JUL {"sentences": [{"text": "FOR THE SECOND TIME, UNIDENTIFIED TERRORISTS DYNAMITED THE OIL PIPELINE BETWEEN HUILA DEPARTMENT AND BARRANCABERMEJA."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, ECOPETROL (COLOMBIAN PETROLEUM ENTERPRISE) WORKERS ARE REPAIRING THE CANO LIMON-COVENAS PIPELINE AND CLEANING UP THE ARAUCA RIVER ALONG THE VENEZUELAN BORDER, WHERE A HUGE OIL SPILL WAS CAUSED BY ANOTHER ATTACK AGAINST THE OIL PIPELINE."}, {"text": "AUTHORITIES CONFIRMED THAT THERE WAS A POWERFUL DYNAMITE EXPLOSION AT THE VINA-PUERTO SALGAR OIL PIPELINE, LOCATED APPROXIMATELY 30 KM FROM NATAGAIMA, IN NORTHERN HUILA DEPARTMENT, CAUSING AN UNDETERMINED AMOUNT OF CRUDE OIL TO SPILL."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE SECOND TIME IN LESS THAN 1 MONTH THAT TERRORISTS HAVE ATTACKED THE OIL PIPELINE OPERATED BY HOUSTON OIL AND ECOPETROL."}, {"text": "A FEW WEEKS AGO, TERRORISTS DESTROYED THE PIPELINE NEAR AIPE, WHICH CAUSED ANOTHER OIL SPILL."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, OPERATORS FROM THE STATE-RUN OIL COMPANY YESTERDAY BEGAN REPAIRING THE CANO LIMON-COVENAS OIL PIPELINE DYNAMITED ON THE NIGHT OF 12 JULY IN ARAUQUITA JURISDICTION, WHICH FORCED THE SUSPENSION OF OIL PUMPING FROM ARAUCA INTENDANCY'S OIL FIELDS TO THE GULF OF MORROSQUILLO."}, {"text": "MEMBERS OF THE CONTINGENCY TEAM SUPPORTED BY PETROVEN (VENEZUELAN PETROLEUM, INC.) AND THE VENEZUELAN ENVIRONMENT AND NATURAL RESOURCES MINISTRY ARE CLEANING UP A HUGE OIL SPILL AT THE ARAUCA RIVER CAUSED BY THE 7 JULY ATTACK AGAINST THE CANO LIMON-COVENAS OIL PIPELINE."}, {"text": "THAT ATTACK RESULTED IN A SPILL OF 13,000 BARRELS OF OIL, WHICH SEVERELY CONTAMINATED FARMING AREAS AND THE ARAUCA RIVER, TO THE POINT THAT THE POTABLE WATER SERVICE WAS TEMPORARILY SUSPENDED IN ARAUCA'S CAPITAL CITY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0024", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 14 JUL 89", "14 JUL 89"]}], {"sentences": [{"text": "FOR THE SECOND TIME, UNIDENTIFIED TERRORISTS DYNAMITED THE OIL PIPELINE BETWEEN HUILA DEPARTMENT AND BARRANCABERMEJA."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, ECOPETROL (COLOMBIAN PETROLEUM ENTERPRISE) WORKERS ARE REPAIRING THE CANO LIMON-COVENAS PIPELINE AND CLEANING UP THE ARAUCA RIVER ALONG THE VENEZUELAN BORDER, WHERE A HUGE OIL SPILL WAS CAUSED BY ANOTHER ATTACK AGAINST THE OIL PIPELINE."}, {"text": "AUTHORITIES CONFIRMED THAT THERE WAS A POWERFUL DYNAMITE EXPLOSION AT THE VINA-PUERTO SALGAR OIL PIPELINE, LOCATED APPROXIMATELY 30 KM FROM NATAGAIMA, IN NORTHERN HUILA DEPARTMENT, CAUSING AN UNDETERMINED AMOUNT OF CRUDE OIL TO SPILL."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE SECOND TIME IN LESS THAN 1 MONTH THAT TERRORISTS HAVE ATTACKED THE OIL PIPELINE OPERATED BY HOUSTON OIL AND ECOPETROL."}, {"text": "A FEW WEEKS AGO, TERRORISTS DESTROYED THE PIPELINE NEAR AIPE, WHICH CAUSED ANOTHER OIL SPILL."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, OPERATORS FROM THE STATE-RUN OIL COMPANY YESTERDAY BEGAN REPAIRING THE CANO LIMON-COVENAS OIL PIPELINE DYNAMITED ON THE NIGHT OF 12 JULY IN ARAUQUITA JURISDICTION, WHICH FORCED THE SUSPENSION OF OIL PUMPING FROM ARAUCA INTENDANCY'S OIL FIELDS TO THE GULF OF MORROSQUILLO."}, {"text": "MEMBERS OF THE CONTINGENCY TEAM SUPPORTED BY PETROVEN (VENEZUELAN PETROLEUM, INC.) {"sentences": [{"text": "TWO CRIMINAL ATTACKS, THE RESIGNATION OF THREE JUDGES, AND A 24-HOUR STRIKE BY WORKERS IN THE JUDICIAL SECTOR--THIS SUMS UP THE JUDICIAL SITUATION IN COLOMBIA OVER THE PAST 20 DAYS."}, {"text": "THE CHAOTIC SITUATION UNLEASHED IN BOGOTA LAST NIGHT WITH THE ASSASINATION OF JUSTICE CARLOS VALENCIA BEGAN ON 28 JULY IN MEDELLIN, WHEN MOTORIZED PAID ASSASINS MURDERED THIRD PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE MARIA ELENA DIAZ."}, {"text": "DIAZ' MURDER UNLEASHED A WAVE OF PROTESTS; 17,000 EMPEMPLOYEES FROM THE LEGAL SECTOR STAGED A STRIKE ON 1 AUGUST AND FORCED A STATEMENT FROM THE GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (PRESIDENT OF NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF THE JUDICIAL BRANCH ANTONIO SUAREZ)"}, {"text": "I AM WARNING THE COUNTRY THAT THE NEXT MURDER IN THE JUDICIAL BRANCH WILL NECESSARILY RESULT IN THE COLLECTIVE RESIGNATION OF ALL THE JUDGES."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) PROTECTIVE MEASURES HAVE BEEN ADOPTED FOR ALL JUDGES AND WORK CONTINUES."}, {"text": "ON 14 AUGUST, DUE TO DEATH THREATS AGAINST HIS DAUGHTER, FIRST PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE ALVARO MEDINA MORENO, WHO WAS INVESTIGATING THE WANUMEN ARMS-TRAFFICKING CASE AND THE ATTACK ON THE DAS (ADMINISTRATIVE DEPARTMENT OF SECURITY) DIRECTOR, ANNOUNCED HIS RESIGNATION."}, {"text": "TWO DAYS LATER, ON 16 AUGUST, DUE TO DEATH THREATS THE EIGHTH PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE IN MEDELLIN, WHO WAS INVESTIGATING THE GOVERNOR OF ANTIOQUIA'S MURDER, RESIGNED."}, {"text": "SHORTLY BEFORE JUSTICE VALENCIA'S MURDER YESTERDAY, THE SEVENTH PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE IN BOGOTA, WHO WAS INVESTIGATING THE SEARCH OF A BUILDING IN NORTHERN BOGOTA, DECIDED TO RESIGN AND LEAVE THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "TO CONCLUDE, THE INTIMIDATION OF JUDGES LED TO VALENCIA'S MURDER LAST NIGHT IN DOWNTOWN BOGOTA."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (UNIDENTIFIED WITNESSES) TWO PEOPLE APPROACHED VALENCIA AND BEGAN SHOOTING AT HIM."}, {"text": "VALENCIA'S BODYGUARDS STOOPED DOWN, THEY DID NOT HAVE TIME TO RESPOND."}, {"text": "WHEN THEIR ATTACKERS FLED, THE BODYGUARDS CAME OUT AND BEGAN SHOOTING WILDLY."}, {"text": "IT WAS A DANGEROUS SITUATION FOR PEOPLE IN THE AREA."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) STUPEFIED BY THE CRIMINAL ATTACKS ON THE JUDICIAL SECTOR, THE GOVERNMENT IS SEEKING WAYS TO SOLVE THE PROBLEMS OF INTIMIDATION."}, {"text": "MADRID EFE IN SPANISH AT 1824 GMT ON 17 AUGUST REPORTS THAT "ANTONIO SUAREZ NINO, PRESIDENT OF THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION FOR THE JUDICIAL BRANCH (ASONAL), HAS REPORTED THAT ALL OF COLOMBIA'S JUDGES TODAY PRESENTED THEIR RESIGNATIONS BECAUSE OF THE ASSASINATION LAST NIGHT OF JUSTICE CARLOS VALENCIA GARCIA."}, {"text": ""THE PRESIDENT OF ASONAL ANNOUNCED THE RESIGNATION EN MASSE OF THE COUNTRY'S JUDGES, SAYING THEY WILL PRESENT THEIR RESIGNATIONS AT THE COUNTRY'S HIGHER COURTS, AND HE REQUESTED A MEETING WITH COLOMBIAN PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO."}, {"text": ""ASONAL PRESIDENT ANTONIO SUAREZ SAID THAT 'IN RESPONSE TO THIS HORRIBLE MASSACRE OF THE JUDICIAL BRANCH, WE HAVE DECREED AN INDEFINITE STRIKE AND THE RESIGNATION EN MASSE OF ALL THE JUDGES, BECAUSE THE COLOMBIAN PEOPLE ARE NOT IN ANY CONDITION TO CONTINUE KILLING EACH OTHER WITH IMPUNITY WHILE THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH LOOKS ON ALMOST COMPLACENTLY.'""}, {"text": ""ASONAL ISSUED A COMMUNIQUE STATING THAT 'THIS GOVERNMENT LACKS THE AUTHENTIC POLITICAL RESOLVE TO GUARANTEE AND PROTECT THE INTEGRITY AND LIVES OF ILLUSTRIOUS FELLOW PATRIOTS SUCH AS VALENCIA.'""}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0030", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["16 AUG 89"]}], "incident_location": {"sentences": [{"text": "TWO CRIMINAL ATTACKS, THE RESIGNATION OF THREE JUDGES, AND A 24-HOUR STRIKE BY WORKERS IN THE JUDICIAL SECTOR--THIS SUMS UP THE JUDICIAL SITUATION IN COLOMBIA OVER THE PAST 20 DAYS."}, {"text": "THE CHAOTIC SITUATION UNLEASHED IN BOGOTA LAST NIGHT WITH THE ASSASINATION OF JUSTICE CARLOS VALENCIA BEGAN ON 28 JULY IN MEDELLIN, WHEN MOTORIZED PAID ASSASINS MURDERED THIRD PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE MARIA ELENA DIAZ."}, {"text": "DIAZ' MURDER UNLEASHED A WAVE OF PROTESTS; 17,000 EMPEMPLOYEES FROM THE LEGAL SECTOR STAGED A STRIKE ON 1 AUGUST AND FORCED A STATEMENT FROM THE GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (PRESIDENT OF NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF THE JUDICIAL BRANCH ANTONIO SUAREZ)"}, {"text": "I AM WARNING THE COUNTRY THAT THE NEXT MURDER IN THE JUDICIAL BRANCH WILL NECESSARILY RESULT IN THE COLLECTIVE RESIGNATION OF ALL THE JUDGES."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) PROTECTIVE MEASURES HAVE BEEN ADOPTED FOR ALL JUDGES AND WORK CONTINUES."}, {"text": "ON 14 AUGUST, DUE TO DEATH THREATS AGAINST HIS DAUGHTER, FIRST PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE ALVARO MEDINA MORENO, WHO WAS INVESTIGATING THE WANUMEN ARMS-TRAFFICKING CASE AND THE ATTACK ON THE DAS (ADMINISTRATIVE DEPARTMENT OF SECURITY) DIRECTOR, ANNOUNCED HIS RESIGNATION."}, {"text": "TWO DAYS LATER, ON 16 AUGUST, DUE TO DEATH THREATS THE EIGHTH PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE IN MEDELLIN, WHO WAS INVESTIGATING THE GOVERNOR OF ANTIOQUIA'S MURDER, RESIGNED."}, {"text": "SHORTLY BEFORE JUSTICE VALENCIA'S MURDER YESTERDAY, THE SEVENTH PUBLIC ORDER JUDGE IN BOGOTA, WHO WAS INVESTIGATING THE SEARCH OF A BUILDING IN NORTHERN BOGOTA, DECIDED TO RESIGN AND LEAVE THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "TO CONCLUDE, THE INTIMIDATION OF JUDGES LED TO VALENCIA'S MURDER LAST NIGHT IN DOWNTOWN BOGOTA."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (UNIDENTIFIED WITNESSES) TWO PEOPLE APPROACHED VALENCIA AND BEGAN SHOOTING AT HIM."}, {"text": "VALENCIA'S BODYGUARDS STOOPED DOWN, THEY DID NOT HAVE TIME TO RESPOND."}, {"text": "WHEN THEIR ATTACKERS FLED, THE BODYGUARDS CAME OUT AND BEGAN SHOOTING WILDLY."}, {"text": "IT WAS A DANGEROUS SITUATION FOR PEOPLE IN THE AREA."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) STUPEFIED BY THE CRIMINAL ATTACKS ON THE JUDICIAL SECTOR, THE GOVERNMENT IS SEEKING WAYS TO SOLVE THE PROBLEMS OF INTIMIDATION."}, {"text": "MADRID EFE IN SPANISH AT 1824 GMT ON 17 AUGUST REPORTS THAT "ANTONIO SUAREZ NINO, PRESIDENT OF THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION FOR THE JUDICIAL BRANCH (ASONAL), HAS REPORTED THAT ALL OF COLOMBIA'S JUDGES TODAY PRESENTED THEIR RESIGNATIONS BECAUSE OF THE ASSASINATION LAST NIGHT OF JUSTICE CARLOS VALENCIA GARCIA."}, {"text": ""THE PRESIDENT OF ASONAL ANNOUNCED THE RESIGNATION EN MASSE OF THE COUNTRY'S JUDGES, SAYING THEY WILL PRESENT THEIR RESIGNATIONS AT THE COUNTRY'S HIGHER COURTS, AND HE REQUESTED A MEETING WITH COLOMBIAN PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO."}, {"text": ""ASONAL PRESIDENT ANTONIO SUAREZ SAID THAT 'IN RESPONSE TO THIS HORRIBLE MASSACRE OF THE JUDICIAL BRANCH, WE HAVE DECREED AN INDEFINITE STRIKE AND THE RESIGNATION EN MASSE OF ALL THE JUDGES, BECAUSE THE COLOMBIAN PEOPLE ARE NOT IN ANY CONDITION TO CONTINUE KILLING EACH OTHER WITH IMPUNITY WHILE THE EXECUTIVE BRANCH LOOKS ON ALMOST COMPLACENTLY.'""}, {"text": ""ASONAL ISSUED A COMMUNIQUE STATING THAT 'THIS GOVERNMENT LACKS THE AUTHENTIC POLITICAL RESOLVE TO GUARANTEE AND PROTECT THE INTEGRITY AND LIVES OF ILLUSTRIOUS FELLOW PATRIOTS SUCH AS VALENCIA.'""}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0030", "message_template": 3, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 14 AUG 89"]}], "incident_location": {"sentences": [{"text": "DURING THE PAST FEW DAYS, VIOLENCE IN COLOMBIA HAS TAKEN SPECTACULAR TURNS."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO A REPORT WHICH CITES RELIABLE SOURCES, IT SEEMS THAT THE HAND OF DRUG TRAFFICKERS IS BEHIND THE ASSASSINATIONS OF JUDGE CARLOS VALENCIA, OF THE BOGOTA (WORDS INDISTINCT), WHICH OCCURRED YESTERDAY (18 AUGUST)."}, {"text": "THE COLOMBIAN DRUG MAFIA HAS CREATED A GREAT MONEY AND CRIME EMPIRE IN COLOMBIA WITH POWERFUL RAMIFICATIONS OUTSIDE ITS BORDERS, ESPECIALLY IN THE UNITED STATES -- THE MAIN CONSUMER OF COCAINE AND OTHER DRUGS IN THE WORLD."}, {"text": "YESTERDAY (18 AUGUST), VENEZUELAN PRESIDENT CARLOS ANDRES PEREZ SPOKE ON THE PHONE WITH HIS COLOMBIAN COUNTERPART, VIRGILIO BARCO, AND IT IS SAID THAT THE MAIN SUBJECT OF THEIR CONVERSATION WAS THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN YOUTH DELINQUENCY AND DRUG TRAFFICKING."}, {"text": "IT IS IMPORTANT TO NOTE THE WORDS OF VENEZUELAN PRESIDENT CARLOS ANDRES PEREZ."}, {"text": "WE MUST REFLECT, SAID CARLOS ANDRES PEREZ, ON THE NEED FOR US, ALL VENEZUELANS, TO FACE DRUG TRAFFICKING IN VENEZUELA."}, {"text": "WE MUST ALSO ACKNOWLEDGE THAT DRUG TRAFFICKING IS THE ABOMINABLE CRIME OF OUR TIMES, AND THAT THERE CANNOT BE ANY HESITATION OR COMPASSION TOWARD DRUG TRAFFICKERS."}, {"text": "THOSE ARE THE WORDS OF VENEZUELAN PRESIDENT CARLOS ANDRES PEREZ."}, {"text": "IN REALITY, THE DRUG TRAFFICKING DRAMA IS SERIOUSLY AFFECTING SEVERAL LATIN AMERICAN COUNTRIES."}, {"text": "WE HAVE THE DRAMATIC CASE OF COLOMBIA, BUT THE SITUATION ALSO EXISTS IN VENEZUELA, BOLIVIA, PERU, WELL, IN SEVERAL LATIN AMERICAN COUNTRIES."}, {"text": "NOW, THE SOLUTION TO THAT PROBLEM...(REPHRASES) AS HAS BEEN POINTED OUT BY LATIN AMERICANS THEMSELVES AND THEIR MOST PROMINENT FIGURES, THE FINAL SOLUTION TO THE DRAMATIC DRUG TRAFFICKING PROBLEM MUST BE BASED ON PUTTING AN END TO THE CONSUMPTION OF DRUGS."}, {"text": "THAT IS THE MAIN STUMBLING BLOCK IN THE FIGHT AGAINST DRUG TRAFFICKING."}, {"text": "THE UNITED STATES IS THE MAIN CONSUMPTION CENTER OF DRUGS IN THE WORLD, AND U.S. POLICY ON DRUG TRAFFICKING IS NOT CONSISTENT WITH THE NEED TO PUT AN END AND ACTIVELY REPRESS THE CONSUMPTION OF DRUGS."}, {"text": "U.S. POLICY, AND ALL THIS IS VERY WELL KNOWN IN LATIN AMERICA, IS BASED ON DESTROYING THE PLANTATIONS OF A NATIVE PLANT IN THE CONTINENT, WHICH IS COCA."}, {"text": "PRESIDENTS, POLITICAL AND SOCIAL FIGURES OF THE CONTINENT HAVE SAID THAT THE SOLUTION IS NOT BASED ON THE DESTRUCTION OF A NATIVE PLANT BUT IN ACTIVE FIGHT AGAINST DRUG CONSUMPTION."}, {"text": "I THINK THAT THE STATEMENTS MADE BY THE PRESIDENT OF VENEZUELA AND THE DRAMATIC SITUATION THAT COLOMBIA IS FACING THESE DAYS CONFIRM THAT THE POLICY FOR FIGHTING DRUG TRAFFICKING MUST BE TENACIOUS, STRONG, WITHOUT HESITATION AND COMPASSION."}, {"text": "IT MUST ALSO BE BASED ON ENDING DRUG CONSUMPTION BY THE UNITED STATES -- THE MAIN DRUG CONSUMER OF THE WORLD -- WHICH LIVES PRECISELY FROM DRUG CONSUMPTION AND ITS BUSINESS."}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "THE ISRAELI EMBASSY IN BOGOTA TODAY CONFIRMED THAT THERE ARE ISRAELI TERRORISTS IN COLOMBIA ENGAGED IN TRAINING RIGHT-WING PARAMILITARY GROUPS THAT, ACCORDING TO INVESTIGATIONS, ARE FINANCED BY DRUG-TRAFFICKING MAFIAS."}, {"text": "ISRAELI CHARGE D'AFFAIRS MICHEL RONEN ADMITTED THERE ARE SEVERAL ISRAELIS ENGAGED IN THAT ILLEGAL ACTIVITY, BUT WARNED THAT THEY DO SO "ON THEIR OWN AND DO NOT ACT ON BEHALF OF MY GOVERNMENT.""}, {"text": "MOREOVER, THIS OFFICIAL DENIED THAT JUBIZ HAZVUMB, CAPTURED 22 AUGUST BY COLOMBIAN AUTHORITIES FOR HIS ALLEGED INVOLVEMENT IN THE MURDER OF SENATOR AND PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE LUIS CARLOS GALAN, WAS AN ISRAELI CITIZEN."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO PRELIMINARY REPORTS REVEALED BY THE PRESS, THE SUSPECT IS AN ISRAELI MERCENARY PAID BY THE MEDELLIN CARTEL -- THE WORLD'S MOST POWERFUL DRUG-TRAFFICKING MAFIA -- THAT APPEARS TO BE DIRECTLY LINKED TO THE MURDERS OF GALAN, A HIGH-RANKING POLICE OFFICER, AND A JUDGE LAST WEEK."}, {"text": "REPORTS DISCLOSING THE PRESENCE OF THESE TERRORISTS IN COLOMBIA APPEARED SEVERAL MONTHS AGO WHEN TELEVISION CLIPS SHOWED A MAN GIVING INSTRUCTIONS IN HEBREW TO A RIGHT-WING PARAMILITARY SQUAD."}, {"text": "SIMILAR CLIPS WERE BROADCAST BY THE U.S. TELEVISION NETWORK NBC, PROMPTING A COMMUNIQUE FROM JERUSALEM WHICH REQUESTED COLOMBIAN AUTHORITIES AND INTERPOL TO PROVIDE ALL INFORMATION ON THE MATTER."}, {"text": "ACORDING TO THE ISRAELI OFFICIAL, THE TERRORISTS' ACTIONS IN COLOMBIA RUN "COUNTER TO ISRAEL'S POLICIES.""}, {"text": "INVESTIGATIONS BY THE ADMINISTRATIVE DEPARTMENT OF SECURITY (DAS) -- THE STATE'S INTELLIGENCE CORPS -- DISCLOSED THE LINKS BETWEEN THE DRUG-TRAFFICKING MAFIAS AND ULTRARIGHT-WING PARAMILITARY GROUPS."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO DAS DIRECTOR GENERAL MIGUEL MAZA MARQUEZ, THE DRUG-TRAFFICKING ORGANIZATIONS, ESPECIALLY THE MEDELLIN CARTEL, SET UP SEVERAL "SCHOOLS FOR GUNMEN" IN A VAST REGION IN THE INTERIOR OF THE COUNTRY WITH ISRAELI, BRITISH, U.S. AND WEST GERMAN TERRORIST INSTRUCTORS."}, {"text": "MOREOVER, NBC WARNED OF THE PRESENCE OF SOUTH AFRICANS."}, {"text": "THE PARAMILITARY SQUADS ARE ACCUSED OF HUNDREDS OF INDIVIDUAL MURDERS AND MASSACRES AGAINST POLITICAL AND LABOR LEADERS, AS WELL AS PEASANTS AND PATRIOTIC UNION LEFTIST MILITANTS IN DIFFERENT PARTS OF THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "THE AUTHORITIES ARE ACCUSING THESE SQUADS' KILLERS OF BEING BEHIND THE CRIME WAVE THE COUNTRY HAS BEEN EXPERIENCING SINCE LAST WEEK, WITH THE MURDERS OF PEOPLE KNOWN FOR THEIR ACTIVITIES AGAINST COCAINE TRAFFICKING."}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "THE STATION ANNOUNCER THEN LISTS WAR BULLETINS FROM GUAZAPA, FROM THE WESTERN PART OF THE COUNTRY, FROM THE METROPOLITAN AREA, AND FROM THE FRANCISCO SANCHEZ EASTERN FRONT."}, {"text": "THE ANNOUNCER REMINDS LISTENERS THAT THESE REPORTS WERE NOT INCLUDED IN THE WEEK'S EVENTS AND SAYS: "THE FIRST REPORT IS FROM THE MODESTO RAMIREZ CENTRAL FRONT, GUAZAPA AREA."}, {"text": "AT 1000 ON 10 AUGUST, SAN CARLOS BATTALION TROOPS BELONGING TO THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE WALKED INTO A MINED FIELD, WHICH LEFT TWO SOLDIERS INJURED AT SAN JOSE GUAYABAL JURISDICTION, CUSCATLAN DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "AT 1800 ON 12 AUGUST, THE SAN CARLOS BATTALION CAME ACROSS MINES PLACED IN THEIR PATH AT LOS LIRIOS."}, {"text": "ONE SOLDIER WAS KILLED AND TWO WERE SERIOUSLY INJURED."}, {"text": "AT 1300 ON 13 AUGUST, ATLACATL BATTALION UNITS WALKED INTO A MINED FIELD, AND THERE WERE TWO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "AT 1330 ANOTHER ATLACATL BATTALION UNIT WALKED INTO A MINED FIELD AT CERRO CAMPANARIO, GUAZAPA HILL, CAUSING ONE MORE CASUALTY."}, {"text": "AT 1900 ON 10 AUGUST, URBAN COMMANDOS TOOK A PATROL CAR BY SURPRISE."}, {"text": "THEY DROPPED A GRENADE INSIDE THE CAR, INJURING FOUR AND PARTIALLY DESTROYING THE VEHICLE.""}, {"text": "THE ANNOUNCER CONTINUES: "THIS SUCCESSFUL OPERATION TOOK PLACE OUTSIDE THE AVENIDA CINEMA IN SAN SALVADOR, SCARCELY ONE BLOCK FROM A NATIONAL GUARD GARRISON.""}, {"text": "THE STATION ANNOUNCER LISTS ITS REPORTS FROM SANTA ANA: "AT 0415 ON 12 AUGUST WE INFLICTED FOUR CASUALTIES AMONG TROOPS BELONGING TO THE 2ND INFANTRY BRIGADE AT (WORDS INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "AT 1715 ANOTHER CASUALTY WAS INFLICTED AT EL PEAR FARM."}, {"text": "AT 0130 ON 12 AUGUST WE INFLICTED ONE MORE CASUALTY AT PUERTAS NEGRAS.""}, {"text": "THE ANNOUNCER ENDS HIS REPORT BY STATING: "THE FRANCISCO SANCHEZ EASTERN FRONT REPORTS THAT AT 1500 ON 12 AUGUST GUERRILLA UNITS ATTACKED AN ENEMY POSITION IN THE NORTHERN PART OF MORAZAN DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "THE CLASH LASTED 20 MINUTES AND WE INFLICTED TWO CASUALTIES ON THE ENEMY.""}, {"text": "THE RADIO REPORTS FROM AN ANASTACIO AQUINO FRONT WAR BULLETIN, WHICH STATES THAT FMLN GUERRILLA UNITS AMBUSHED THE 1ST COMPANY OF MILITARY DETACHMENT NO 2 JR BATTALION AT LA PENA CANTON, VILLA VICTORIA JURISDICTION, CABANAS DEPARTMENT, AT 0745 ON 14 AUGUST, "KILLING SIX ENEMIES AND WOUNDING FOUR OTHERS.""}, {"text": "THE RADIO ANNOUNCER THEN GIVES A REPORT COMING FROM THE MODESTO RAMIREZ FRONT IN CHALATENANGO DEPARTMENT, WHICH STATES THAT GUERRILLA UNITS CLASHED WITH BRACAMONTE BATTALION TROOPS AT NUEVA TRINIDAD JURISDICTION AT 0900 ON 14 AUGUST, INFLICTING TWO CASUALTIES ON THE "DEMORALIZED BRACAMONTE BATTALION TROOPS.""}, {"text": "ANOTHER REPORT SAYS THAT A GROUP OF FMLN GUERRILLAS OCCUPIED THE TOWN OF DULCE NOMBRE DE MARIA, CHALATENANGO DEPARTMENT, DURING 5 HOURS AT 1500 ON 11 AUGUST."}, {"text": "THE RADIO STATION GOES ON TO AIR A REPORT STATING THAT GUERRILLA UNITS ATTACKED A MILITARY POST WITH MORTAR FIRE, GRENADES, AND M-16 RIFLE FIRE, "KILLING ONE ENEMY AND WOUNDING ANOTHER AT 1215 ON 13 AUGUST.""}, {"text": "THE ATTACK WAS CARRIED OUT "ONLY 100 METERS AWAY FROM A CHECKPOINT LOCATED AT THE ENTRANCE TO THE TOWN OF LA PALMA.""}, {"text": "THE NEXT REPORT COMING FROM CHALATENANGO DEPARTMENT SAYS THAT FMLN MILITIAS SABOTAGED POWER LINES ALONG THE ROAD LINKING NUEVA CONCEPCION TO THE NORTHERN TRUNK HIGHWAY AT 1800 ON 12 AUGUST."}, {"text": "THE ANNOUNCER THEN SAYS THAT GUERRILLA UNITS ATTACKED 3D INFANTRY BRIGADE TROOPS AT LOS AVELINES CANTON, GUATAJIAGUA JURISDICTION, MORAZAN DEPARTMENT, AT 1600 ON 11 AUGUST, INFLICTING FOUR CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "THE REPORT STATES: "THE ATTACK WAS CARRIED OUT WITH HAND GRENADES AND RIFLE FIRE.""}, {"text": ""WE REPORT THAT ONE OF OUR COMRADES WAS WOUNDED IN THIS ATTACK, BUT NOT VERY SERIOUSLY.""}, {"text": "THE NEXT REPORT STATES THAT GUERRILLA UNITS INFLICTED ONE CASUALTY AMONG THE MARINES BATTALION IN JUCUARAN JURISDICTION, USULUTAN DEPARTMENT, AT 1200 ON 12 AUGUST."}, {"text": "THE LAST REPORT SAYS THAT FMLN UNITS WOUNDED ONE OROMONTIQUE BATTALION CORPORAL AT EL TABLON, JUCUARAN JURISDICTION, AT 1630 ON 13 {"sentences": [{"text": "THIS STATION HAS LEARNED THAT THREE PERSONS HAVE BEEN KILLED AT THE JOSE MARIA CORDOBA INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, IN THE TOWN OF RIO NEGRO, ANTIOQUIA DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "ONE OF THE PERSONS KILLED WAS WEARING A MILITARY UNIFORM, BUT WE STILL DO NOT KNOW IF HE WAS IN DISGUISE OR IF HE BELONGED TO THE SECURITY CORPS."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO PRELIMINARY REPORTS FROM THE ANTIOQUIA POLICE, THIS WAS AN ATTACK ON THE INSTALLATIONS OF THE JOSE MARIA CORDOBA AIRPORT."}, {"text": "I REPEAT: THIS IS A PRELIMINARY REPORT BY THE ANTIOQUIA POLICE."}, {"text": "RIGHT NOW, TOP OFFICIALS AND ANTIOQUIA POLICE CHIEFS ARE ON THEIR WAY TO THE AIRPORT."}, {"text": "THE AIRPORT HAS BEEN SEALED OFF, AND PEOPLE ARE TRAPPED INSIDE OFFICES THERE."}, {"text": "NO ONE IS ALLOWED NEAR THE SCENE OF THE VIOLENT SHOOTING THAT TOOK PLACE THERE JUST A FEW MINUTES AGO."}, {"text": "A SEARCH IS UNDER WAY THROUGHOUT RIO NEGRO'S SAN NICOLAS VALLEY, WHERE THE AIRPORT IS LOCATED, FOR THE PERPETRATORS OF THIS ATTACK, WHO ARE NOW BELIEVED TO BE DRIVING TWO YELLOW RENAULTS AND ARE BEING PURSUED BY THE POLICE."}, {"text": "I REPEAT: SO FAR, WE KNOW THAT THREE PERSONS HAVE BEEN KILLED INSIDE THE AIRPORT."}, {"text": "ONE OF THOSE KILLED WAS WEARING A MILITARY UNIFORM."}, {"text": "THE ANTIOQUIA POLICE HAVE REPORTED THAT THIS WAS AN ATTACK ON THE AIRPORT INSTALLATIONS."}, {"text": {"sentences": [{"text": "TWO PERSONS WERE INJURED IN DYNAMITE ATTACKS PERPETRATED THIS EVENING AGAINST TWO BANK BRANCHES IN THIS NORTHWESTERN COLOMBIAN CITY."}, {"text": "THE FIRST POLICE REPORTS INDICATE THAT A BOMB EXPLODED IN FRONT OF THE STATE-OWNED AGRARIAN BOARD IN THE SUBURBS OF MANRIQUE, AND ANOTHER AT THE AGRARIAN BOARD BRANCH IN THE SECTOR OF ARANJUEZ."}, {"text": "ONE PERSON WAS SERIOUSLY WOUNDED IN EACH OF THE TERRORIST ATTACKS, BUT NO DEATHS WERE REPORTED."}, {"text": "THE DEVICE WHICH EXPLODED IN MANRIQUE DESTROYED THE BANK BUILDING AND A BUS THAT WAS PARKED IN FRONT OF THE BUILDING, AND CAUSED CONSIDERABLE DAMAGE IN SEVERAL STORES NEARBY."}, {"text": "THE EXPLOSION IN THE OTHER BRANCH WAS OF A LESSER MAGNITUDE, AND IT BROKE WINDOWS AND CAUSED DAMAGE INSIDE THE OFFICES."}, {"text": "THE SCANT POLICE INFORMATION SAID THAT THE DEVICES WERE APPARENTLY LEFT IN FRONT OF THE TWO BANK BRANCHES MINUTES BEFORE THE CURFEW BEGAN FOR THE 6TH CONSECUTIVE DAY--PRECISELY TO COUNTER THE WAVE OF TERRORISM CAUSED BY DRUG TRAFFICKERS."}, {"text": "THESE REPRESENT THE SECOND AND THIRD DYNAMITE ATTACKS IN MEDELLIN THIS EVENING."}, {"text": "THE PREVIOUS ONE TOOK PLACE 2 HOURS EARLIER AND BLEW UP A POLICE POST, BUT FAILED TO INJURE ITS FIVE OCCUPANTS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0037", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", {"sentences": [{"text": "DAS (ADMINISTRATIVE DEPARTMENT OF SECURITY) DIRECTOR MIGUEL MAZA MARQUEZ CONFIRMED TODAY THAT THE GOVERNMENT AND THE JUDICIAL AUTHORITIES HAD KNOWN FOR OVER 1 YEAR THAT THERE WERE MERCENARIES IN OUR COUNTRY, BUT POLICE AUTHORITIES APPARENTLY PREVENTED AN INVESTIGATION THAT HAD BEEN ORDERED, AS A MATTER OF FACT, BY A FEMALE JUDGE."}, {"text": "OUR REPORTER HERNANDO CORRALES HAS THE DETAILS: (BEGIN RECORDING) (CORRALES) IF THE AUTHORITIES IN CHARGE OF AN OPERATION NEAR PUERTO BOYACA ON 18 JULY LAST YEAR HAD NOT SABOTAGED IT, THE FOREIGN INSTRUCTORS AT THE SERVICE OF THE MEDELLIN CARTEL WOULD NOW BE JAIL."}, {"text": "ON THAT DATE, MARTA LUCIA GONZALEZ, SECOND JUDGE OF PUBLIC ORDER, WROTE A FILE NOTE SAYING THAT THE JUDICIAL INSPECTION WAS UNJUSTLY TORPEDOED WITH THE ARGUMENT THAT NOTHING HAD BEEN FOUND AND THAT THIS ARGUMENT WAS SENSELESS AND ILLOGICAL SINCE ABSOLUTELY NO ONE OTHER THAN THE UNDERSIGNED JUDGE COULD DECIDE IF HE OR SHE HAD ANYTHING TO INSPECT, OR IF HE OR SHE SHOULD OR SHOULD NOT CONDUCT THE JUDICIAL PROCEEDING."}, {"text": "THE DOCUMENT, WHICH IS CONTAINED IN THE DOSSIER ON THE MASSACRE IN LA HONDURA AND LA NEGRA, URABA REGION, SAYS THAT SHE WAS LEFT 2 DAYS INSIDE A PLANE AT THE AIRPORT OF THE TEXAS PETROLEUM COMPANY IN PUERTO BOYACA AND THAT THE POLICE AUTHORITIES ACCOMPANYING HER FAILED TO EXPLAIN TO HER WHY THEY HAD NOT TAKEN ANY ACTION."}, {"text": "(UNIDENTIFIED SPEAKER) IN FACT, SHE AND SEVERAL DAS INSPECTORS ENCOUNTERED SOME OBSTACLES."}, {"text": "THE ATTORNEY GENERAL'S OFFICE WAS INFORMED OF THESE OBSTACLES IN ORDER FOR IT TO MAKE AN INVESTIGATION."}, {"text": "I THINK THAT WHEN SHE AND THE DAS PERSONNEL WERE PREPARING TO GO TO PUERTO BOYACA IT WAS ALREADY KNOWN THAT THESE PEOPLE WOULD BE PRESENT THERE FOR THESE PROCEEDINGS AND THIS WAS QUITE WORRISOME."}, {"text": "(CORRALES) AS IS KNOWN, JUDGE GONZALEZ HAD TO LEAVE COLOMBIA BECAUSE HER LIFE WAS THREATENED, AND HER FATHER, FORMER BOYACA GOVERNOR ALVARO GONZALEZ SANTANA, WAS SUBSEQUENTLY MURDERED."}, {"text": "MOREOVER, GEN MAZA MARQUEZ SAID FURTHER THAT THE FACT THAT A PAYMENT IS BEING OFFERED FOR THE CAPTURE OF PABLO ESCOBAR AND GONZALO RODRIGUEZ GACHA DOES NOT MEAN THAT OTHER PERSONS ACCUSED OF BEING CAPOS OF THE MAFIA ARE NOT BEING SOUGHT TOO."}, {"text": "(MAZA) WE ARE TAKING ACTION THE LENGTH AND BREADTH OF THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "WE ARE NOT SHOWING ANY SPECIAL CONSIDERATIONS BECAUSE WE INTEND TO ACT INDISCRIMINATELY."}, {"text": "WHAT WE WANT IS TO FIGHT A SCOURGE THAT HAS GREATLY HARMED ALL COLOMBIANS."}, {"text": "(CORRALES) THE DAS DIRECTOR SAID THAT IF ANYONE BEING HELD IN CONNECTION WITH THE INVESTIGATION OF THE KILLING OF LUIS CARLOS GALAN IS RELEASED, THAT DOES NOT MEAN THAT THE INVESTIGATIONS ARE NOT PROCEEDING WELL."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0038", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 13 SEP 89"]}], "incident_location": {"sentences": [{"text": "DAS (ADMINISTRATIVE DEPARTMENT OF SECURITY) DIRECTOR MIGUEL MAZA MARQUEZ CONFIRMED TODAY THAT THE GOVERNMENT AND THE JUDICIAL AUTHORITIES HAD KNOWN FOR OVER 1 YEAR THAT THERE WERE MERCENARIES IN OUR COUNTRY, BUT POLICE AUTHORITIES APPARENTLY PREVENTED AN INVESTIGATION THAT HAD BEEN ORDERED, AS A MATTER OF FACT, BY A FEMALE JUDGE."}, {"text": "OUR REPORTER HERNANDO CORRALES HAS THE DETAILS: (BEGIN RECORDING) (CORRALES) IF THE AUTHORITIES IN CHARGE OF AN OPERATION NEAR PUERTO BOYACA ON 18 JULY LAST YEAR HAD NOT SABOTAGED IT, THE FOREIGN INSTRUCTORS AT THE SERVICE OF THE MEDELLIN CARTEL WOULD NOW BE JAIL."}, {"text": "ON THAT DATE, MARTA LUCIA GONZALEZ, SECOND JUDGE OF PUBLIC ORDER, WROTE A FILE NOTE SAYING THAT THE JUDICIAL INSPECTION WAS UNJUSTLY TORPEDOED WITH THE ARGUMENT THAT NOTHING HAD BEEN FOUND AND THAT THIS ARGUMENT WAS SENSELESS AND ILLOGICAL SINCE ABSOLUTELY NO ONE OTHER THAN THE UNDERSIGNED JUDGE COULD DECIDE IF HE OR SHE HAD ANYTHING TO INSPECT, OR IF HE OR SHE SHOULD OR SHOULD NOT CONDUCT THE JUDICIAL PROCEEDING."}, {"text": "THE DOCUMENT, WHICH IS CONTAINED IN THE DOSSIER ON THE MASSACRE IN LA HONDURA AND LA NEGRA, URABA REGION, SAYS THAT SHE WAS LEFT 2 DAYS INSIDE A PLANE AT THE AIRPORT OF THE TEXAS PETROLEUM COMPANY IN PUERTO BOYACA AND THAT THE POLICE AUTHORITIES ACCOMPANYING HER FAILED TO EXPLAIN TO HER WHY THEY HAD NOT TAKEN ANY ACTION."}, {"text": "(UNIDENTIFIED SPEAKER) IN FACT, SHE AND SEVERAL DAS INSPECTORS ENCOUNTERED SOME OBSTACLES."}, {"text": "THE ATTORNEY GENERAL'S OFFICE WAS INFORMED OF THESE OBSTACLES IN ORDER FOR IT TO MAKE AN INVESTIGATION."}, {"text": "I THINK THAT WHEN SHE AND THE DAS PERSONNEL WERE PREPARING TO GO TO PUERTO BOYACA IT WAS ALREADY KNOWN THAT THESE PEOPLE WOULD BE PRESENT THERE FOR THESE PROCEEDINGS AND THIS WAS QUITE WORRISOME."}, {"text": "(CORRALES) AS IS KNOWN, JUDGE GONZALEZ HAD TO LEAVE COLOMBIA BECAUSE HER LIFE WAS THREATENED, AND HER FATHER, FORMER BOYACA GOVERNOR ALVARO GONZALEZ SANTANA, WAS SUBSEQUENTLY MURDERED."}, {"text": "MOREOVER, GEN MAZA MARQUEZ SAID FURTHER THAT THE FACT THAT A PAYMENT IS BEING OFFERED FOR THE CAPTURE OF PABLO ESCOBAR AND GONZALO RODRIGUEZ GACHA DOES NOT MEAN THAT OTHER PERSONS ACCUSED OF BEING CAPOS OF THE MAFIA ARE NOT BEING SOUGHT TOO."}, {"text": "(MAZA) WE ARE TAKING ACTION THE LENGTH AND BREADTH OF THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "WE ARE NOT SHOWING ANY SPECIAL CONSIDERATIONS BECAUSE WE INTEND TO ACT INDISCRIMINATELY."}, {"text": "WHAT WE WANT IS TO FIGHT A SCOURGE THAT HAS GREATLY HARMED ALL COLOMBIANS."}, {"text": "(CORRALES) THE DAS DIRECTOR SAID THAT IF ANYONE BEING HELD IN CONNECTION WITH THE INVESTIGATION OF THE KILLING OF LUIS CARLOS GALAN IS RELEASED, THAT DOES NOT MEAN THAT THE INVESTIGATIONS ARE NOT PROCEEDING WELL."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0038", "message_template": 3, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 13 SEP 89"]}], "incident_location": {"sentences": [{"text": "AUTHORITIES HAVE OFFICIALLY REPORTED THAT SEVERAL BANK OFFICES WERE ADVERSELY AFFECTED TONIGHT IN THE CHAPINERO NEIGHBORHOOD OF NORTHERN BOGOTA WHEN TWO BOMBS EXPLODED, CAUSING MINOR INJURIES TO A CHILD AND A SECURITY GUARD."}, {"text": "THE FIRST BOMB EXPLODED BY THE DOOR OF A BANCO DE OCCIDENTE BRANCH AT 2115 LOCAL TIME (0215 GMT), AND THE SHOCK WAVE DAMAGED OTHER NEARBY BANKS."}, {"text": "FOLLOWING THE EXPLOSION, A 9-YEAR-OLD BOY WHO LIVES NEAR THE BANCO DE OCCIDENTE WAS WOUNDED BY PIECES OF GLASS, SAID HIS RELATIVES, WHO TOOK HIM TO THE "MARLY" CLINIC NEAR THE AREA."}, {"text": "AT THE SAME TIME, ANOTHER BOMB EXPLODED AT A BANCO POPULAR BRANCH, TWO BLOCKS AWAY FROM WHERE THE FIRST EXPLOSION TOOK PLACE, POLICE SAID."}, {"text": "OTHER BANKS AND SHOPS WERE DAMAGED BY THE SECOND EXPLOSION, AND THE SECURITY GUARD AT THE BANCO POPULAR WAS ALSO INJURED BY PIECES OF FLYING GLASS, THE AUTHORITIES SAID."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO PRELIMINARY REPORTS, TWO MEN PLACED THE EXPLOSIVE DEVICES AND LEFT THE SCENE ON FOOT."}, {"text": "BOTH OF THESE ATTACKS TONIGHT, ATTRIBUTED TO THE DRUG TRAFFICKING CARTELS, TOOK PLACE AFTER 10 BOMBS EXPLODED EARLY THIS MORNING IN THE TEUSAQUILLO AREA IN DOWNTOWN BOGOTA."}, {"text": "THE BOMBS WERE PLACED IN NINE POLITICAL OFFICES OF THE LIBERAL AND SOCIAL CONSERVATIVE PARTIES AND IN ANOTHER BANK OFFICE."}], {"sentences": [{"text": "I HAVE BEEN IN TOUCH WITH GENERAL OCTAVIO VARGAS SILVA, NATIONAL POLICE OPERATIONAL COMMANDER AND INSPECTOR."}, {"text": "GEN VARGAS HAS SAID THAT THE TWO PEOPLE WHO WERE KILLED IN THE ATTACK THAT TOOK PLACE AT SUBA MUNICIPALITY LAST NIGHT HAVE NOT YET BEEN IDENTIFIED."}, {"text": "(VARGAS) TWO PEOPLE WERE KILLED AND FIVE OTHERS WERE WOUNDED AS A RESULT OF THE ATTACK."}, {"text": "THE TWO PEOPLE WHO WERE KILLED ARE YET TO BE IDENTIFIED."}, {"text": "THOSE WOUNDED INCLUDE THREE EMPLOYEES OF THE GAS STATION WHERE THE CAR BOMB WENT OFF AND TWO PEOPLE WHO WERE WALKING BY THE GAS STATION AT THE MOMENT OF THE EXPLOSION."}, {"text": "PRELIMINARY REPORTS HAVE ESTIMATED THAT THE EXPLOSION CAUSED 70 MILLION PESOS IN LOSSES."}, {"text": "(CARRILLO) GENERAL, APPROXIMATELY HOW MANY KILOGRAMS OF EXPLOSIVES WERE IN THE CAR BOMB?"}, {"text": "(VARGAS) APPARENTLY IT CONTAINED 60 KG OF DYNAMITE."}, {"text": "THE DYNAMITE WAS PLACED INSIDE AN OLD STATION WAGON."}, {"text": "SOMETHING MUST HAVE HAPPENED TO THE PEOPLE WHO WERE INSIDE THE VEHICLE AT THE TIME OF THE EXPLOSION -- THE TWO PEOPLE WHO WERE KILLED."}, {"text": "APPARENTLY THE CAR BOMB WENT OFF BY ACCIDENT."}, {"text": "IT WAS NOT SUPPOSED TO HAVE GONE OFF AT THAT GAS STATION."}, {"text": "(CARRILLO) HAVE THE PEOPLE WHO WERE KILLED BEEN IDENTIFIED?"}, {"text": "(VARGAS)"}, {"text": "NO, NOT YET."}, {"text": "WE ARE TRYING TO IDENTIFY THEM NOW."}, {"text": "(CARRILLO) ARE THERE SPECIAL SECURITY MEASURES TO COUNTER THIS WAVE OF TERRORISM?"}, {"text": "(VARGAS)"}, {"text": "YES, OF COURSE."}, {"text": "WE ARE CARRYING OUT A SERIES OF JOINT ACTIONS WITH THE BOGOTA POLICE DEPARTMENT AND ADMINISTRATIVE DEPARTMENT OF SECURITY PERSONNEL TO NEUTRALIZE TERRORIST ACTIONS."}, {"text": "WE ARE CARRYING OUT THOSE ACTIONS IN AREAS WE CONSIDER CRITICAL OR VULNERABLE AND IN OTHER AREAS WHERE WE ARE COUNTERACTING AND NEUTRALIZING TERRORIST ACTIONS, AS I TOLD YOU."}, {"text": "(CARRILLO) ARE THERE SECRET AGENTS THROUGHOUT THE ENTIRE CITY?"}, {"text": "(VARGAS)"}, {"text": "YES, WE HAVE UNIFORMED AND CIVILIAN PERSONNEL GUARDING THE CITY RIGHT NOW."}, {"text": "WE ALSO HAVE THE SUPPORT OF THE BOGOTA POLICE DEPARTMENT, OF DIJIN (DIRECTORATE OF JUDICIAL POLICE AND INVESTIGATIONS), AND OF CIJIN (EXPANSION UNKNOWN)."}, {"text": "THEY ARE COOPERATING WITH US."}, {"text": "THEY ARE GUARDING AREAS WE CONSIDER CRITICAL OR PLACES THAT COULD BE TARGETS OF TERRORIST ATTACKS."}, {"text": "(CARRILLO) WHAT OTHER MEASURES HAVE YOU ADOPTED ALONG WITH THE 13TH INFANTRY BRIGADE AND THE BOGOTA MAYOR?"}, {"text": "(VARGAS) WE HAVE IMPLEMENTED A NUMBER OF MEASURES, SUCH AS INCREASING PERSONNEL ON THE STREETS AND HUMAN AND MATERIAL RESOURCES."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION, WE HAVE ESTABLISHED CHEKCKPOINTS IN AREAS WE CONSIDER CRITICAL AND ARE CARRYING OUT A NUMBER OF OPERATIONAL ACTIVITIES THAT WILL HELP US LOCATE THESE CRIMINALS."}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "SUCH AN UNCONDITIONAL CEASE-FIRE DOES NOT CORRESPOND TO THE SPIRIT OF THE ESQUIPULAS AND TELA AGREEMENTS AND THE ACCORDS THE GOVERNMENT AND THE FMLN SIGNED IN MEXICO IN WHICH THE SIDES CLEARLY AGREED TO FIND SOLUTIONS IN THE AREA AND IN EL SALVADOR."}, {"text": "ASKING FOR AN END TO THE WAR AND NEGOTIATIONS IS LIKE DEMANDING THAT THE SITUATION BE CHANGED WITHOUT HAVING WON THE WAR."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION TO BEING UNREALISTIC, THIS IS A FORMULA FOR NOT NEGOTIATING AND CONTINUING THE WAR."}, {"text": "IN THE ESQUIPULAS II DOCUMENTS, THE GOVERNMENTS URGE THE SIDES TO AGREE TO A CEASE-FIRE."}, {"text": "THE TELA ACCORDS ALSO APPEAL TO THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT TO REACH AN AGREEMENT WITH THE FMLN IN THE SPIRIT OF THE ESQUIPULAS II ACCORDS."}, {"text": "THIS PARTICULAR AGREEMENT LINKS THE CESSATION OF HOSTILITIES TO DEMOCRATIZATION, SOCIAL JUSTICE, AND SELF-DETERMINATION AS A HARMONIOUS, INDIVISIBLE WHOLE."}, {"text": "THIS CONCEPT IS SUPPORTED BY THE UN SECURITY COUNCIL IN ITS RESOLUTION 637 OF 27 JULY 1989."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION, THE FIRST PARAGRAPH OF THE MEXICAN ACCORD READS AS FOLLOWS: THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT AND THE FMLN WILL TALK IN AN EFFORT TO REACH AN UNDERSTANDING THROUGH NEGOTIATIONS TO CONCLUDE THE ARMED CONFLICT THROUGH POLITICAL MEANS AS SOON AS PRACTICABLE."}, {"text": "THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT AND THE FMLN WILL FOSTER THE COUNTRY'S DEMOCRATIZATION AND REUNITE SALVADORAN SOCIETY."}, {"text": "THE DIALOGUE IS MEANT TO SERVE AS AN INSTRUMENT FOR REACHING AN AGREEMENT ON CESSATION OF HOSTILITIES."}, {"text": "THE AGREEMENT THAT THE GOVERNMENT SIGNED IN MEXICO SAYS NOTHING OF TALKING ABOUT OR NEGOTIATING THE FMLN'S DEMOBILIZATION BUT MENTIONS NEGOTIATIONS TO ENCOURAGE DEMOCRATIZATION TO AGREE ON THE CESSATION OF HOSTILITIES."}, {"text": "BY INCREASING THE NUMBER OF HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATIONS, CRISTIANI IS CLOSING THE DOOR TO DEMOCRATIZATION."}, {"text": "THIS, PLUS HIS REFUSAL TO REACH AN AGREEMENT WITH THE FMLN, MAKES HIM GUILTY OF NONCOMPLIANCE WITH THE COMMITMENTS THAT THE GOVERNMENT MADE AT ESQUIPULAS."}, {"text": "3. IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE COMMITMENT WE MADE IN MEXICO AND WITH THE REGIONAL ACCORDS, WE REITERATE OUR FULL WILLINGNESS TO AGREE WITH THE GOVERNMENT ON A CEASE-FIRE AS SOON AS PRACTICABLE AND TO ATTEND THE UPCOMING NEGOTIATION MEETING IN COSTA RICA."}, {"text": "FOR THIS MEETING, WE HAVE INCLUDED IN OUR PEACE PROPOSAL AN AGREEMENT ON A CEASE-FIRE BASED ON THE FOLLOWING POINTS: REFORMS TO THE JUDICIAL SYSTEM; CESSATION OF REPRESSION; TRIAL OF BOTH THOSE GUILTY OF THE MURDER OF MONSIGNOR ARNULFO ROMERO AND THOSE FOUND TO BE MEMBERS OF THE DEATH SQUADS; ENFORCEMENT OF THE 1980 ECONOMIC AND SOCIAL REFORMS; AND SUSPENSION OF THE ECONOMIC MEASURES THAT EXACERBATE THE CRISIS AND THE WAR; PURGE OF THE ARMY; CONSTITUTIONAL AMENDMENTS; HOLDING THE 1991 ELECTIONS AHEAD OF SCHEDULE; MINIMUM OPERATIONAL GUARANTEES TO ESTABLISH GEOGRAPHICAL AREAS FOR THE FORCES TO MAINTAIN AN EFFECTIVE CEASE-FIRE."}, {"text": "AFTER STRONG OPPOSITION TO THE PRESENCE OF THE UN AND OAS SECRETARY GENERALS' REPRESENTATIVES, WHO WILL SERVE AS WITNESSES AT THE DIALOGUE TABLE, CRISTIANI AGREED TO INVITE THEM TO THE COSTA RICA MEETING."}, {"text": "WE HOPE HE KEEPS HIS WORD BECAUSE THIS WILL LEND SERIOUSNESS TO THE PROCESS AND GUARANTEE THE NEGOTIATIONS INITIATED IN MEXICO."}, {"text": "SIGNED THE FMLN GENERAL COMMAND"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0043", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": {"sentences": [{"text": ""THE EXTRADITABLES," THE ARMED BRANCH OF THE MEDELLIN CARTEL HAVE CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE MURDER OF TWO EMPLOYEES OF BOGOTA'S DAILY EL ESPECTADOR PERPETRATED TODAY IN MEDELLIN, A SOURCE FROM THAT NEWSPAPER TOLD EFE."}, {"text": "MIGUEL SOLER RODRIGUEZ, EL ESPECTATOR'S CIRCULATION MANAGER AND MARTHA LUZ LOPEZ, THE CORRESPONDENT'S OFFICE ADMINISTRATOR, WERE KILLED TODAY IN SEPARATE ATTACKS CARRIED OUT BY GUNMEN IN MEDELLIN, COLOMBIA'S SECOND LARGEST CITY AND CAPITAL OF THE ANTIOQUIA DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "SHORTLY AFTER THE MURDERS, AN ANONYMOUS CALL WAS RECEIVED AT EL ESPECTADOR'S OFFICE IN MEDELLIN, THREATENING TO KILL ALL THE EDITORS AND OFFICE PERSONNEL WHO DO NOT RESIGN IN 3 DAYS."}, {"text": ""THE EXTRADITABLES," THE VOICE SAID, "DO NOT WANT THAT NEWSPAPER CIRCULATING IN ANTIOQUIA ANYMORE.""}, {"text": "MARTHA LUZ LOPEZ, 35, WHO WORKED FOR EL ESPECTADOR 11 YEARS, WAS KILLED BY TWO MEN ON MOTORCYCLES WHO INTERCEPTED HER CAR AT A CORNER AND SHOT HER SEVERAL TIMES."}, {"text": "AT THE MOMENT OF THE ATTACK, SHE WAS ACCOMPANIED BY HER MOTHER MARTHA LOPEZ OROZCO DE LOPEZ, WHO WAS WOUNDED."}, {"text": "SOLER, WHO WAS 45-YEARS OLD AND HAD WORKED FOR 25 YEARS AT EL ESPECTATOR, WAS ALSO KILLED BY UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS WHILE HE WAS ON HIS WAY BACK TO HIS RESIDENCE."}, {"text": "SOLER, WHO WAS IN CHARGE OF ADVERTISING AND CIRCULATION OF EL ESPECTADOR IN MEDELLIN AND THE NORTHWESTERN AREA OF COLOMBIA, WAS MARRIED AND THE FATHER OF THREE CHILDREN."}, {"text": "THE MAIN OFFICES IN BOGOTA OF EL ESPECTADOR, THE NEWSPAPER MOST THREATENED BY COLOMBIA'S DRUG TRAFFICKING MAFIA, WERE PARTIALLY DESTROYED ON 2 SEPTEMBER WHEN A CAR BOMB EXPLOSION INJURED OVER 90 PEOPLE."}, {"text": "NEWSPAPER DIRECTOR GUILLERMO CANO WAS MURDERED AS HE WAS LEAVING HIS OFFICE ON 17 DECEMBER 1986."}, {"text": "THIS CRIME WAS ATTRIBUTED TO THE MEDELLIN CARTEL, WHICH TOGETHER WITH THE CALI CARTEL, IS CONSIDERED TO BE AMONG THE MOST IMPORTANT ORGANIZATIONS IN THE WORLD INVOLVED IN THE TRAFFICKING AND DISTRIBUTION OF COCAINE."}, {"text": "NEWSPAPER ATTORNEY AND JOURNALIST HECTOR GIRALDO GALVEZ, WHO WAS THE CIVIL PROSECUTOR IN THE INVESTIGATION INTO GUILLERMO CANO'S HOMICIDE, WAS ALSO MURDERED IN BOGOTA ON 29 MARCH."}, {"text": "EL ESPECTADOR HAS CHARACTERIZED ITSELF BY REJECTING AND CONDEMNING DRUG TRAFFICKING AND OTHER CRIMINAL ACTIVITIES INVOLVING MAFIOSOS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0046", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["10 OCT 89"]}], "incident_location": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": ""THE EXTRADITABLES," THE ARMED BRANCH OF THE MEDELLIN CARTEL HAVE CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE MURDER OF TWO EMPLOYEES OF BOGOTA'S DAILY EL ESPECTADOR PERPETRATED TODAY IN MEDELLIN, A SOURCE FROM THAT NEWSPAPER TOLD EFE."}, {"text": "MIGUEL SOLER RODRIGUEZ, EL ESPECTATOR'S CIRCULATION MANAGER AND MARTHA LUZ LOPEZ, THE CORRESPONDENT'S OFFICE ADMINISTRATOR, WERE KILLED TODAY IN SEPARATE ATTACKS CARRIED OUT BY GUNMEN IN MEDELLIN, COLOMBIA'S SECOND LARGEST CITY AND CAPITAL OF THE ANTIOQUIA DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "SHORTLY AFTER THE MURDERS, AN ANONYMOUS CALL WAS RECEIVED AT EL ESPECTADOR'S OFFICE IN MEDELLIN, THREATENING TO KILL ALL THE EDITORS AND OFFICE PERSONNEL WHO DO NOT RESIGN IN 3 DAYS."}, {"text": ""THE EXTRADITABLES," THE VOICE SAID, "DO NOT WANT THAT NEWSPAPER CIRCULATING IN ANTIOQUIA ANYMORE.""}, {"text": "MARTHA LUZ LOPEZ, 35, WHO WORKED FOR EL ESPECTADOR 11 YEARS, WAS KILLED BY TWO MEN ON MOTORCYCLES WHO INTERCEPTED HER CAR AT A CORNER AND SHOT HER SEVERAL TIMES."}, {"text": "AT THE MOMENT OF THE ATTACK, SHE WAS ACCOMPANIED BY HER MOTHER MARTHA LOPEZ OROZCO DE LOPEZ, WHO WAS WOUNDED."}, {"text": "SOLER, WHO WAS 45-YEARS OLD AND HAD WORKED FOR 25 YEARS AT EL ESPECTATOR, WAS ALSO KILLED BY UNIDENTIFIED INDIVIDUALS WHILE HE WAS ON HIS WAY BACK TO HIS RESIDENCE."}, {"text": "SOLER, WHO WAS IN CHARGE OF ADVERTISING AND CIRCULATION OF EL ESPECTADOR IN MEDELLIN AND THE NORTHWESTERN AREA OF COLOMBIA, WAS MARRIED AND THE FATHER OF THREE CHILDREN."}, {"text": "THE MAIN OFFICES IN BOGOTA OF EL ESPECTADOR, THE NEWSPAPER MOST THREATENED BY COLOMBIA'S DRUG TRAFFICKING MAFIA, WERE PARTIALLY DESTROYED ON 2 SEPTEMBER WHEN A CAR BOMB EXPLOSION INJURED OVER 90 PEOPLE."}, {"text": "NEWSPAPER DIRECTOR GUILLERMO CANO WAS MURDERED AS HE WAS LEAVING HIS OFFICE ON 17 DECEMBER 1986."}, {"text": "THIS CRIME WAS ATTRIBUTED TO THE MEDELLIN CARTEL, WHICH TOGETHER WITH THE CALI CARTEL, IS CONSIDERED TO BE AMONG THE MOST IMPORTANT ORGANIZATIONS IN THE WORLD INVOLVED IN THE TRAFFICKING AND DISTRIBUTION OF COCAINE."}, {"text": "NEWSPAPER ATTORNEY AND JOURNALIST HECTOR GIRALDO GALVEZ, WHO WAS THE CIVIL PROSECUTOR IN THE INVESTIGATION INTO GUILLERMO CANO'S HOMICIDE, WAS ALSO MURDERED IN BOGOTA ON 29 MARCH."}, {"text": "EL ESPECTADOR HAS CHARACTERIZED ITSELF BY REJECTING AND CONDEMNING DRUG TRAFFICKING AND OTHER CRIMINAL ACTIVITIES INVOLVING MAFIOSOS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0046", "message_template": 3, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["02 SEP 89"]}], "incident_location": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": "GUATEMALAN ARCHBISHOP PROSPERO PENADOS DEL BARRIO TODAY REPORTED THE KIDNAPPING OF A NUN, DIANA MACK ORTIZ, 20 YEARS OLD, BORN IN THE STATE OF COLORADO IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA."}, {"text": "THE ARCHBISHOP ALSO REPORTED THAT ANOTHER U.S. NUN, PATRICIA DENNY, LEFT GUATEMALA 17 DAYS AGO BECAUSE OF CONTINUOUS DEATH THREATS OVER THE TELEPHONE AND IN WRITING."}, {"text": "PENADOS SAID DIANA MACK ORTIZ WAS KIDNAPPED ON 2 NOVEMBER IN ANTIGUA GUATEMALA, 45 KM SOUTH OF GUATEMALA CITY, WHEN SHE WAS ATTENDING A SEMINAR ALONG WITH OTHER NUNS."}, {"text": "THE ARCHBISHOP EXPLAINED THE NUN HAD BEEN RECEIVING DEATH THREATS."}, {"text": "SHE HAD BEEN URGED TO LEAVE GUATEMALA, BUT SHE DECIDED TO CONTINUE WORKING IN THIS COUNTRY."}, {"text": "THE KIDNAPPED NUN, WHO HAD BEEN IN GUATEMALA FOR A YEAR, WAS TEACHING AT THE SAN MIGUEL ACATAN ELEMENTARY SCHOOL IN HUEHUETENANGO DEPARTMENT IN NORTHEAST GUATEMALA."}, {"text": "SHE BELONGS TO THE ORDER OF THE URSILINA, PENADOS REPORTED."}, {"text": "PATRICIA DENNY, 54, LEFT GUATEMALA AFTER UNIDENTIFIED MEN WARNED HER THAT IF SHE WISHED TO CONTINUE LIVING SHE HAD TO LEAVE THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "DENNY HAD ARRIVED IN GUATEMALA IN 1984, BELONGED TO THE SISTERS OF MARY KNOLL, AND WAS WORKING AT A PARISH IN MIXCO MUNICIPALITY IN SOUTHERN GUATEMALA CITY."}, {"text": "THE ARCHBISHOP SAID ALL THIS IS THE "BEGINNING OF A CAMPAIGN TO INTIMIDATE THE CATHOLIC CHURCH.""}, {"text": "HE DID NOT MENTION WHICH GROUPS ARE PERPETRATING THESE INTIMIDATION ACTIONS."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, PENADOS SAID HE IS GOING TO TALK TO GUATEMALAN PRESIDENT VINICIO CEREZO TODAY TO REPORT THE INCIDENTS WITH THE U.S. NUNS."}, {"text": "PENADOS STATED THAT THIS KIND OF ACTION "HARMED CATHOLICISM VERY MUCH IN PAST YEARS," WHEN REPRESSION SEVERELY HIT THIS SECTOR."}, {"text": "HE POINTED OUT THAT THIS KIND OF INCIDENT HAD NOT HAPPENED SINCE PRESIDENT CEREZO TOOK OVER POWER IN GUATEMALA ON 14 JANUARY 1986."}, {"text": "THE ARCHBISHOP DEMANDED THAT MACK ORTIZ' KIDNAPPERS RESPECT HER LIFE AND PHYSICAL INTEGRITY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0048", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", {"sentences": [{"text": "ON 5 NOVEMBER, RADIO VENCEREMOS REPORTS THAT GUERRILLAS HAVE CARRIED OUT 2 AMBUSHES ALONG THE PANAMERICAN HIGHWAY, INFLICTING 26 ARMY CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "THE REPORT INDICATED THAT AT 0600 ON 4 NOVEMBER, THE REBELS PLACED A BOMB ON A LIGHT TANK NEAR FLORES DE TEPEYAC, APASTEPEQUE."}, {"text": "IT IS ESTIMATED THAT THE ACTION RESULTED IN 9 CASUALTIES; THE LIGHT TANK WAS COMPLETELY DESTROYED."}, {"text": "THE SECOND AMBUSH OCCURRED AT 0815 ON 4 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THE REBELS AMBUSHED A 10-VEHICLE MILITARY CONVOY AND LEFT AT LEAST 17 CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "SOME TIME AFTER THE REBEL ACTION, THE ARMY DIRECTED MORTAR FIRE TO THE AREA AND THE AIR FORCE LEVELED MACHINEGUN FIRE UPON THIS POPULATED ZONE."}, {"text": "TRAFFIC ON THE PANAMERICAN HIGHWAY WAS PARALYZED WHILE THE ARMED FORCES EVACUATED THE MANY CASUALTIES FROM THE AREA IN HELICOPTERS."}, {"text": "A LATER REPORT TOLD OF URBAN COMMANDOS ATTACKING A TREASURY POLICE UNIT AT 5TH AVENUE AND 5TH PONIENTE STREET IN SAN SALVADOR, RESULTING IN 2 CASUALTIES TO THE TREASURY POLICE."}, {"text": "ALSO, REBEL UNITS WERE SAID TO ATTACK MILITARY DETACHMENT NO 1 COMMANDOS ON THE OUTSKIRTS OF TOTONIQUE, CHALATENANGO DEPARTMENT DURING THE AFTERNOON OF 3 NOVEMBER, INFLICTING TWO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "IN ANOTHER ITEM, THE CENTRAL ANASTACIO AQUINO FRONT WAS REPORTED TO CLAIM TAKING PART IN ACTIONS AGAINST THE BELLOSO BATTALION."}, {"text": "FMLN REBELS CLASHED WITH SOLDIERS IN CANTON COYOLITO IN TECOLUCA JURISDICTION, SAN VICENTE DEPARTMENT AT 0900 ON 3 NOVEMBER, AND INFLICTED THREE CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "THAT SAME DAY, THE SAME UNIT WAS ATTACKED IN FINCA SAJELIO AND THE GUERRILLAS CLAIMED TO HAVE INFLICTED 2 MORE CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "THE SAME TROOPS WERE SAID TO SUFFER 2 MORE CASUALTIES IN A MINED AREA ON 4 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "AN FMLN UNIT WAS ALSO SAID TO HAVE SEIZED THE TOWN OF LOS HERNANDEZ IN CANTON MATASANO, CABANAS DEPARTMENT ON 4 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "FOUR PYLONS WERE BLOWN UP, INTERRUPTING A 46,000-VOLT ELECTRICAL LINE."}, {"text": "RADIO VENCEREMOS ON 6 NOVEMBER CARRIES ITS WEEKLY MILITARY REPORT: "DURING THE PAST WEEK, RADIO VENCEREMOS REPORTED INFLICTING MANY CASUALTIES ON THE ARMED FORCES."}, {"text": "THE TOTAL NUMBER OF CASUALTIES INFLICTED ON THE ARMED FORCES WAS 124, INCLUDING AN ARCE BATTALION OFFICER WHO WAS HIT IN (WORD INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "FMLN FORCES AMBUSHED FIVE MILITARY CONVOYS ALONG DIFFERENT HIGHWAYS THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "DURING THE WEEK, TWO PARAMILITARY MEMBERS WERE CAPTURED."}, {"text": "THE FMLN RESPECTED THE LIVES OF THESE MEN AND RELEASED THEM IMMEDIATELY, BUT CONFISCATED THEIR 3 RIFLES AND 300 CARTRIDGES."}, {"text": "WE HIGHLIGHT THE ATTACK BY OUR URBAN COMMANDOS ON COMMAND STAFF INSTALLATIONS."}, {"text": "THIS ATTACK TOOK PLACE IN A SAN SALVADOR THAT IS TOTALLY MILITARIZED, NEVERTHELESS, WE MANAGED TO HIT THE TOP DEATH SQUADS MEMBERS' CENTRAL NERVE."}, {"text": "GUERRILLA ACTIONS IN THE METAPAN AREA INCREASED DURING THE WEEK AND OUR MEN AMBUSHED SOLDIERS ALONG THE SANTA ANA-METAPAN ROAD SEVERAL TIMES."}, {"text": "IN CHALATENANGO, OUR MEN CARRIED OUT CONTINUOUS ACTIONS AGAINST 4TH INFANTRY BRIGADE TROOPS IN EL REFUGIO AND OTHER PLACES IN SAN IGNACIO."}, {"text": "WE HAVE ALREADY AMPLY REPORTED HEAVY CLASHES AGAINST PARAMILITARY GROUPS IN SAN FRANCISCO CANTON, CABANAS DEPARTMENT, WHERE WE CAPTURED THE AFOREMENTIONED PRISONERS AND CONFISCATED THEIR WEAPONS."}, {"text": "WE CARRIED OUT IMPORTANT AMBUSH OPERATIONS AGAINST MILITARY TROOPS TRYING TO TRANSIT THE PANAMERICAN AND COASTAL HIGHWAYS IN SAN VICENTE AND LA PAZ DEPARTMENTS."}, {"text": "WE ALSO MET THE BELLOSO BATTALION TROOPS AND CAUSED THEIR FIRST CASUALTIES.""}, {"text": "THE STATION ALSO REPORTED THAT GUERRILLAS ATTACKED A SECTION OF THE SORIANO BATTALION IN FINCA LAS MERCEDES AND INFLICTED THREE CASUALTIES ON THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE TROOPS, INCLUDING A RADIO OPERATOR."}, {"text": "AN M-16 RIFLE WAS CONFISCATED FROM THE SOLDIERS."}, {"text": "REBEL UNIT WAS SAID TO HAVE AMBUSHED A MILITARY CONVOY ALONG THE COASTAL ROAD NEAR SAN CRISTOBAL IN THE TECOLUCA JURISDICTION, SAN VICENTE DEPARTMENT AT NOON OF 5 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "OUR MEN CONFIRM HAVING INFLICTED 6 ARMY CASUALTIES."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0050", "message_template": 1, {"sentences": [{"text": "WE ARE HEARING STATEMENTS BY COMMANDER JORGE SHAFIK HANDAL, WHO IS TALKING ABOUT COL PONCE AND CRISTIANI'S RESPONSIBILITY IN THE TERRORIST ATTACK ON FENASTRAS."}, {"text": "THIS INCIDENT PROMPTED A VISIT TO OUR COUNTRY BY U.S. OFFICIAL BERNARD ARONSON."}, {"text": "LET US HEAR WHAT COMMANDER HANDAL HAS TO SAY ABOUT THE U.S. OFFICIAL'S VISIT."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (HANDAL) OF COURSE, THE UNITED STATES DOES NOT WANT TO APPEAR AS IF IT WERE WITHDRAWING SUPPORT FROM PRESIDENT CRISTIANI."}, {"text": "WE WERE JUST SAYING THAT ARONSON HAD ARRIVED AND HE LOOKED WORRIED."}, {"text": "THE NICE LOOKING GLASS HOUSE THEY HAD BUILT HAS RAPIDLY BEGUN TO FALL APART."}, {"text": "ARONSON APPARENTLY CAME TO SEE HOW HE COULD PATCH THINGS UP."}, {"text": "WE RECALL A SIMILAR HIGH-LEVEL VISIT BACK AROUND 1984, IF MY MEMORY SERVES ME RIGHT, WHEN THE CURRENT U.S. PRESIDENT ARRIVED."}, {"text": "AT THAT TIME HE WAS VICE PRESIDENT UNDER THE BUSH ADMINISTRATION, NO, THE REAGAN ADMINISTRATION, AND CAME TO SEE HOW TO IMPROVE THE SUPPOSEDLY CENTRIST GOVERNMENT AND HOW TO PUT AN END TO THE DEATH SQUADS."}, {"text": "HE TOOK A LIST BACK WITH HIM...(CHANGES THOUGHT) LET US TAKE A LOOK AT HOW THEY OPERATE."}, {"text": "WHEN THEY TAKE ANY ACTION THEY ARE VERY CLEAR AND DIRECT."}, {"text": "THEY HAD A POLITICAL INTEREST IN PUTTING ALL THIS TOGETHER, SO BUSH TOOK BACK WITH HIM A LIST OF 15 MILITARY MEMBERS SO THEY COULD BE FIRED."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0053", "message_template": 1, {"sentences": [{"text": "SALVADORAN PEOPLE: GOOD MORNING."}, {"text": "I AM SPEAKING ON BEHALF OF THE SALVADORAN ARMED FORCES THAT IS ON ITS FEET AT 0115 ON 12 NOVEMBER, CONFRONTING A TREACHEROUS ATTACK BY THE FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) TERRORISTS WHO AT 2000 ON 11 NOVEMBER--DISPLAYING THEIR WARMONGERING STRATEGY AND WITHOUT CARING ABOUT THE SUFFERING OF THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE--CARRIED OUT TREACHEROUS ACTIONS IN WHICH THE CIVILIAN POPULATION WERE THE ONLY ONES WHO HAVE SUFFERED."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY AND PUBLIC SECURITY PERSONNEL HAVE REACTED IN AN EFFICIENT MANNER IN REJECTING THE TERRORIST ENEMY."}, {"text": "WE ARE OBLIGATED TO REPORT TO THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE WHAT HAS HAPPENED."}, {"text": "THE MOST IMPORTANT ACTIONS THAT HAVE TAKEN PLACE ON THE NIGHT OF 11 NOVEMBER ARE AS FOLLOWS: AN ATTACK ON THE RESIDENCE OF THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY PRESIDENT, WHO IS UNHARMED; AND AN ATTACK ON THE CENTRAL ELECTIONS COUNCIL WHERE NO MATERIAL DAMAGE OR CASUALTIES OCCURRED."}, {"text": "LIKEWISE, THERE WAS AN ATTACK ON THE PRESIDENTIAL RESIDENCE WHICH CAUSED SLIGHT MATERIAL DAMAGE AND NO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "FORTUNATELY FOR ALL SALVADORANS, THE PRESIDENT OF THE REPUBLIC IS UNDER FULL PROTECTION AND HE WAS NEVER IN ANY DANGER."}, {"text": "LIKEWISE, WE REPORT THAT THERE WAS AN ATTACK ON HIS PRIVATE RESIDENCE."}, {"text": "WE ALSO WANT TO REPORT TO THE {"sentences": [{"text": "SALVADORAN PEOPLE: GOOD MORNING."}, {"text": "I AM SPEAKING ON BEHALF OF THE SALVADORAN ARMED FORCES THAT IS ON ITS FEET AT 0115 ON 12 NOVEMBER, CONFRONTING A TREACHEROUS ATTACK BY THE FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) TERRORISTS WHO AT 2000 ON 11 NOVEMBER--DISPLAYING THEIR WARMONGERING STRATEGY AND WITHOUT CARING ABOUT THE SUFFERING OF THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE--CARRIED OUT TREACHEROUS ACTIONS IN WHICH THE CIVILIAN POPULATION WERE THE ONLY ONES WHO HAVE SUFFERED."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY AND PUBLIC SECURITY PERSONNEL HAVE REACTED IN AN EFFICIENT MANNER IN REJECTING THE TERRORIST ENEMY."}, {"text": "WE ARE OBLIGATED TO REPORT TO THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE WHAT HAS HAPPENED."}, {"text": "THE MOST IMPORTANT ACTIONS THAT HAVE TAKEN PLACE ON THE NIGHT OF 11 NOVEMBER ARE AS FOLLOWS: AN ATTACK ON THE RESIDENCE OF THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY PRESIDENT, WHO IS UNHARMED; AND AN ATTACK ON THE CENTRAL ELECTIONS COUNCIL WHERE NO MATERIAL DAMAGE OR CASUALTIES OCCURRED."}, {"text": "LIKEWISE, THERE WAS AN ATTACK ON THE PRESIDENTIAL RESIDENCE WHICH CAUSED SLIGHT MATERIAL DAMAGE AND NO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "FORTUNATELY FOR ALL SALVADORANS, THE PRESIDENT OF THE REPUBLIC IS UNDER FULL PROTECTION AND HE WAS NEVER IN ANY DANGER."}, {"text": "LIKEWISE, WE REPORT THAT THERE WAS AN ATTACK ON HIS PRIVATE RESIDENCE."}, {"text": "WE ALSO WANT TO REPORT TO THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE THAT SOME MILITARY PERSONNEL WERE HARASSED, SUCH AS THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE, THE NATIONAL POLICE GARRISON IN THE ZACAMIL NEIGHBORHOOD, AND THE 6TH INFANTRY BRIGADE IN USULUTAN CITY WHERE ONE MINOR WAS INJURED."}, {"text": "THERE WAS ALSO HARASSMENT OF THE 3D INFANTRY BRIGADE WITH HEADQUARTERS IN SAN MIGUEL."}, {"text": "THERE WAS NO MATERIAL DAMAGE AND THERE WERE NO CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "(CONTINUED)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0054", "message_template": 2, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["11 NOV 89"]}], {"sentences": [{"text": "THE SALVADORAN GUERRILLAS ASSURED TODAY THEY HAVE "CONSOLIDATED" FOUR OF THE MOST DENSELY POPULATED NEIGHBORHOODS IN NORTHERN SAN SALVADOR WHERE SOME 300,000 PERSONS LIVE."}, {"text": "COMMANDER AMILCAR, ONE OF THE REBEL CHIEFS WHO HAS OCCUPIED THE ZACAMIL NEIGHBORHOOD, TOLD ACAN - EFE THAT HE AND HIS MEN CAME TO SAN SALVADOR "PREPARED, AND WITH SUFFICIENT AMMUNITION TO REMAIN FOR SEVERAL DAYS.""}, {"text": "IN A GENERAL ASSESEMENT OF THE GUERRILLA OFFENSIVE, THE YOUNG COMMANDER SAID THAT THE ARMY "CANNOT ENTER" THE "AREA UNDER REBEL CONTROL," BUT IT IS ATTACKING THE REBELS FROM THE NATIONAL POLICE HEADQUARTERS AND USING HELICOPTER GUNSHIPS."}, {"text": ""HOWEVER, THE PEOPLE HAVE THE TRUMP CARD (FOR THE SUCCESS OF THE OFFENSIVE)," HE ADDED."}, {"text": "AMILCAR, WHO IS 26-YEARS-AGO AND LOOKS LIKE A STUDENT, WAS WALKING DOWN THE HALLWAYS OF ONE OF THE CRAMPED FIVE-STORY APARTMENT BUILDINGS IN ZACAMIL WHILE EXPLAINING THAT THE GOAL OF THE REBEL OFFENSIVE IS "TO SEEK OPTIONS FOR BUILDING PEACE IN EL SALVADOR.""}, {"text": "HE ADDED THAT THE GUERRILLAS SEEK "TO DISRUPT THE DIALOGUE CONDITIONS, AND GO TO THE CONVERSATIONS WITH A POLITICAL AND MILITARY ADVANTAGE SO THAT THE GOVERNMENT WILL AGREE WITH US ON WHAT THE PEOPLE WANT: DEMOCRACY, A PEOPLE'S ECONOMIC POLICY, AND A PURGE IN THE ARMED FORCES, AMONG OTHER THINGS.""}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLAS AND THE GOVERNMENT OF EL SALVADOR HAVE HELD TWO MEETINGS IN RECENT MONTHS, THE FIRST ONE IN MEXICO AND THE SECOND ONE IN COSTA RICA."}, {"text": "A THIRD MEETING WAS TO BE HELD SHORTLY IN VENEZUELA, BUT THE FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) ANNOUNCED THAT IT WILL NOT ATTEND."}, {"text": "THE FMLN LAUNCHED THE MOST IMPORTANT MILITARY OFFENSIVE SINCE 1981 ON 11 NOVEMBER, ATTACKING 50 MILITARY POSITIONS, 20 OF THEM IN SAN SALVADOR."}, {"text": "IN THE FIRST 24 HOURS, THE OFFENSIVE HAS CAUSED NEARLY 300 CASUALTIES (127 DEAD AND 155 WOUNDED) ACCORDING TO THE ARMY, AND OVER 400 CASUALTIES ACCORDING TO THE GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "THE OFFENSIVE HAS BEEN NAMED "OUT WITH THE FASCISTS!"}, {"text": "FEBE ELIZABETH LIVES!""}, {"text": "IN HOMAGE TO A TRADE UNION LEADER KILLED 13 DAYS AGO ALONG WITH NINE OTHER WORKERS IN A DYNAMITE EXPLOSION IN THE CAPITAL CITY ATTRIBUTED TO THE ULTRARIGHTIST DEATH SQUADS."}, {"text": "ARMED WITH AN AUTOMATIC AK-47 RIFLE, AMILCAR SAID THAT THE FMLN "HAS CONSOLIDATED THE ZACAMIL, CUSCATANCINGO, MEJICANOS, AND PANAMA NEIGHBORHOODS, AND WE HAVE BESIEGED THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE.""}, {"text": "ALL THE PLACES HE MENTIONED ARE IN NORTHERN SAN SALVADOR, WHERE THE BLOODIEST CLASHES BETWEEN THE GUERRILLAS AND THE GOVERNMENT TROOPS HAVE TAKEN PLACE."}, {"text": "AT NIGHTFALL ON 12 NOVEMBER AND PRIOR TO THE CURFEW THAT BEGINS AT 2000 (0200 GMT), THE RESIDENTS OF ZACAMIL WERE OUTSIDE THEIR BUILDINGS CARRYING CANDLES AS THERE IS NO ELECTRICITY."}, {"text": "AMILCAR ASSURED THAT THE GUERRILLAS HAVE INFLICTED AT LEAST 18 CASUALTIES ON THE ARMED FORCES IN THAT AREA AND HAVE SEIZED ABOUT 20 RIFLES AND 1 M-60 MACHINEGUN."}, {"text": ""THIS OFFENSIVE IS A MILITARY AND POLITICAL ACHIEVEMENT."}, {"text": "AS A RESULT OF THE CLOSING OF THE COMALAPA INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, THE MAIN AIRPORT OF THE COUNTRY, WE HAVE SUCCEEDED IN LETTING THE WORLD THAT WE ARE AT WAR AND ARE AN EMERGING POWER," THE REBEL COMMANDER SAID."}, {"text": "COMALAPA AIRPORT, LOCATED 50 KM SOUTH OF SAN SALVADOR, WAS CLOSED "FOR SECURITY REASONS.""}, {"text": "ACORDING TO THE FMLN CLANDESTINE STATION, RADIO VENCEREMOS, THE GUERRILLA FIGHTERS DESTROYED THREE MILITARY HELICOPTERS ON THE GROUND AND CAUSED SOME DAMAGE ON THE AIRPORTS'S MAIN LANDING STRIP."}, {"text": "REFERRING TO THE GOVERNMENT'S DECISION TO IMPOSE A CURFEW AND A NATIONWIDE STATE OF SIEGE EFFECTIVE TONIGHT, COMMANDER AMILCAR SAID: "WE HAD ALREADY TAKEN THIS INTO CONSIDERATION WHEN WE LAUNCHED THE OFFENSIVE.""}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT "CANNOT ACT INDISCRIMINATELY AGAINST THE CIVILIAN POPULATION," AMILCAR SAID; ADDING THAT "THE CITIZENS' RIGHTS WERE SUSPENDED TO BOMB THE PLACES TAKEN OVER BY OUR FORCES.""}, {"text": "THE PEOPLE OF ZACAMIL AND OTHER NEIGHBORHOODS LOCATED NORTH OF THE CAPITAL HAVE LIVED IN TERROR SINCE SATURDAY, 11 NOVEMBER, WHEN THEY WERE TRAPPED IN THE CROSSFIRE BETWEEN THE REBELS AND THE MILITARY, SUBJECTED TO THE AIR RAIDS AND THE THREAT THAT LIVING WITH THE GUERRILLA MEMBERS REPRESENTS TO THEM."}, {"text": "AT LEAST TWO CIVILIANS HAVE DIED IN ZACAMIL AND FIVE MORE HAVE BEEN WOUNDED, INCLUDING TWO CHILDREN, AS A RESULT OF THE ARMED CLASHES."}], {"sentences": [{"text": "THE SALVADORAN GUERRILLAS ASSURED TODAY THEY HAVE "CONSOLIDATED" FOUR OF THE MOST DENSELY POPULATED NEIGHBORHOODS IN NORTHERN SAN SALVADOR WHERE SOME 300,000 PERSONS LIVE."}, {"text": "COMMANDER AMILCAR, ONE OF THE REBEL CHIEFS WHO HAS OCCUPIED THE ZACAMIL NEIGHBORHOOD, TOLD ACAN - EFE THAT HE AND HIS MEN CAME TO SAN SALVADOR "PREPARED, AND WITH SUFFICIENT AMMUNITION TO REMAIN FOR SEVERAL DAYS.""}, {"text": "IN A GENERAL ASSESEMENT OF THE GUERRILLA OFFENSIVE, THE YOUNG COMMANDER SAID THAT THE ARMY "CANNOT ENTER" THE "AREA UNDER REBEL CONTROL," BUT IT IS ATTACKING THE REBELS FROM THE NATIONAL POLICE HEADQUARTERS AND USING HELICOPTER GUNSHIPS."}, {"text": ""HOWEVER, THE PEOPLE HAVE THE TRUMP CARD (FOR THE SUCCESS OF THE OFFENSIVE)," HE ADDED."}, {"text": "AMILCAR, WHO IS 26-YEARS-AGO AND LOOKS LIKE A STUDENT, WAS WALKING DOWN THE HALLWAYS OF ONE OF THE CRAMPED FIVE-STORY APARTMENT BUILDINGS IN ZACAMIL WHILE EXPLAINING THAT THE GOAL OF THE REBEL OFFENSIVE IS "TO SEEK OPTIONS FOR BUILDING PEACE IN EL SALVADOR.""}, {"text": "HE ADDED THAT THE GUERRILLAS SEEK "TO DISRUPT THE DIALOGUE CONDITIONS, AND GO TO THE CONVERSATIONS WITH A POLITICAL AND MILITARY ADVANTAGE SO THAT THE GOVERNMENT WILL AGREE WITH US ON WHAT THE PEOPLE WANT: DEMOCRACY, A PEOPLE'S ECONOMIC POLICY, AND A PURGE IN THE ARMED FORCES, AMONG OTHER THINGS.""}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLAS AND THE GOVERNMENT OF EL SALVADOR HAVE HELD TWO MEETINGS IN RECENT MONTHS, THE FIRST ONE IN MEXICO AND THE SECOND ONE IN COSTA RICA."}, {"text": "A THIRD MEETING WAS TO BE HELD SHORTLY IN VENEZUELA, BUT THE FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) ANNOUNCED THAT IT WILL NOT ATTEND."}, {"text": "THE FMLN LAUNCHED THE MOST IMPORTANT MILITARY OFFENSIVE SINCE 1981 ON 11 NOVEMBER, ATTACKING 50 MILITARY POSITIONS, 20 OF THEM IN SAN SALVADOR."}, {"text": "IN THE FIRST 24 HOURS, THE OFFENSIVE HAS CAUSED NEARLY 300 CASUALTIES (127 DEAD AND 155 WOUNDED) ACCORDING TO THE ARMY, AND OVER 400 CASUALTIES ACCORDING TO THE GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "THE OFFENSIVE HAS BEEN NAMED "OUT WITH THE FASCISTS!"}, {"text": "FEBE ELIZABETH LIVES!""}, {"text": "IN HOMAGE TO A TRADE UNION LEADER KILLED 13 DAYS AGO ALONG WITH NINE OTHER WORKERS IN A DYNAMITE EXPLOSION IN THE CAPITAL CITY ATTRIBUTED TO THE ULTRARIGHTIST DEATH SQUADS."}, {"text": "ARMED WITH AN AUTOMATIC AK-47 RIFLE, AMILCAR SAID THAT THE FMLN "HAS CONSOLIDATED THE ZACAMIL, CUSCATANCINGO, MEJICANOS, AND PANAMA NEIGHBORHOODS, AND WE HAVE BESIEGED THE 1ST INFANTRY BRIGADE.""}, {"text": "ALL THE PLACES HE MENTIONED ARE IN NORTHERN SAN SALVADOR, WHERE THE BLOODIEST CLASHES BETWEEN THE GUERRILLAS AND THE GOVERNMENT TROOPS HAVE TAKEN PLACE."}, {"text": "AT NIGHTFALL ON 12 NOVEMBER AND PRIOR TO THE CURFEW THAT BEGINS AT 2000 (0200 GMT), THE RESIDENTS OF ZACAMIL WERE OUTSIDE THEIR BUILDINGS CARRYING CANDLES AS THERE IS NO ELECTRICITY."}, {"text": "AMILCAR ASSURED THAT THE GUERRILLAS HAVE INFLICTED AT LEAST 18 CASUALTIES ON THE ARMED FORCES IN THAT AREA AND HAVE SEIZED ABOUT 20 RIFLES AND 1 M-60 MACHINEGUN."}, {"text": ""THIS OFFENSIVE IS A MILITARY AND POLITICAL ACHIEVEMENT."}, {"text": "AS A RESULT OF THE CLOSING OF THE COMALAPA INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT, THE MAIN AIRPORT OF THE COUNTRY, WE HAVE SUCCEEDED IN LETTING THE WORLD THAT WE ARE AT WAR AND ARE AN EMERGING POWER," THE REBEL COMMANDER SAID."}, {"text": "COMALAPA AIRPORT, LOCATED 50 KM SOUTH OF SAN SALVADOR, WAS CLOSED "FOR SECURITY REASONS.""}, {"text": "ACORDING TO THE FMLN CLANDESTINE STATION, RADIO VENCEREMOS, THE GUERRILLA FIGHTERS DESTROYED THREE MILITARY HELICOPTERS ON THE GROUND AND CAUSED SOME DAMAGE ON THE AIRPORTS'S MAIN LANDING STRIP."}, {"text": "REFERRING TO THE GOVERNMENT'S DECISION TO IMPOSE A CURFEW AND A NATIONWIDE STATE OF SIEGE EFFECTIVE TONIGHT, COMMANDER AMILCAR SAID: "WE HAD ALREADY TAKEN THIS INTO CONSIDERATION WHEN WE LAUNCHED THE OFFENSIVE.""}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT "CANNOT ACT INDISCRIMINATELY AGAINST THE CIVILIAN POPULATION," AMILCAR SAID; ADDING THAT "THE CITIZENS' RIGHTS WERE SUSPENDED TO BOMB THE PLACES TAKEN OVER BY OUR FORCES.""}, {"text": "THE PEOPLE OF ZACAMIL AND OTHER NEIGHBORHOODS LOCATED NORTH OF THE CAPITAL HAVE LIVED IN TERROR SINCE SATURDAY, 11 NOVEMBER, WHEN THEY WERE TRAPPED IN THE CROSSFIRE BETWEEN THE REBELS AND THE MILITARY, SUBJECTED TO THE AIR RAIDS AND THE THREAT THAT LIVING WITH THE GUERRILLA MEMBERS REPRESENTS TO THEM."}, {"text": "AT LEAST TWO CIVILIANS HAVE DIED IN ZACAMIL AND FIVE MORE HAVE BEEN WOUNDED, INCLUDING TWO CHILDREN, AS A RESULT OF THE ARMED CLASHES."}], {"sentences": [{"text": "WE HAVE A LAST MINUTE REPORT FROM SAN MIGUEL."}, {"text": "AT EXACTLY 1100 1700 GMT YESTERDAY, 12 NOVEMBER, AN ARMORED PERSONNEL CARRIER WAS DESTROYED WITH AN RPG-7 ROCKET (WORDS INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "FOUR ENEMY CASUALTIES WERE REPORTED."}, {"text": "WE REPEAT: AN ARMORED PERSONNEL CARRIER WAS DESTROYED BY OUR FIGHTERS IN SAN MIGUEL."}, {"text": "OUR FIGHTERS USED AN RPG-7 ROCKET LAUNCHER TO DESTROY THE ARMORED PERSONNEL CARRIER."}, {"text": "NOW WE HAVE MORE INFORMATION FROM SAN SALVADOR."}, {"text": "AT 0800 1400 GMT THIS MORNING, A C-47 PLANE FLEW OVER AND STRAFED THE MEJICANOS DOWNTOWN AREA, WHERE THOUSANDS OF PEOPLE LIVE."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE REPORT WE RECEIVED, MANY CIVILIANS HAVE BEEN INJURED."}, {"text": "WE WERE ALSO ADVISED THAT THE C-47 LEFT THE AREA AFTER ITS ATTACK."}, {"text": "WE ONCE AGAIN CALL ON THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY TO PRESSURE ALFREDO CRISTIANI'S GOVERNMENT TO STOP THIS KIND OF HUMAN RIGHTS VIOLATION."}, {"text": "THESE ACTIONS ARE DIRECTED AGAINST THE CIVILIAN POPULATION."}, {"text": "THE ARMED FORCES HAS BEEN SHELLING AND STRAFING DENSELY POPULATED AREAS IN SAN SALVADOR SINCE SATURDAY."}, {"text": "IN THE PAST WE HAVE DENOUNCED INDISCRIMINATE SHELLING OF RURAL AREAS; HOWEVER, THESE ARE UNPRECEDENTED ATTACKS."}, {"text": "THIS SHELLING AND BOMBING HAS ALREADY RESULTED IN MANY CIVILIAN CASUALTIES."}],
