{"sentences": [{"text": "A HIGH-RANKING UNITED NATIONS OFFICIAL IN SAN SALVADOR TODAY VOICED DISAPPROVAL REGARDING THE SUPPORT EXPRESSED BY NICARAGUAN PRESIDENT DANIEL ORTEGA FOR THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN)."}, {"text": ""NICARAGUA'S SUPPORT FOR THE FMLN IS AN INSULT TO THE CENTRAL AMERICAN PEACE PROCESS," SAID THE UNITED NATIONS OFFICIAL WHO WISHED TO REMAIN ANONYMOUS."}, {"text": "HE IS PARTICIPATING IN THE UNITED NATIONS PEACE EFFORTS IN THE AREA."}, {"text": "THE OFFENSIVE LAUNCHED BY THE FMLN ON 11 NOVEMBER, THE MOST IMPORTANT ONE SINCE 1981, HAS ALREADY RESULTED IN 139 DEAD AND 313 WOUNDED, INCLUDING SOLDIERS, REBELS, AND CIVILIANS, GOVERNMENT SOURCES REPORTED TODAY."}, {"text": "ORTEGA, ON 11 NOVEMBER, DESCRIBED THE ARMY'S ACTIONS AS A "GENOCIDE" AND A "MASSACRE," REFERRING TO THE BOMBINGS OF NEIGHBORHOODS OCCUPIED BY THE GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE OFFICIAL, THE OPEN SUPPORT VOICED BY ORTEGA TO THE SALVADORAN REBELS "IS A MISTAKE AND AN INTERVENTION.""}, {"text": "THE UN OFFICIAL EMPHASIZED THAT "THIS GIVES THE SALVADORAN CONFLICT AN INTERNATIONAL DIMENSION AND THE UNITED STATES HAS SAID THAT IS HAS NOT RULED OUT AN INTERVENTION IN THE AREA DUE TO THE NICARAGUAN SUPPORT TO THE MARXIST GUERRILLA OF EL SALVADOR.""}, {"text": "THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT OF RIGHTIST ALFREDO CRISTIANI HAS BLAMED ORTEGA FOR VIOLATING {"sentences": [{"text": "THE HUMAN RIGHTS PROMOTION AND PROTECTION SECRETARIAT (SECRETARIA DE PROMOCION Y PROTECCION DE LOS DERECHOS HUMANOS) OF THE FMLN STRONGLY CONDEMNS THE MASSACRE OF FIVE SPANISH-BORN JESUIT PRIESTS AND THREE SALVADORAN CITIZENS CARRIED OUT BY THE SALVADORAN ARMED FORCES SOLDIERS."}, {"text": "IGNORING A MARTIAL LAW PROHIBITING ALL TRAVEL, EARLY THIS MORNING A LARGE NUMBER OF HEAVILY ARMED SOLDIERS BURST INTO THE RESIDENCE OF THE PRIESTS WHO MANAGE THE JOSE SIMEON CANAS CATHOLIC UNIVERSITY (UCA)."}, {"text": "THE SOLDIERS BROKE INTO THE PRIESTS' BEDROOMS, CAPTURED THEM, AND BRUTALLY MURDERED THEM IN THE GARDEN."}, {"text": "THE VICTIMS OF THIS HATEFUL COLLECTIVE CRIME WERE: PRIEST AND DR IGNACIO ELLACURIA, THE UCA DIRECTOR; PRIEST AND DR IGNACIO MARTIN BARO, UCA DEPUTY DIRECTOR; PRIEST AND DR SEGUNDO MONTES, UCA HUMAN RIGHTS INSTITUTE DIRECTOR; PRIEST AND DR AMANDO LOPEZ, UCA DEAN; PRIEST JUAN RAMON MORENO; AND JOAQUIN LOPEZ Y LOPEZ, AS WELL AS JULIA RAMOS AND HER 15-YEAR-OLD DAUGHTER, ELVA RAMOS."}, {"text": "THE PERSONS WHO ORDERED THE HORRIBLE MURDER OF THE JESUITS AND THREE SALVADORAN CITIZENS ARE THE SAME ONES WHO ORDERED PILOTS, ARTILLERY MEN, AND MACHINEGUNNERS IN PLANES TO ATTACK THE CIVILIAN POPULATION."}, {"text": "THEY ARE THE SAME ONES WHO ARE AGAINST REACHING A POLITICAL SOLUTION TO THE SALVADORAN CONFLICT."}, {"text": "THEY ARE THE TOP MILITARY AND POLITICAL FIGURES IN ALFREDO CRISTIANI'S ADMINISTRATION."}, {"text": "THE HUMAN RIGHTS PROMOTION AND PROTECTION SECRETARIAT CALLS ON THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY TO TIE THE HANDS OF THESE MURDERERS OF SALVADORAN PEOPLE AND TO AID IN FINDING A SOLUTION TO THE NATIONAL CRISIS SO WE MAY ATTAIN A JUST AND LASTING PEACE OUR PEOPLE SO DESIRE."}, {"text": "NO MORE BARBARIC ACTIONS IN SAN SALVADOR."}, {"text": "NO MORE INJUSTICES."}, {"text": "TRIAL AND PUNISHMENT FOR THE MURDERERS."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY AND POLITICAL LEADERS OF CRISTIANI'S GOVERNMENT MUST BE OUSTED."}, {"text": "EL SALVADOR, 16 NOV 1989"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0060", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["16 NOV 89"]}], {"sentences": [{"text": "FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN) DETACHMENTS HAVE CONDUCTED THE LARGEST MILITARY OPERATION IN THE ENTIRE HISTORY OF THE SALVADORAN CONFLICT IN THE COUNTRY'S CAPITAL."}, {"text": "AN OFFENSIVE WAS LAUNCHED SIMULTANEOUSLY THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY'S TERRITORY; HOWEVER, SAN SALVADOR'S CITY BLOCKS, WHICH WERE THE SCENE OF FIERCE FIGHTING BETWEEN FMLN DETACHMENTS AND GOVERNMENT TROOPS, WERE THE EPICENTER OF SUNDAY'S EVENTS."}, {"text": "THE INTENSE FIREFIGHT INVOLVING ARTILLERY AND HELICOPTERS LASTED APPROXIMATELY 18 HOURS AND ENCOMPASSED VIRTUALLY THE ENTIRE CAPITAL, COMPLETELY PARALYZING LIFE IN THE CITY."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO REUTER, ATTEMPTS WERE MADE TO STORM PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI'S OFFICIAL AND PERSONAL RESIDENCES; HOWEVER, IT IS REPORTED THAT THE PRESIDENT WAS NOT HURT."}, {"text": "REPORTS OF THE LOSSES ON BOTH SIDES ARE CONTRADICTORY."}, {"text": "A STATE OF SIEGE HAS BEEN INTRODUCED IN EL SALVADOR AND CONSTITUTIONAL GUARANTEES HAVE BEEN SUSPENDED."}, {"text": "A CURFEW IS IN FORCE IN THE CAPITAL, AND THE INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT HAS BEEN CLOSED."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO PRESIDENT CRISTIANI, WHOSE SPEECH WAS BROADCAST ON THE RADIO, THESE STEPS ARE NEEDED TO "DEFEND THE POPULATION AGAINST LEFT-WING TERRORISM.""}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE PRESIDENT, THE MILITARY ARE IN COMPLETE CONTROL OF THE SITUATION; HOWEVER, IT IS REPORTED FROM SAN SALVADOR THAT THESE WORDS BY A. CRISTIANI WERE HEARD ON THE AIRWAVES ACCOMPANIED BY CONTINUAL EXPLOSIONS AND SHOOTING."}, {"text": "INTERNATIONAL OBSERVERS REGARD EVENTS IN SAN SALVADOR IN THE CONTEXT OF THE INTERRUPTED TALKS BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT AND THE INSURGENTS."}, {"text": "THE THIRD ROUND OF THESE TALKS SHOULD HAVE BEEN HELD RECENTLY IN CARACAS, BUT OPPOSITION REPRESENTATIVES REFUSED TO TAKE PART IN THEM AFTER A LEFT-WING TRADE UNION'S HEADQUARTERS WAS SUBJECTED TO ARTILLERY BOMBARDMENT RESULTING IN THE DEATHS OF AT LEAST 10 PEOPLE."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE INSURGENTS, THE GOVERNMENT DECIDED ON DIALOGUE WITH THEM SOLELY OUT OF PROPAGANDA CONSIDERATIONS, WITH NO INTENTION OF REACHING ANY AGREEMENT."}, {"text": "SUNDAY'S OFFENSIVE WAS THUS AN ATTEMPT ON THEIR PART TO SHOW THEMSELVES TO BE A FORCE TO BE RECKONED WITH."}, {"text": "IN THE OPINION OF OBSERVERS, HOWEVER, EVENTS IN SAN SALVADOR PRACTICALLY RULE OUT ALL HOPES OF SUCCESS FOR FUTURE TALKS BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT AND REPRESENTATIVES OF THE INSURGENTS."}, {"text": "MOREOVER, THE FIGHTING IN THE SALVADORAN CAPITAL, A REUTER CORRESPONDENT BELIEVES, DEALT THE FRAGILE PEACE SETTLEMENT PROCESS IN CENTRAL AMERICA A CONSIDERABLE BLOW."}], {"sentences": [{"text": "APPROXIMATELY 1,000 PEOPLE DEMONSTRATED TODAY AT THE BURGOS MAIN SQUARE (CENTRAL) TO ASK THE SPANISH GOVERNMENT TO MEDIATE IN THE SALVADORAN CONFLICT, AND IN BARCELONA (NORTHEASTERN), A DEMONSTRATION TO EXPRESS SUPPORT FOR THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE HAS BEEN SCHEDULED FOR 22 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THE DEMONSTRATORS, CONVOKED BY THE SOLIDARITY WITH LATIN AMERICA COMMITTEE, VERBALLY ATTACKED SALVADORAN PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI AND HAVE ASKED THE SPANISH GOVERNMENT TO OFFER ITSELF AS A MEDIATOR TO PROMOTE AN END THE ARMED CONFLICT."}, {"text": "SOME OF THE PEOPLE WHO ATTENDED THE DEMONSTRATION, WHICH WAS HELD WITHOUT INCIDENTS, CARRIED PLACARTS DENOUNCING THE KILLING OF SIX JESUIT PRIESTS -- FIVE OF WHOM WERE SPANISH CITIZENS -- AND TWO SALVADORAN WOMEN AT THE CENTRAL AMERICAN UNIVERSITY."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, CIVIC ORGANIZATIONS, STUDENT ASSOCIATIONS, LABOR UNIONS, AND POLITICAL PARTIES IN CATALUNA HAVE SCHEDULED A DEMONSTRATION IN SUPPORT OF THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE TO BE HELD IN BARCELONA ON 22 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THESE ORGANIZATIONS, WHICH HAVE FORMED AN EMERGENCY COMMITTEE, HAVE OPENED AN ACCOUNT AT THE "LA CAIXA" SAVINGS BANK WHERE ECONOMIC DONATIONS ARE BEING ACCEPTED TO HELP THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE."}, {"text": "IN A MANIFESTO RELEASED, THE COMMITTEE DEMANDS AN END TO THE BOMBING OF CIVILIANS, THE IMMEDIATE EVACUATION OF THE WOUNDED, AND AN END TO ATTACKS AGAINST THE UNION HEADQUARTERS AND LEADERS."}, {"text": "LIKEWISE, THE COMMITTEE HAS DEMANDED AN END TO U.S. INTERVENTION IN EL SALVADOR AND THAT THE GUATEMALAN AND HONDURAN ARMIES REFRAIN FROM PARTICIPATING IN THE CONFLICT."}, {"text": ""WE ASK THE SPANISH GOVERNMENT INSTITUTIONS AND THE EEC TO PRESSURE THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT TO BEGIN A REAL NEGOTIATION THAT WILL AN END TO THE CONFLICT AND ITS CAUSES, THE MANIFESTO STATES."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0065", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 19 {"sentences": [{"text": "APPROXIMATELY 1,000 PEOPLE DEMONSTRATED TODAY AT THE BURGOS MAIN SQUARE (CENTRAL) TO ASK THE SPANISH GOVERNMENT TO MEDIATE IN THE SALVADORAN CONFLICT, AND IN BARCELONA (NORTHEASTERN), A DEMONSTRATION TO EXPRESS SUPPORT FOR THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE HAS BEEN SCHEDULED FOR 22 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THE DEMONSTRATORS, CONVOKED BY THE SOLIDARITY WITH LATIN AMERICA COMMITTEE, VERBALLY ATTACKED SALVADORAN PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI AND HAVE ASKED THE SPANISH GOVERNMENT TO OFFER ITSELF AS A MEDIATOR TO PROMOTE AN END THE ARMED CONFLICT."}, {"text": "SOME OF THE PEOPLE WHO ATTENDED THE DEMONSTRATION, WHICH WAS HELD WITHOUT INCIDENTS, CARRIED PLACARTS DENOUNCING THE KILLING OF SIX JESUIT PRIESTS -- FIVE OF WHOM WERE SPANISH CITIZENS -- AND TWO SALVADORAN WOMEN AT THE CENTRAL AMERICAN UNIVERSITY."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, CIVIC ORGANIZATIONS, STUDENT ASSOCIATIONS, LABOR UNIONS, AND POLITICAL PARTIES IN CATALUNA HAVE SCHEDULED A DEMONSTRATION IN SUPPORT OF THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE TO BE HELD IN BARCELONA ON 22 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THESE ORGANIZATIONS, WHICH HAVE FORMED AN EMERGENCY COMMITTEE, HAVE OPENED AN ACCOUNT AT THE "LA CAIXA" SAVINGS BANK WHERE ECONOMIC DONATIONS ARE BEING ACCEPTED TO HELP THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE."}, {"text": "IN A MANIFESTO RELEASED, THE COMMITTEE DEMANDS AN END TO THE BOMBING OF CIVILIANS, THE IMMEDIATE EVACUATION OF THE WOUNDED, AND AN END TO ATTACKS AGAINST THE UNION HEADQUARTERS AND LEADERS."}, {"text": "LIKEWISE, THE COMMITTEE HAS DEMANDED AN END TO U.S. INTERVENTION IN EL SALVADOR AND THAT THE GUATEMALAN AND HONDURAN ARMIES REFRAIN FROM PARTICIPATING IN THE CONFLICT."}, {"text": ""WE ASK THE SPANISH GOVERNMENT INSTITUTIONS AND THE EEC TO PRESSURE THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT TO BEGIN A REAL NEGOTIATION THAT WILL AN END TO THE CONFLICT AND ITS CAUSES, THE MANIFESTO STATES."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0065", "message_template": 2, "message_template_optional": true, "incident_date": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": "PRESIDENT VINICIO CEREZO HAS TACITLY BLAMED PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI'S ADMINISTRATION FOR THE CRISIS WHICH PREVAILS IN THE COUNTRY AS A RESULT OF THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT'S (FMLN) OFFENSIVE WHICH WAS LAUNCHED ON SATURDAY 11 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "CEREZO ATTENDED THE CONCLUSION OF A SEMINAR SPONSORED BY THE CENTRAL AMERICAN INSTITUTE FOR POLITICAL STUDIES (INCEP) ON 17 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THE EVENT WAS HELD AT 2100 AT THE GUATEMALA FIESTA HOTEL."}, {"text": "THE NEW CENTRAL AMERICAN VICE PRESIDENT OF THE CHRISTIAN DEMOCRATIC ORGANIZATION OF AMERICA (ODCA) WAS SWORN IN AT THE EVENT."}, {"text": "CARLOS MORALES EHRLICH, OF EL SALVADOR, WAS REPLACED BY PROFESSOR CATALINA SOBERANIS, OF GUATEMALA."}, {"text": "DURING HIS SPEECH MORALES EHRLICH BLAMED THE EXTREME RIGHT DEATH SQUADS OF EL SALVADOR FOR THE ASSASSINATION OF SIX JESUIT PRIESTS AT THE CENTRAL AMERICAN UNIVERSITY."}, {"text": "DURING HIS SPEECH, WHICH WAS MORE LIKE AN INFORMAL CHAT, PRESIDENT CEREZO ATTRIBUTED THE SITUATION WHICH PREVAILS IN EL SALVADOR TO PRESIDENT CRISTIANI'S INEFFICIENCY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0066", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 17 NOV 89", "11 NOV 89 - {"sentences": [{"text": "HEAVY CLASHES ARE TAKING PLACE RIGHT NOW IN ESCALON AND SAN BENITO RESIDENTIAL AREAS."}, {"text": "THERE IS NO GOING BACK."}, {"text": "WE HAVE BROKEN THE DEFENSIVE LINES OF THE ENEMY."}, {"text": "WE HAVE BROKEN (WORDS INDISTINCT) IN THE CAPITAL CITY, WE ARE FIGHTING IN FRONT OF THE DENS OF COLONEL PONCE AND OTHER OFFICERS WHO HAVE TURNED THE WAR INTO A BUSINESS."}, {"text": "THOSE OFFICERS HAVE LUXURIOUS MANSIONS IN MIAMI."}, {"text": "EVERY WEEKEND AND EVEN IN SPITE OF THE WAR, COL PONCE HAS ORGIES IN HIS LUXURIOUS HOMES IN THE COUNTRY'S INTERIOR."}, {"text": {"sentences": [{"text": "THE REBEL COMMANDERS WHO DIRECTED THE OCCUPATION OF SEVERAL SAN SALVADOR NEIGHBORHOODS LAST WEEK, TODAY HEADED THE SEIZURE OF THE SHERATON HOTEL, WHERE OAS SECRETARY GENERAL JOAO BAENA SOARES WAS TRAPPED FOR MORE THAN 8 HOURS."}, {"text": "NEWSMEN WHO ENTERED THE HOTEL THIS AFTERNOON DURING THE EVACUATION OF BAENA BY DIPLOMATS WERE ABLE TO CONFIRM THAT COMMANDER AMILCAR, KNOWN AS "EL CHOCO," WHO DIRECTED THE COMBAT OPERATIONS IN THE ZACAMIL NEIGHBORHOOD, WAS SEEN TODAY ON THE THIRD FLOOR OF THE SHERATON HOTEL."}, {"text": "SEVERAL REBELS HAVE SAID THAT FACUNDO GUARDADO ("COMMANDER ESTEBAN"), ONE OF THE FOUNDERS OF THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT AND ONE OF THE LEADERS OF THE OFFENSIVE THAT BEGAN IN THE CAPITAL ON 11 NOVEMBER, IS SOMEWHERE NEAR THE HOTEL."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE REBELS, GUARDADO EXPECTED TO INITIATE THIS AFTERNOON'S "NEGOTIATIONS" WITH THE MANAGER OF THE HOTEL, ROBERT NEWELL."}, {"text": "SEVERAL U.S. MILITARY ADVISERS, AS WELL AS ONE FROM GUATEMALA AND ANOTHER ONE FROM CHILE REMAIN IN THE HANDS OF THE REBELS."}, {"text": "EL CHOCO SAID: "WE CAN RESIST FOR AS LONG AS WE HAVE TO."}, {"text": "ALL THEY CAN DO IS BOMB THE PLACE AND LET US SEE IF THEY ARE WILLING TO DO THAT.""}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE YOUNG GUERRILLA COMMANDER, THE REBEL WITHDRAWAL FROM THE ZACAMIL, CUSCATANCINGO, AND MEJICANOS NEIGHBORHOODS, AMONG OTHERS, "WAS PART OF THE PLAN" THAT WAS COMPLETED TODAY WITH THE ARRIVAL AT THE SHERATON HOTEL AREA."}, {"text": "THE REBEL SAID: "WE HAVE COME HERE TODAY, TO THE ESCALON COLONY, TO THEIR AREA, THE AREA OF THE BOURGEOISIE, TO SEE IF THEY DO HERE WHAT THEY DID WITH THE PEOPLE, WHO WERE HURT BY THE AIR FORCE BOMBING OPERATIONS.""}, {"text": "AT 0430 (1030 GMT) TODAY, THE FMLN GUERRILLAS INITIATED HEAVY FIGHTING AROUND THE SHERATON HOTEL, WHERE OAS SECRETARY GENERAL JOAO BAENA SOARES WAS STAYING."}, {"text": "BAENA SOARES WAS EVACUATED FROM THE SHERATON HOTEL TO THE HEADQUARTERS OF THE ARMED FORCES STAFF WHERE HE MET WITH THE "HIGHEST SALVADORAN AUTHORITIES," ACCORDING TO DIPLOMATIC AND MILITARY SOURCES."}, {"text": "THIS AFTERNOON, THE GUERRILLAS ARE STILL OCCUPYING SEVERAL FLOORS OF THE HOTEL, WHICH HAS BULLET HOLES, DESTROYED WINDOWS, AND BROKEN FURNITURE ALL OVER THE FLOOR."}, {"text": "THE AREA HAS BEEN SURROUNDED BY LIGHT ARMORED TANKS AND IS BEING PATROLLED BY SEVERAL ARMED SALVADORAN AIR FORCE HELICOPTERS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0068", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["21 NOV {"sentences": [{"text": "THE REBEL COMMANDERS WHO DIRECTED THE OCCUPATION OF SEVERAL SAN SALVADOR NEIGHBORHOODS LAST WEEK, TODAY HEADED THE SEIZURE OF THE SHERATON HOTEL, WHERE OAS SECRETARY GENERAL JOAO BAENA SOARES WAS TRAPPED FOR MORE THAN 8 HOURS."}, {"text": "NEWSMEN WHO ENTERED THE HOTEL THIS AFTERNOON DURING THE EVACUATION OF BAENA BY DIPLOMATS WERE ABLE TO CONFIRM THAT COMMANDER AMILCAR, KNOWN AS "EL CHOCO," WHO DIRECTED THE COMBAT OPERATIONS IN THE ZACAMIL NEIGHBORHOOD, WAS SEEN TODAY ON THE THIRD FLOOR OF THE SHERATON HOTEL."}, {"text": "SEVERAL REBELS HAVE SAID THAT FACUNDO GUARDADO ("COMMANDER ESTEBAN"), ONE OF THE FOUNDERS OF THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT AND ONE OF THE LEADERS OF THE OFFENSIVE THAT BEGAN IN THE CAPITAL ON 11 NOVEMBER, IS SOMEWHERE NEAR THE HOTEL."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE REBELS, GUARDADO EXPECTED TO INITIATE THIS AFTERNOON'S "NEGOTIATIONS" WITH THE MANAGER OF THE HOTEL, ROBERT NEWELL."}, {"text": "SEVERAL U.S. MILITARY ADVISERS, AS WELL AS ONE FROM GUATEMALA AND ANOTHER ONE FROM CHILE REMAIN IN THE HANDS OF THE REBELS."}, {"text": "EL CHOCO SAID: "WE CAN RESIST FOR AS LONG AS WE HAVE TO."}, {"text": "ALL THEY CAN DO IS BOMB THE PLACE AND LET US SEE IF THEY ARE WILLING TO DO THAT.""}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE YOUNG GUERRILLA COMMANDER, THE REBEL WITHDRAWAL FROM THE ZACAMIL, CUSCATANCINGO, AND MEJICANOS NEIGHBORHOODS, AMONG OTHERS, "WAS PART OF THE PLAN" THAT WAS COMPLETED TODAY WITH THE ARRIVAL AT THE SHERATON HOTEL AREA."}, {"text": "THE REBEL SAID: "WE HAVE COME HERE TODAY, TO THE ESCALON COLONY, TO THEIR AREA, THE AREA OF THE BOURGEOISIE, TO SEE IF THEY DO HERE WHAT THEY DID WITH THE PEOPLE, WHO WERE HURT BY THE AIR FORCE BOMBING OPERATIONS.""}, {"text": "AT 0430 (1030 GMT) TODAY, THE FMLN GUERRILLAS INITIATED HEAVY FIGHTING AROUND THE SHERATON HOTEL, WHERE OAS SECRETARY GENERAL JOAO BAENA SOARES WAS STAYING."}, {"text": "BAENA SOARES WAS EVACUATED FROM THE SHERATON HOTEL TO THE HEADQUARTERS OF THE ARMED FORCES STAFF WHERE HE MET WITH THE "HIGHEST SALVADORAN AUTHORITIES," ACCORDING TO DIPLOMATIC AND MILITARY SOURCES."}, {"text": "THIS AFTERNOON, THE GUERRILLAS ARE STILL OCCUPYING SEVERAL FLOORS OF THE HOTEL, WHICH HAS BULLET HOLES, DESTROYED WINDOWS, AND BROKEN FURNITURE ALL OVER THE FLOOR."}, {"text": "THE AREA HAS BEEN SURROUNDED BY LIGHT ARMORED TANKS AND IS BEING PATROLLED BY SEVERAL ARMED SALVADORAN AIR FORCE HELICOPTERS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0068", "message_template": 2, "message_template_optional": true, "incident_date": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": "THE PICTURE PUBLISHED TODAY BY THE NEWSPAPER GRANMA IN ITS THIRD EDITION SPEAKS FOR ITSELF."}, {"text": "IN FACT, AS THE NEWSPAPER SUGGESTS, THE YANKEE HAND IS TODAY IN EL SALVADOR AS IT WAS YESTERDAY IN VIETNAM."}, {"text": "THE WOUNDED MOTHER WHO TRIES TO COMFORT HER DAUGHTER, A VICTIM OF THE BOMBINGS, IS NOT AN ISOLATED PICTURE."}, {"text": "IT IS A SYMBOL OF THE CRIMES THAT ARE BEING COMMITTED AGAINST THE CIVILIAN POPULATION IN THAT COUNTRY."}, {"text": "THE UNITED STATES IS NOT INNOCENT OF THESE CRIMES BECAUSE U.S. PILOTS ARE PARTICIPATING IN THE MASSACRE."}, {"text": "IN THE MEANTIME, WHAT IS THE HUMAN RIGHTS CHAMPION DOING?"}, {"text": "IN FACT, HE IS DOING NOTHING THAT COULD NOT BE PREDICTED."}, {"text": "PRESIDENT BUSH GETS ON THE PHONE AND CALLS HIS SALVADORAN CRONY ALFREDO CRISTINI TO ASSURE HIM THAT EVERYTHING IS ALL RIGHT, THAT HE CAN GO ON, THAT THE U.S. POSITION IS FAVORABLE TO HIS REGIME."}, {"text": "THE HUMAN RIGHTS CHAMPION ASKS NO QUESTIONS ABOUT THE RECENT BRUTAL KILLINGS OF UNION LEADERS BY THE ARMY."}, {"text": "BUSH ASKS NO QUESTIONS ABOUT THE MASSACRE OF SPANISH PRIESTS."}, {"text": "THE PRESIDENT ONLY PRAISES THE ARMY, THE AIR FORCE, THE POLICE AND PARAMILITARY EFFORTS TO STOP THE GUERRILLA OFFENSIVE."}, {"text": "BUSH AND CRISTIANI COULD NOT FAIL TO MENTION THE TRITE SLOGAN OF THE CUBAN AND NICARAGUAN AID TO THE SALVADORAN GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "NOR DID BUSH FAIL TO EXPRESS THE AMERICAN PEOPLE'S SOLIDARITY."}, {"text": "BUT, SOLIDARITY WITH WHOM?"}, {"text": "ALL WE HAVE HEARD ABOUT UP TO NOW ARE THE PROTESTS PROVOKED IN THE UNITED STATES BY THE U.S. MILITARY AID TO THE SALVADORAN REGIME."}, {"text": "THE ONLY REALITIES ARE THE DEMONSTRATIONS STAGED FROM LOS ANGELES TO NEW YORK TO REPUDIATE THE U.S. AID."}, {"text": "THE ONLY FACT IS THAT THE HUMAN RIGHTS CHAMPION IS BEING PUBLICLY QUESTIONED ABOUT THIS AID."}, {"text": "THE ONLY PICTURE THAT HAS BEEN DISSEMINATED THROUGHOUT THE WORLD IS THAT OF A WOMAN WHO INTERRUPTS BUSH'S SPEECH TO SHOUT TO HIM: WHY ARE WE SENDING MONEY TO EL SALVADOR?"}, {"text": "WHY ARE WE KILLING PRIESTS IN EL SALVADOR?"}, {"text": "IT IS NOT POSSIBLE TO OVERLOOK THE U.S. GOVERNMENT'S RESPONSIBILITY IN THE CURRENT SALVADORAN SITUATION."}, {"text": "THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNITY MUST BE AWARE OF THIS REALITY AND MUST ACT ACCORDINGLY."}], "template": {"sentences": [{"text": "...THAT THE FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) LAUNCHED AGAINST THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE ON 11 NOVEMBER."}, {"text": "THE FMLN LAUNCHED THIS AGGRESSION WITH ALL OF ITS FORCES, CHIEFLY USING A CONCENTRATION OF WEAPONS AND FIGHTERS IN THE SAN SALVADOR METROPOLITAN ZONE, IN ZACATECOLUCA, LA PAZ DEPARTMENT, AND AT TIMES IN USULUTAN CITY, USULUTAN DEPARMENT, AND IN SAN MIGUEL CITY, SAN MIGUEL DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "IN THIS AGGRESSION THE FMLN DISPLAYED ITS WEAPONRY."}, {"text": "IT DISPLAYED AN INCREDIBLE AMOUNT OF WEAPONS, WHICH....(CHANGES THOUGHT) BY THE WAY, IN RECENT DAYS THE SALVADORAN ARMED FORCES HAVE BEGUN A NUMBER OF SEARCHES IN SOME HOUSES WHERE IT IS BELIEVED THAT SOME OF THESE WEAPONS WERE LOCATED."}, {"text": "WE HAVE ALREADY FOUND LARGE AMOUNTS OF WEAPONS."}, {"text": "IN ADDITION, THE FMLN LAUNCHED AN AGGRESSION AND HID BEHIND YOU, SALVADORAN PEOPLE."}, {"text": "IT USED YOU AS A SHIELD, WANTING TO CONVEY THE IDEA THAT THEY HAVE THE SUPPORT OF THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE AND THAT THE PEOPLE HERE WOULD RISE UP TO SUPPORT THEM."}, {"text": "THEY HAVE REALIZED THAT THIS VIEW IS TOTALLY FALSE."}, {"text": "FAR FROM SUPPORTING THE FMLN, THE SALVADORAN PEOPLE, SALVADORAN BROTHERS, SUPPORTED THE ARMED FORCES IN THE TREMENDOUS EFFORT IT HAS CONDUCTED TO REPEL THE FMLN AGGRESSION."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, WE MUST NOW CONSIDER A VERY IMPORTANT MATTER."}, {"text": "IT IS IMPOSSIBLE TO CARRY OUT AN AGGRESSION OF THIS SIZE WITHOUT SUPPORT FROM SOMEONE ABROAD."}, {"text": "ON THIS OCCASION, WE ARE CERTAIN THAT THIS SUPPORT CAME FROM NICARAGUAN PRESIDENT ORTEGA AND CUBAN PRESIDENT CASTRO, BUT CHIEFLY FROM ORTEGA WHO IS TRYING TO RAISE A SMOKESCREEN IN THE FACE OF THE REAL POSSIBILITY THAT MRS VIOLETTA CHAMORRO MAY DEFEAT HIM IN THE ELECTIONS, AND BECAUSE THE FMLN HAS ALWAYS BEEN THE PUPPET OF THE INTERNATIONAL COMMUNIST AGGRESSION IN WHICH ORTEGA AND CASTRO PARTICIPATE."}, {"text": "IF THIS IS NOT SO, LET US TAKE A LOOK AT WHAT HAS HAPPENED."}, {"text": "DURING THOSE TIMES WHEN YOU WERE SUFFERING MOMENTS OF ANGUISH LAST WEEK, YOU WERE ABLE TO SEE THE LARGE NUMBER OF FOREIGNERS WHO WERE SUPPORTING THE FMLN TERRORISTS."}, {"text": "WE HAVE ALSO MANAGED TO COLLECT EVIDENCE THAT THE ORTEGA GOVERNMENT TRAINED FMLN FIGHTERS IN THE USE OF CERTAIN KINDS OF WEAPONRY, SPECIFICALLY THE GRENADE LAUNCHERS."}, {"text": "WHAT HAPPENED?"}, {"text": "IN THE PAST FEW WEEKS WE BEGAN NOTICING WHAT KIND OF WEAPONS WERE BEING USED."}, {"text": "IN THE FOILED ATTACK ON THE PRESIDENTIAL HOUSE, A SUBSEQUENT ATTACK ON THE SALVADORAN ARMED FORCES' JOINT CHIEFS OF STAFF, AND LASTLY, AN ATTACK ON THE NATIONAL GUARD GARRISON PARTICULAR KINDS OF WEAPONS WERE BEING USED."}, {"text": "AS A RESULT OF THE SAVAGE ACTION BY FMLN, TWO LITTLE GIRLS WERE KILLED."}, {"text": "MOREOVER, LET US RECALL AND SEE THE CONNECTION THAT EXISTS WITH ALL THE SHIPMENTS THAT THE SALVADORAN ARMED FORCES HAVE BEEN STOPPING BETWEEN NICARAGUAN AND EL SALVADOR."}, {"text": "ONE SHIPMENT WAS MADE PRIOR TO THE VISIT WE PRESIDENTS MADE TO COSTA RICA."}, {"text": "IN THAT COUNTRY, WE DENOUNCED ORTEGA FOR CONTINUING TO SEND WEAPONS AND SUPPORTING THE FMLN IN AN OPEN VIOLATION OF THE CENTRAL AMERICAN PEACE PROCESS."}, {"text": "AND WHAT HAS HAPPENED LATELY?"}, {"text": "ON 25 NOVEMBER, SALVADORAN PEOPLE, TWO LIGHT AIRPLANES COMING FROM NICARAGUA WERE DISCOVERED."}, {"text": "THEIR FLIGHT COURSE INDICATES THAT THEY CAME FROM NICARAGUA, ESPECIALLY THE ONE WHERE THE WEAPONS WERE FOUND."}, {"text": "AS ADDITIONAL PROOF, WE HAVE A DOCUMENT SHOWING THAT ONE LIGHT AIRCRAFT BELONGS TO THE SETA TRANSPORTATION COMPANY LOCATED IN NICARAGUA'S AUGUSTO CESAR SANDINO AIRPORT."}, {"text": "IT WAS BRINGING SOPHISTICATED EQUIPMENT FOR THE FMLN."}, {"text": "IN THAT AIRCRAFT ACCIDENT, FOUR PEOPLE WERE KILLED: THE PILOT WHO WAS WEARING CIVILIAN CLOTHES AND THREE OTHER PEOPLE WERE WEARING MILITARY UNIFORMS; I MEAN CAMOUFLAGE UNIFORMS LIKE THE ONES WORN IN MANY COUNTRIES, AND LIKE THE ONES THE SALVADORAN ARMED FORCE USE."}, {"text": "IT IS BELIEVED THAT TWO OF THOSE PEOPLE DIED AS A RESULT OF THE ACCIDENT."}, {"text": "WE ALSO BELIEVE THAT ANOTHER PERSON KILLED HIMSELF BECAUSE HE HAD A WEAPON IN HIS HAND AND A BULLET WOUND IN FOREHEAD."}, {"text": "HE KILLED HIMSELF BECAUSE HE SAW HIMSELF IMPLICATED IN THIS SITUATION."}, {"text": "(CONTINUED)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0070", "message_template": 1, "message_template_optional": true, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["11 NOV 89 - 26 NOV {"sentences": [{"text": "OUR FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) FORCES HAVE TAKEN OVER BUNKERS FROM THE VARIOUS MILITARY CHIEFS IN ESCALON AND MANUEL JOSE ARCE NEIGHBORHOODS WHERE OUR UNITS SEIZED THOUSANDS OF CARTRIDGES, RIFLES, GRENADES, AND OTHER TYPES OF ARMS WHICH THESE MILITARY CHIEFS USUALLY STORE IN THE BUNKERS THAT THEY MAINTAIN IN THESE RESIDENTIAL SECTORS."}, {"text": "AS WE HAVE REPORTED, THE GENERAL STAFF RESPONDED WITH A 4-PRONGED DELAYED RESPONSE."}, {"text": "THE ARMED FORCES ATTACKED FROM FOUR ADVANCED POSITIONS, ONE HELD BY THE BRACAMONTE BATTALION, WHICH ADVANCED TOWARD ESCALON; IT WAS NEUTRALIZED BY OUR AMBUSHES."}, {"text": "OUR UNITS ARE ENTRENCHED IN THE MANSIONS OF THE OLIGARCHS IN THAT SECTOR OF ESCALON NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "THEY AMBUSHED AND REPELLED ATTACKS FROM THE VANGUARD POSITIONS LAUNCHED BY THE ARMED FORCES."}, {"text": "THE SECOND DIRECTION IN WHICH THE ENEMY RESPONDED TO OUR PRESENCE WAS DIRECTED ON THE SOUTHERN FREEWAY."}, {"text": "THIS SECOND POSITION WAS AMBUSHED WITH RPG-7 ROCKET LAUNCHERS AND MACHINEGUN FIRE."}, {"text": "THE THIRD ENEMY POSITION, WHICH WAS ADVANCING ON SANTA TECLA, WAS AMBUSHED AT LA UNIVERSAL POINT AND WAS ALSO NEUTRALIZED."}, {"text": "THE ATLACATL BATTALION DEPLOYMENT ALONG GUADALUPE GARDENS WAS ALSO NEUTRALIZED."}, {"text": "OUR BATTALIONS ARE STAGING SABOTAGE ACTIONS ON ELECTRICITY POSTS IN THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS."}, {"text": "ALSO, WE HAVE A NEW REPORT WHICH INDICATES THAT FMLN UNITS HAVE SET UP DOWNED ELECTRICITY POSTS AS BARRICADES ALONG THE SOUTH FREEWAY AND IN THE ESCALON NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "WE REPEAT, ALONG THE SOUTH FREEWAY AND IN THE ESCALON NEIGHBORHOOD, FMLN UNITS HAVE USED DOWNED ELECTRICITY POSTS AND VEHICLES AS BARRICADES."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE SITUATION IN EL SALVADOR."}, {"text": "THROUGHOUT THE NORTHERN SECTOR OF THE CAPITAL, OUR UNITS ARE MAINTAINING POSITIONS."}, {"text": "THE TROOPS IN THE INTERIOR PART OF THE REPUBLIC IN THAT NORTHERN REGION REFUSE TO ADVANCE TOWARD OUR POSITIONS, WHILE OUR UNITS ARE EXTENDING ALONG THE NORTHWESTERN AND SOUTHWESTERN REGION OF THE CAPITAL."}, {"text": "OUR UNITS ARE EXTENDING AND MOVING FOWARD ALONG THESE ZONES."}, {"text": "THE AIR FORCE HAS OPENED FIRE ON SOME OF OUR POSITIONS IN THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS."}, {"text": "WE REITERATE THE CALL TO THE INHABITANTS OF THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS TO ABANDON ALL THOSE ZONES IMMEDIATELY."}, {"text": "THE AIR FORCE IS BEGINNING NEW AIR RAIDS ON FMLN POSITIONS IN THOSE REGIONS."}, {"text": "THEREFORE, WE CALL ON THE INHABITANTS OF THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS TO LEAVE THOSE AREAS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0071", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": UNITS SEIZED THOUSANDS OF CARTRIDGES, RIFLES, GRENADES, AND OTHER TYPES OF ARMS WHICH THESE MILITARY CHIEFS USUALLY STORE IN THE BUNKERS THAT THEY MAINTAIN IN THESE RESIDENTIAL SECTORS."}, {"text": "AS WE HAVE REPORTED, THE GENERAL STAFF RESPONDED WITH A 4-PRONGED DELAYED RESPONSE."}, {"text": "THE ARMED FORCES ATTACKED FROM FOUR ADVANCED POSITIONS, ONE HELD BY THE BRACAMONTE BATTALION, WHICH ADVANCED TOWARD ESCALON; IT WAS NEUTRALIZED BY OUR AMBUSHES."}, {"text": "OUR UNITS ARE ENTRENCHED IN THE MANSIONS OF THE OLIGARCHS IN THAT SECTOR OF ESCALON NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "THEY AMBUSHED AND REPELLED ATTACKS FROM THE VANGUARD POSITIONS LAUNCHED BY THE ARMED FORCES."}, {"text": "THE SECOND DIRECTION IN WHICH THE ENEMY RESPONDED TO OUR PRESENCE WAS DIRECTED ON THE SOUTHERN FREEWAY."}, {"text": "THIS SECOND POSITION WAS AMBUSHED WITH RPG-7 ROCKET LAUNCHERS AND MACHINEGUN FIRE."}, {"text": "THE THIRD ENEMY POSITION, WHICH WAS ADVANCING ON SANTA TECLA, WAS AMBUSHED AT LA UNIVERSAL POINT AND WAS ALSO NEUTRALIZED."}, {"text": "THE ATLACATL BATTALION DEPLOYMENT ALONG GUADALUPE GARDENS WAS ALSO NEUTRALIZED."}, {"text": "OUR BATTALIONS ARE STAGING SABOTAGE ACTIONS ON ELECTRICITY POSTS IN THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS."}, {"text": "ALSO, WE HAVE A NEW REPORT WHICH INDICATES THAT FMLN UNITS HAVE SET UP DOWNED ELECTRICITY POSTS AS BARRICADES ALONG THE SOUTH FREEWAY AND IN THE ESCALON NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": "WE REPEAT, ALONG THE SOUTH FREEWAY AND IN THE ESCALON NEIGHBORHOOD, FMLN UNITS HAVE USED DOWNED ELECTRICITY POSTS AND VEHICLES AS BARRICADES."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE SITUATION IN EL SALVADOR."}, {"text": "THROUGHOUT THE NORTHERN SECTOR OF THE CAPITAL, OUR UNITS ARE MAINTAINING POSITIONS."}, {"text": "THE TROOPS IN THE INTERIOR PART OF THE REPUBLIC IN THAT NORTHERN REGION REFUSE TO ADVANCE TOWARD OUR POSITIONS, WHILE OUR UNITS ARE EXTENDING ALONG THE NORTHWESTERN AND SOUTHWESTERN REGION OF THE CAPITAL."}, {"text": "OUR UNITS ARE EXTENDING AND MOVING FOWARD ALONG THESE ZONES."}, {"text": "THE AIR FORCE HAS OPENED FIRE ON SOME OF OUR POSITIONS IN THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS."}, {"text": "WE REITERATE THE CALL TO THE INHABITANTS OF THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS TO ABANDON ALL THOSE ZONES IMMEDIATELY."}, {"text": "THE AIR FORCE IS BEGINNING NEW AIR RAIDS ON FMLN POSITIONS IN THOSE REGIONS."}, {"text": "THEREFORE, WE CALL ON THE INHABITANTS OF THE ESCALON AND SAN BENITO NEIGHBORHOODS TO LEAVE THOSE AREAS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0071", "message_template": 2, "incident_date": [{"type": {"sentences": [{"text": "THE TREASURY POLICE HAVE INFORMED THIS NETWORK THAT TERRORIST (WORDS INDISTINCT) ALBERTO CHICA FERNANDEZ, A LEADER IN THE (NAME INDISTINCT) LABOR UNION, CONFESSED THAT THE FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) TERRORIST LEADERS MAY INITIATE SUMMARY ACTIONS WITH A VIEW TO PURGING THE LEADERS OF LEFTIST GROUPS BECAUSE OF THE FAILURE OF THE SO-CALLED "FINAL OFFENSIVE TO THE END.""}, {"text": "CHICA SAID THAT THE TERRORIST LEADERSHIP HAS VIOLENTLY (WORD INDISTINCT) HUMBERTO CENTENO, MARCO TULIO LIMA, AND AN INDIVIDUAL IDENTIFIED ONLY AS JULIO CESAR, FROM THE UNTS (NATIONAL UNION OF SALVADORAN WORKERS), AS WELL AS OTHER LEFTIST LEADERS, FOR PROVIDING FALSE INFORMATION REGARDING THE CONDITIONS FOR A POPULAR INSURRECTION."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO CHICA, THE FMLN LEADERS IN MANAGUA DECIDED TO LAUNCH THE OFFENSIVE, TRUSTING THE UNTS LEADERS' REPORTS THAT CONDITIONS WERE RIGHT FOR AN INSURRECTION BECAUSE FEBE ELIZABETH VELAZQUEZ' DEATH IN THE DYNAMITE ATTACK AGAINST FENASTRAS (SALVADORAN WORKERS NATIONAL UNION FEDERATION) HAD IGNITED THE PEOPLE'S SPIRITS."}, {"text": "THE PRISONER SAID THAT THE FMLN MAY CARRY OUT A SUMMARY TRIAL IN THE STYLE OF COMMUNIST PARTIES AGAINST THOSE RESPONSIBLE FOR THE FAILURE."}, {"text": "NOW, HE SAID, TO SAVE THEMSELVES FROM THE RESPONSIBILITY OF HAVING DECEIVED THE TERRORIST CRIMINALS WHO ALLOWED THEMSELVES TO BE LED BY LIES, THE UNTS LEADERS ARE EXPECTED TO CALL NEWS CONFERENCES TO ANNOUNCE THAT THEIR STRUGGLE CONTINUES."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, A REPORT FROM ZACATECOLUCA, LA PAZ DEPARTMENT, INDICATES THAT FMLN TERRORIST CRIMINALS, USING SAM-7 MISSILES, ATTACKED A SALVADORAN AIR FORCE 0-2 AIRPLANE WHICH WAS IN THE AREA DIRECTING SUPPORT NEAR PIEDRA GRANDE ABAJO IN THE JURISDICTION OF ZACATECOLUCA."}, {"text": "NO DAMAGES OR CASUALTIES WERE REPORTED."}, {"text": "ANOTHER FMLN MISSILE WAS FIRED FROM LAS PIEDRAS HILL, IN THE SAME AREA, AGAINST ANOTHER SALVADORAN AIR FORCE 0-2 AIRPLANE, BUT THE AIRPLANE WAS NOT DAMAGED."}, {"text": "THE SOURCE SAYS THE MISSILE EXPLODED IN THE AIR OVER ZACATECOLUCA."}, {"text": "THE AIR FORCE, TO WHICH EXPERIENCED PILOTS LEND THEIR PROFESSIONAL SERVICES, IS {"sentences": [{"text": "COMRADES: A NEW ELEMENT THAT WE MUST ANALYZE AND EXPLAIN EMERGED AT THE CONCLUSION OF THE CENTRAL AMERICAN PRESIDENTS' EMERGENCY MEETING."}, {"text": "LET US SEE FIRST WHY THE MEETING TOOK PLACE."}, {"text": "THE MAIN REASON IS THE VERY COMPLICATED PREDICAMENT IN WHICH OUR OFFENSIVE HAS PLACED CRISTIANI AND THE HIGH COMMAND."}, {"text": "AS YOU WILL REMEMBER, THE GOVERNMENT HAS MET WITH MUCH INTERNATIONAL DISREPUTE AND ISOLATION BECAUSE OF THE BRUTAL ASSASSINATION OF JESUIT PRIESTS AND THE BOMBING OF THE CIVILIAN POPULATION."}, {"text": "LET US RECALL, AS A SIGNIFICANT FACT, THAT THE UNITED NATIONS HAS CONDEMNED THE GOVERNMENT BECAUSE OF ALL IT HAS DONE, ESPECIALLY BECAUSE OF THE LATEST ATROCITIES."}, {"text": "ON THAT OCCASION, EL SALVADOR WAS THE ONLY COUNTRY THAT VOTED AGAINST THAT RESOLUTION WHILE 96 COUNTRIES VOTED IN FAVOR."}, {"text": "WE MENTION THIS CASE AS A MOST SIGNIFICANT ONE, BUT THE FACT IS THAT THERE HAS BEEN SO MUCH WORLDWIDE CONDEMNATION THAT THE DICTATORSHIP HAS FOUND ITSELF IN A REALLY DESPERATE SITUATION."}, {"text": "THIS WAS A CAUSE OF CONCERN FOR THE NORTH AMERICANS."}, {"text": "TO WHOM COULD THEY TURN AT A TIME WHEN ALL INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS HAD TURNED THEIR BACKS ON CRISTIANI?"}, {"text": "THE NORTH AMERICANS HAD TO RESORT TO SOME FORUM THAT WOULD NOT CONDEMN THE GENOCIDAL REGIME AND THAT, ON THE CONTRARY, WOULD PROVIDE SUPPORT IN SPITE OF ALL THE ATROCITIES THE REGIME HAS COMMITTED."}, {"text": "THE MOST SUITABLE IDEA WAS TO PROMOTE AN EMERGENCY MEETING OF CENTRAL AMERICAN PRESIDENTS, BECAUSE IN CENTRAL AMERICA, AS WE ALL KNOW, THE NORTH AMERICANS HAVE HAD THEIR BACKYARD AND MOST OF THESE COUNTRIES SERVE THEIR INTERESTS."}, {"text": "THE MEETING WAS CALLED TO TRY TO PULL CRISTIANI OUT OF INTERNATIONAL ISOLATION."}, {"text": "UNDER WHAT CONDITIONS DID SUMMIT TAKE PLACE?"}, {"text": "WE HAVE TO SAY FIRST THAT THE PRESIDENTS OF EL SALVADOR AND COSTA RICA, AND PROBABLY OF GUATEMALA, HAD REACHED AN AGREEMENT PRIOR TO THE MEETING."}, {"text": "THE SUBJECT OF THE DISCUSSION WAS A DOCUMENT DRAFTED BY ARIAS AND CEREZO."}, {"text": "THIS DOCUMENT EXPRESSED SUPPORT FOR CRISTIANI FROM THE VERY BEGINNING."}, {"text": "JOSEPH SULLIVAN, A U.S. STATE DEPARTMENT OFFICIAL IN CHARGE OF LATIN AMERICAN AFFAIRS, AS WELL AS OTHER U.S. STATE DEPARTMENT OFFICIALS, WERE PRESENT AT THE MEETING."}, {"text": "THE COSTA RICAN AMBASSADOR TO NICARAGUA -- A PRO-U.S. MAN WHO INTRODUCED THE NICARAGUAN CONTRAS AT THE MEETING -- WAS ALSO PRESENT, CONSPIRING ALL THE TIME."}, {"text": "THE FMLN WAS NOT EVEN ALLOWED TO ENTER COSTA RICA."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, IN SPITE OF THE FACT THAT THE MEETING HAD BEEN FIXED AND IN SPITE OF THE U.S. PRESENCE, THE AGREEMENT TO SUPPORT CRISTIANI WAS ACHIEVED ALMOST AT THE PRICE OF KILLING THE ESQUIPULAS AGREEMENT."}, {"text": "IT WAS NOT EASY."}, {"text": "THE U.S. WILL TO CONDEMN THE FMLN AND TO BACK CRISTIANI PREVAILED IN THE MIDST OF MUCH BICKERING AND THE INSOLENCE OF THE HONDURAN PRESIDENT."}, {"text": "AS YOU CAN SEE, IT WAS NOT EASY TO FIND SUPPORT FOR THE GENOCIDAL REGIME EVEN IN PLACES WHERE THE NORTH AMERICANS THINK THEY HAVE THE BULL BY THE HORNS."}, {"text": "LET US SEE, AS A THIRD POINT, IN WHAT THE DECLARATION CONSISTS."}, {"text": "(CONTINUED)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0076", "message_template": 1, {"sentences": [{"text": "IN VIEW OF THE SUCCESSFUL OPERATION TODAY IN WHICH GONZALO RODRIGUEZ GACHA, HIS SON FREDDY, AND SEVERAL OF HIS BODYGUARDS WERE KILLED, PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO TODAY CALLED AN URGENT COUNCIL OF MINISTERS MEETING TO DISCUSS THE SITUATION AND RECEIVE A FULL REPORT FROM MILITARY AND POLICE AUTHORITIES."}, {"text": "HERE IS THE SECOND PART OF THE NEWS CONFERENCE FEATURING DAS DIRECTOR GENERAL MIGUEL MAZA MARQUEZ."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (MAZA) THE DAS HAS EVIDENCE SHOWING THAT THIS INDIVIDUAL MASTERMINDED TWO ATTACKS INCLUDING THE THE MOST RECENT AND WORST ONE IN WHICH MORE THAN 60 INNOCENT PEOPLE WERE KILLED."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "HOW DO YOU KNOW THAT GONZALO RODRIGUEZ GACHA MASTERMINDED THE RECENT ATTACK ON DAS?"}, {"text": "(MAZA) BECAUSE THE INVESTIGATIONS THAT WE HAVE CONDUCTED ALONG WITH THE NATIONAL POLICE EVER SINCE THE ATTACK OCCURRED POINT IN THAT DIRECTION."}, {"text": "IF WE COMPARE THE MODUS OPERANDI OF RODRIGUEZ AND HIS PEOPLE, WE COME TO THE CONCLUSION THAT THE PERIOD BETWEEN THE (WORD INDISTINCT) AND THE ACTION ITSELF ARE VERY SIMILAR."}, {"text": "FURTHERMORE, THIS MAN WAS IN THERE CELEBRATING THE GENOCIDE THAT HE HAD COMMITTED IN BOGOTA."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "(QUESTION INDISTINCT) (MAZA) BECAUSE THE INTELLIGENCE REPORTS INDICATE THIS, AND ACCORDING TO CERTAIN STATEMENTS WE HAVE, HE WAS OVERJOYED BY THE DAMAGE THAT HE HAD CAUSED IN THE CITY GIVEN THE LARGE NUMBER OF PEOPLE WHO WERE KILLED; SEEING HIM SUNBATHING AND SWIMMING ON THE ATLANTIC COAST LED US TO BELIEVE THIS."}, {"text": "(REPORTER) IS THIS A POLICE REACTION TO THE DRUG TRAFFICKERS' ATTACK ON DAS?"}, {"text": "(MAZA) NO, I AM NOT SAYING THAT IT IS A REACTION."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE RESULT OF VERY PROFESSIONAL WORK ON THE PART OF THE NATIONAL POLICE."}, {"text": "THAT IS WHAT I TOLD THE PRESIDENT TODAY."}, {"text": "I BRIEFED HIM ON THE EVENTS WHICH LED TO THE ACTION THAT HAS CHANGED THE SITUATION WHICH HAD PREVAILED IN THE {"sentences": [{"text": "FOREIGN MINISTER HERNAN FELIPE ERRAZURIZ HAS REPORTED THAT THE CHILEANS INVOLVED IN THE ABDUCTION OF BRAZILIAN BUSINESSMAN ABILIO DINIZ WILL BE PROSECUTED IN BRAZIL BECAUSE THE KIDNAPPING WAS PLANNED AND PERFORMED OUTSIDE OF CHILE."}, {"text": "HE NOTED THAT, IN LINE WITH ITS POLICY IN SUCH MATTERS, THE CHILEAN FOREIGN MINISTRY HAS NOT BEEN INVOLVED IN THE RELEASE OF THE BUSINESSMAN."}, {"text": "DINIZ WAS RELEASED AFTER BEING HELD FOR 6 DAYS BY FIVE CHILEANS, TWO CANADIANS, TWO ARGENTINES, AND ONE BRAZILIAN."}, {"text": "THE POLICE HAVE REPORTED THAT THE CHILEANS CLAIMED TO BELONG TO THE EXTREMIST MIR (MOVEMENT OF THE REVOLUTIONARY LEFT) GROUP, BUT THIS ASSERTION HAS NOT YET BEEN CONFIRMED."}, {"text": "ERRAZURIZ SAID THAT THE FOREIGN MINISTRY HAS BEEN IN PERMANENT CONTACT WITH CHILEAN AMBASSADOR TO BRAZIL RAUL SCHMIDT IN KEEPING TRACK OF THE CASE."}, {"text": "THE MINISTER ALSO POINTED OUT THAT HE HAS BEEN IN DIRECT CONTACT WITH INTERNATIONAL SECURITY SERVICES, INCLUDING INTERPOL, TO DETERMINE THE IDENTITIES OF THE PRESUMED CHILEANS."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0078", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", {"sentences": [{"text": "OFFICIAL SOURCES TODAY REPORTED THAT AT LEAST EIGHT PEOPLE, INCLUDING SOLDIERS, REBELS, AND CIVILIANS, WERE KILLED DURING CLASHES BETWEEN THE ARMY AND GUERRILLAS OVER THE PAST WEEKEND IN VARIOUS POINTS OF THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "MILITARY SPOKESMEN FOR THE 6TH INFANTRY BRIGADE, HEADQUARTERED IN THE EASTERN USULUTAN DEPARTMENT, TOLD ACAN-EFE THAT TWO REBELS WERE KILLED AND ONE WOUNDED DURING A CLASH WITH GOVERNMENT TROOPS IN SAN AGUSTIN."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, THE ARMED FORCES PRESS COMMITTEE (COPREFA) REPORTED THAT THE BODIES OF TWO GUERRILLAS, WHO WERE PRESUMABLY KILLED DURING CLASHES WITH THE ARMY, WERE FOUND BY SOLDIERS IN THE OUTSKIRTS OF SANTA TECLA, IN THE CENTRAL LA LIBERTAD DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "COPREFA REPORTED THAT TWO SOLDIERS WERE KILLED DURING A CLASH WITH MEMBERS OF THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN) IN COMASAGUA, ABOUT 28 KM TO THE SOUTHWEST OF (SAN) SALVADOR, WHERE A REBEL ATTACK ON A COFFEE PROCESSING PLANT WAS SUCCESSFULLY REPELLED."}, {"text": "IT REPORTED THAT A CIVILIAN WAS KILLED IN THE CROSSFIRE AND THAT A SOLDIER WAS ALSO KILLED DURING CLASHES IN ZARAGOZA, SOUTH OF SAN SALVADOR, WHERE TWO GUERRILLAS WERE WOUNDED."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY REPORT STATED THAT 10 REBELS WERE WOUNDED IN TECOLUCA, SAN VICENTE DEPARTMENT, ABOUT 60 KM EAST OF THE CAPITAL, DURING AN ARMED CLASH BETWEEN INSURGENTS AND THE 5TH (INFANTRY) BRIGADE, HEADQUARTERED IN THAT DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "THREE OTHER SOLDIERS WERE WOUNDED DURING AN FMLN AMBUSH IN GUAZAPA, NORTH OF (SAN) SALVADOR, ONE OF THE GUERRILLAS' MAIN BASTIONS."}, {"text": "THE SALVADORAN (AIR) FORCE THIS MORNING BOMBED REBEL POSITIONS IN THE OUTSKIRTS OF JUCUAPA, USULUTAN DEPARTMENT, BUT NO RESULTS ARE YET AVAILABLE, AREA RESIDENTS TOLD ACAN-EFE."}, {"text": "THE FMLN THIS MORNING HARRASSED (ARMY POSITIONS STATIONED NEAR) AYUTUXTEPEQUE, NORTH OF (SAN) SALVADOR, WITHOUT INFLICTING ANY CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "COPREFA ALSO REPORTED THAT THE (ARMED) FORCES SEIZED FROM THE GUERRILLAS 500 ELECTRIC CATAPULTS, IN THE NORTHERN (CHALATENANGO) DEPARTMENT, WHICH THE FMLN HAD USED SINCE LAST YEAR TO ATTACK (SAN) SALVADOR GARRISONS."}, {"text": "SALVADORAN (RED) CROSS SOURCES TODAY REPORTED THAT A 48-YEAR-OLD WOMAN IDENTIFIED AS MARIA LUZ LOPEZ WAS WOUNDED LAST NIGHT WHEN A POWERFUL BOMB, WHICH DAMAGED SEVERAL BUSINESSES IN (SAN) SALVADOR, EXPLODED."}, {"text": "THE BOMB WAS PLANTED IN A HEAVILY COMMERCIAL AREA OF DOWNTOWN (SAN) SALVADOR CAUSING HEAVY PROPERTY LOSES, ACCORDING TO THE OWNERS WHO PROVIDED NO SPECIFIC FIGURES."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE FOURTH DYNAMITE ATTACK ON BUSINESSES IN (SAN) SALVADOR SO FAR IN 1990."}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLAS INTENSIFIED THEIR ACTS OF SABOTAGE AGAINST THE ECONOMY, ESPECIALLY AGAINST THE ENTIRE ELECTRICAL POWER SYSTEM, ON 2 JANUARY WHEN AN UNILATERAL MILITARY TRUCE THEY DECREED OVER THE CHRISTMAS AND NEW YEAR HOLIDAYS HAD EXPIRED."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0080", {"sentences": [{"text": "OFFICIAL SOURCES TODAY REPORTED THAT AT LEAST EIGHT PEOPLE, INCLUDING SOLDIERS, REBELS, AND CIVILIANS, WERE KILLED DURING CLASHES BETWEEN THE ARMY AND GUERRILLAS OVER THE PAST WEEKEND IN VARIOUS POINTS OF THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "MILITARY SPOKESMEN FOR THE 6TH INFANTRY BRIGADE, HEADQUARTERED IN THE EASTERN USULUTAN DEPARTMENT, TOLD ACAN-EFE THAT TWO REBELS WERE KILLED AND ONE WOUNDED DURING A CLASH WITH GOVERNMENT TROOPS IN SAN AGUSTIN."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, THE ARMED FORCES PRESS COMMITTEE (COPREFA) REPORTED THAT THE BODIES OF TWO GUERRILLAS, WHO WERE PRESUMABLY KILLED DURING CLASHES WITH THE ARMY, WERE FOUND BY SOLDIERS IN THE OUTSKIRTS OF SANTA TECLA, IN THE CENTRAL LA LIBERTAD DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "COPREFA REPORTED THAT TWO SOLDIERS WERE KILLED DURING A CLASH WITH MEMBERS OF THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN) IN COMASAGUA, ABOUT 28 KM TO THE SOUTHWEST OF (SAN) SALVADOR, WHERE A REBEL ATTACK ON A COFFEE PROCESSING PLANT WAS SUCCESSFULLY REPELLED."}, {"text": "IT REPORTED THAT A CIVILIAN WAS KILLED IN THE CROSSFIRE AND THAT A SOLDIER WAS ALSO KILLED DURING CLASHES IN ZARAGOZA, SOUTH OF SAN SALVADOR, WHERE TWO GUERRILLAS WERE WOUNDED."}, {"text": "THE MILITARY REPORT STATED THAT 10 REBELS WERE WOUNDED IN TECOLUCA, SAN VICENTE DEPARTMENT, ABOUT 60 KM EAST OF THE CAPITAL, DURING AN ARMED CLASH BETWEEN INSURGENTS AND THE 5TH (INFANTRY) BRIGADE, HEADQUARTERED IN THAT DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "THREE OTHER SOLDIERS WERE WOUNDED DURING AN FMLN AMBUSH IN GUAZAPA, NORTH OF (SAN) SALVADOR, ONE OF THE GUERRILLAS' MAIN BASTIONS."}, {"text": "THE SALVADORAN (AIR) FORCE THIS MORNING BOMBED REBEL POSITIONS IN THE OUTSKIRTS OF JUCUAPA, USULUTAN DEPARTMENT, BUT NO RESULTS ARE YET AVAILABLE, AREA RESIDENTS TOLD ACAN-EFE."}, {"text": "THE FMLN THIS MORNING HARRASSED (ARMY POSITIONS STATIONED NEAR) AYUTUXTEPEQUE, NORTH OF (SAN) SALVADOR, WITHOUT INFLICTING ANY CASUALTIES."}, {"text": "COPREFA ALSO REPORTED {"sentences": [{"text": "GOOD EVENING."}, {"text": "I HAVE CALLED THIS NEWS CONFERENCE TO READ A FOREIGN MINISTRY COMMUNIQUE: (WORDS INDISTINCT) TODAY THE PANAMANIAN GOVERNMENT TOLD LUIS SANDIGA CABRERA, OUR CHARGE D'AFFAIRES IN PANAMA, THAT HE MUST LEAVE PANAMA IN 72 HOURS."}, {"text": "2. WE HAVE EXPRESSED TO THE PANAMANIAN GOVERNMENT, THROUGH THE PANAMANIAN CHARGE D'AFFAIRES IN LIMA, OUR SURPRISE AND STRONG PROTEST OVER THAT DECISION."}, {"text": "3. IN VIEW OF THIS DECISION, THE PERUVIAN GOVERNMENT HAS DECIDED TO REDUCE THE PERSONNEL OF ITS DIPLOMATIC MISSION IN PANAMA AND TO MAINTAIN ITS RELATIONS WITH THAT COUNTRY AT THE FIRST SECRETARY LEVEL."}, {"text": "PERU WILL IN THIS WAY CONTINUE TO FULFILL THE HUMANITARIAN MISSION OF PROTECTING THOSE WHO HAVE SOUGHT ASYLUM IN ITS EMBASSY IN PANAMA WHILE THE PANAMANIAN GOVERNMENT ISSUES THE SAFE-CONDUCTS THAT WE REQUESTED IN ACCORDANCE TO THE CONVENTION ON DIPLOMATIC ASYLUM SIGNED IN CARACAS ON 28 MARCH 1954."}, {"text": "PERU IS CONTACTING THE MEMBERS OF THE PERMANENT MECHANISM FOR CONSULTATION AND POLITICAL AGREEMENT (GROUP OF EIGHT) TO EXPLAIN THE SITUATION AND TO ASK FOR SOLIDARITY AND COOPERATION IN OVERCOMING THIS MOMENTARY CRISIS."}, {"text": "THE DELICATE SITUATION REGARDING THE PEOPLE AT THE PERUVIAN EMBASSY HAS PROVOKED OUR JUSTIFIED ALARM AND IMPELLED US TO BEGIN TALKS TO ENSURE THAT THEIR DIPLOMATIC ASYLUM WILL BE RESPECTED."}, {"text": "WE HAVE TALKED WITH THE AMBASSADORS FROM THE COUNTRIES OF THE PERMANENT MECHANISM FOR CONSULTATION AND POLITICAL AGREEMENT."}, {"text": "I HAVE PERSONALLY SPOKEN WITH THE AMBASSADORS OF VENEZUELA, MEXICO, AND COLOMBIA."}, {"text": "I AM NOW READY TO ANSWER ANY QUESTIONS: (REPORTER)"}, {"text": "MR LARCO COX, UNOFFICIAL SOURCES HAVE SAID THAT THE PEOPLE IN THE PERUVIAN EMBASSY IN PANAMA ARE NOT EXACTLY POLITICAL REFUGEES BUT COMMON CRIMINALS."}, {"text": "WHAT DO YOU SAY ABOUT THIS?"}, {"text": "(LARCO COX) THE COUNTRY THAT GRANTS ASYLUM DETERMINES THIS."}, {"text": "WE HAVE BEEN VERY CAREFUL TO REVIEW EACH ONE OF THEM AND THEIR FILES."}, {"text": "WE HAVE CHECKED TO SEE IF ANY OF THEM WERE FACING ANY TRIALS IN PANAMA OR THE UNITED STATES."}, {"text": "OUR INVESTIGATION HAS REVEALED THAT NONE OF THEM ARE FACING ANY TRIALS."}, {"text": "THE CHARGES WERE MADE AFTERWARD."}, {"text": "WE SEE THIS AS A RESULT OF THE EMOTIONAL CLIMATE PRESENTLY EXISTING IN PANAMA."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "WHAT IS YOUR PERSONAL OPINION OF THE INCIDENT?"}, {"text": "(LARCO COX)"}, {"text": "IT IS THE DIPLOMATIC WAY TO EXPRESS A PROTEST OVER WHAT THEY HAVE BEEN LED TO BELIEVE."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO PANAMANIAN REPORTS, CHARGE D'AFFAIRES LUIS SANDIGA HAS MADE STATEMENTS ON THE SITUATION THAT DID NOT PLEASE THE GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "THE TRUTH IS THAT SANDIGA HAS NOT MADE ANY DECLARATIONS."}, {"text": "HOWEVER, FORMER AMBASSADOR CASTRO ARENAS IS IN PANAMA AND HE HAS EMBARKED ON A CAMPAIGN IN WHICH HE IS SEEKING RETALIATION AGAINST THE PERUVIAN GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "HE COULD NOT THINK OF ANYTHING BETTER THAN TO POINT AT SANDIGA AS THE PERSON RESPONSIBLE FOR ALLEGED STATEMENTS."}, {"text": "SANDIGA HAS NOT SAID A WORD ABOUT THE SITUATION BECAUSE THAT IS NOT HIS JOB."}, {"text": "BESIDES, HIS CAR AND THE CAR BELONGING TO ONE OF THE EMBASSY'S MILITARY ATTACHES HAVE BEEN STOLEN; THERE IS NO WAY TO BEGIN AN INVESTIGATION."}, {"text": "(REPORTER) ARE YOU SAYING THAT FORMER AMBASSADOR CASTRO ARENAS IS DIRECTLY RESPONSIBLE FOR THE SITUATION?"}, {"text": "(LARCO COX) YOU CAN MAKE YOUR OWN CONCLUSIONS."}, {"text": "(REPORTER) IF THE SITUATION DETERIORATES, WILL PERU RECALL ALL OF ITS PERSONNEL FROM PANAMA?"}, {"text": "(LARCO COX) WE CANNOT GO TO THAT EXTREME BECAUSE WE ARE FULFILLING A HUMANITARIAN CAUSE, AS WE SAID IN THE COMMUNIQUE."}, {"text": "OUR FIRST RESPONSIBILITY AT THIS TIME IS TO SEE THAT THE RIGHT OF ASYLUM IS RESPECTED."}, {"text": "AS LONG AS THE REFUGEES REMAIN IN THE EMBASSY, WE WILL MAINTAIN OUR REPRESENTATION AT THE LEVEL OF FIRST {"sentences": [{"text": "THE COLOMBIAN LEFTIST ALLIANCE, PATRIOTIC UNION (UP), WAS THE FIRST PARTY TO REGISTER A PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE IN THE UPCOMING 27 MAY ELECTIONS WHEN IT OFFICIALLY REGISTERED BERNARDO JARAMILLO OSSA, 34, AS ITS CANDIDATE TODAY."}, {"text": "PRIOR TO JARAMILLO OSSA'S ARRIVAL AT THE NATIONAL REGISTRY OFFICE, ACCOMPANIED BY 12 BODYGUARDS, EXPLOSIVES EXPERTS FROM THE SECRET POLICE DEPARTMENT CHECKED THE BUILDING AND CORDONED OFF THE ENTRANCE HE WAS GOING TO USE."}, {"text": "UP WAS FOUNDED IN 1985 AND HAS LOST ALMOST 1,000 MEMBERS AND REGIONAL LEADERS IN VIOLENT ATTACKS."}, {"text": "IT HAS ALSO LOST MOST OF ITS REPRESENTATIVES IN BOGOTA, INCLUDING JAIME PARDO LEAL, THE PARTY FOUNDER AND A PREVIOUS PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE WHO WAS MURDERED IN 1987."}, {"text": "COLOMBIAN COMMUNIST PARTY PRESIDENT GILBERTO VIEIRA AND THE ENTIRE UP DIRECTORATE ATTENDED BERNARDO JARAMILLO'S REGISTRATION."}, {"text": "LAST WEEK, THE STATE COUNCIL, COLOMBIA'S HIGHEST LEGAL AND ADMINISTRATIVE BODY, HAD ACCREDITED BERNARDO JARAMILLO AS UP'S PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE."}, {"text": "BEFORE MAKING HIS CANDIDACY EFFECTIVE, BERNARDO JARAMILLO TOLD EFE THAT HE WOULD ATTEMPT TO BECOME "THE WILL OF A WIDE AND DEMOCRATIC SECTOR OF THE PEOPLE AND AN ALTERNATIVE TO TRADITIONAL COLOMBIAN BIPARTISANSHIP.""}, {"text": "HE ADDED: "OUR MOVEMENT WANTS TO TRANSCEND THE LIMITS OF THE UP AND OBTAIN FOLLOWERS FROM OTHER SECTORS OF THE DEMOCRATIC LEFT WHO SUPPORT NEW GOVERNMENT ALTERNATIVES.""}, {"text": "HE DID NOT REJECT THE POSSIBILITY THAT UP AND THE 19TH APRIL MOVEMENT (M-19), A REBEL MOVEMENT THAT IS MAKING EFFORTS TO JOIN THE COUNTRY'S LEGAL POLITICAL SYSTEM, WILL PRESENT JOINT ELECTORAL TICKETS IN SOME REGIONS IN THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": ""THERE IS NOTHING CONCRETE ON THIS," HE ADDED, "BUT IT COULD BE AN ALTERNATIVE IF THEY PROPOSE IT.""}, {"text": "UP PRESIDENT DIEGO MONTANA STATED THAT "OUR PARTY'S MAIN OBJECTIVE IN THESE ELECTIONS IS TO BREAK THE LIBERAL AND SOCIAL CONSERVATIVE HEGEMONY.""}, {"text": "THESE TWO SECTORS HAVE SHARED POWER DURING COLOMBIA'S ENTIRE REPUBLICAN PERIOD."}, {"text": ""WE PRESENT OUR CANDIDATE TO OTHER POLITICAL MOVEMENTS WITH THE HOPE THAT HIS CANDIDACY WILL BE BACKED AND THAT WE CAN CREATE A NEW AND WIDER FORCE WITH POSSIBILITIES OF ATTAINING VICTORY," HE NOTED."}, {"text": "JARAMILLO'S CAMPAIGN SLOGAN, "COUNTRYMEN, GIVE ME YOUR HAND" APPEARED IN POSTERS THROUGHOUT BOGOTA TODAY."}, {"text": "AFTER REGISTERING, BERNARDO JARAMILLO ATTENDED THE FUNERAL OF A FELLOW PARTY MEMBER, VLADIMIR ESCOBAR, A SOACHA MUNICIPAL OFFICIAL WHO WAS SHOT BETWEEN THE EYES AND KILLED THIS WEEK."}, {"text": "THE SOACHA MUNICIPALITY IS CLOSE TO BOGOTA."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0082", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": {"sentences": [{"text": "CONCERNING THE PROSPECTS FOR THE DIALOGUE - NEGOTIATION BASED ON THE MEDIATION OF UN SECRETARY GENERAL JAVIER PEREZ DE CUELLAR AND THE DEBATE IN THE U.S. CONGRESS ON THE AID TO EL SALVADOR, THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN) REPORTS: 1. WE HAVE VIEWED WITH GREAT CONCERN THE GOVERNMENT AND ARMY'S REJECTION MR PEREZ DE CUELLAR'S PARTICIPATION IN THE DIALOGUE - NEGOTIATION PROCESS AS A MEDIATOR."}, {"text": "THIS ATTITUDE IS AN OBSTACLE TO A PROCESS THAT COULD FACILITATE THE NEGOTIATION EFFORT."}, {"text": "ON OUR PART, WE HAVE ACCEPTED THIS MEDIATION AND WE HAVE UNDERTAKEN EFFORTS TO ACHIEVE IT."}, {"text": "2. THE STATE OF SIEGE, THE ASSASSINATION OF SOCIAL DEMOCRATIC LEADER HECTOR OQUELI, THE DOUBTFUL AND INSUFFICIENT INITIAL RESULTS IN THE CASE OF THE JESUIT PRIESTS, THE ABSENCE OF CONDITIONS FOR THE POLITICAL ACTIVITY OF THE OPPOSITION, THE CONTINUATION OF THE PERSECUTION OF CHURCHES, AND THE LACK OF FREEDOM OF SPEECH THROUGH THE DIRECT OR COVERT GAGGING OF THE PRESS SHOW THAT CRISTIANI'S GOVERNMENT IS CARRYING OUT A POLICY OF CONFRONTATION WITH ALL THE COUNTRY'S SOCIAL AND POLITICAL FORCES."}, {"text": "FOR THIS REASON, THE TERMS OF THE DIALOGUE - NEGOTIATION MUST BE REORIENTED SO THAT IT WILL BE TURNED INTO A NATIONAL PROCESS WITH THE PARTICIPATION OF ALL THOSE FORCES."}, {"text": "3. WE VIEW AS GRAVELY ERRONEOUS THE PERSISTENCE OF A GOVERNMENT POLICY BASED ON THE IDEA OF THE FMLN'S ALLEGED MILITARY WEAKNESS."}, {"text": "THIS POSITION, SIMILAR TO THE ONE THAT WAS PUT FORTH PRIOR TO 11 NOVEMBER (DATE OF THE BEGINNING OF THE FMLN MILITARY OFFENSIVE) WILL ONLY LEAD THE COUNTRY TO GREATER LEVELS OF CONFRONTATION."}, {"text": "4. WE REAFFIRM OUR WILLINGNESS TO HOLD THE MEETING OF BOTH SIDES WITH THE UN SECRETARY GENERAL SOON."}, {"text": "WE HOPE THAT MR CRISTIANI'S VISIT TO THE UNITED NATIONS WILL LEAD TO SUCH A MEETING AND THAT WE CAN AGREE WITH THE MEDIATOR ON THE DATE TO HOLD IT."}, {"text": "5. WE BELIEVE THAT THE U.S. AID TO THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT IS DIRECTED AGAINST DEMOCRATIZATION AND A POLITICAL SOLUTION."}, {"text": "THE SENDING OF SIGNALS TO ONE OR ANOTHER SECTOR OF THE GOVERNMENT OR ARMY, USING THE PRESSURE OF SETTING CONDITIONS OR THREATENING THE END OF AID, DOES NOT RESOLVE THE PROBLEM."}, {"text": "WE BELIEVE THE MEMBERS OF THE U.S. CONGRESS CAN MAKE AN IMPORTANT CONTRIBUTION TO END THE WAR IN OUR COUNTRY BY AGREEING TO SUSPEND THAT AID, SOMETHING WHICH COULD FORM PART OF A NEGOTIATED AGREEMENT THAT WOULD SIMULTANEOUSLY ENTAIL A CEASE-FIRE."}, {"text": "(SIGNED) FMLN GENERAL COMMAND COMMANDERS SALVADOR SANCHEZ CEREN, SHAFIK JORGE HANDAL, FRANCISCO JOVEL, EDUARDO SANCHO, JOAQUIN VILLALOBOS 30 JANUARY 1990"}], "template": {"message_id": {"sentences": [{"text": "SMARTLY DRESSED AND SPEAKING IN NEARLY PERFECT ENGLISH, SALVADORAN PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI HAS AGAIN VISITED THE UNITED STATES, WHERE HE TRIED TO APPEAR AT THE CONGRESS AND THE UNITED NATIONS AS A STATESMAN AWARE OF HIS RIGHTS."}, {"text": "THIS IS, HOWEVER, A CRITICAL MOMENT FOR THE SALVADORAN PRESIDENT, AND HE KNOWS IT."}, {"text": "BUT THIS POINT WAS ALSO STRESSED BY THE LARGE NUMBERS OF PEOPLE WHO BOOED HIM AT NEARLY EVERY LARGE U.S. CITY HE VISITED."}, {"text": "ALTHOUGH THE GHOSTS OF THE ASSASSINATED JESUITS SHADOWED HIM ALL DURING HIS TOUR, THE ARENA (NATIONALIST REPUBLICAN ALLIANCE) REPRESENTATIVE, JUST AS HIS PREDECESSOR JOSE NAPOLEON DUARTE DID, FLEW TO THE UNITED STATES TO TRY TO CONVINCE THE LEGISLATORS, PARTICULARLY THE DEMOCRATS, THAT HE INTENDS TO RESUME THE DIALOGUE FOR PEACE AND CHECK THE ARMY'S CRIMINAL ASPIRATIONS."}, {"text": "WAVING THE HUMAN RIGHTS FLAG HAS BEEN THE MOST IMPORTANT THING FOR CRISTIANI, PARTICULARLY BECAUSE HE IS AWARE THAT WITH THIS ACTION HE CAN CONTINUE TO RECEIVE WASHINGTON'S FINANCIAL SUPPORT FOR HIS GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO TO SOME EXPERTS, CRISTIANI WENT FARTHER THAN HIS PREDECESSOR."}, {"text": "HE ASKED THE UN SECRETARY GENERAL TO HELP IN THE RESUMPTION OF TALKS WITH THE GUERRILLAS, REPLACED SEVERAL MILITARY OFFICERS OF DOUBTFUL REPUTATION, AND ASSURED HE WILL PUNISH SEVERELY EIGHT SOLDIERS ACCUSED OF ASSASSINATING THE SIX JESUIT PRIESTS."}, {"text": "WE MUST KEEP IN MIND THAT, PRIOR TO HIS TRIP, THE SALVADORAN PRESIDENT SUCCEEDED IN CURBING A COUP ATTEMPT STAGED BY ARMY REACTIONARY GROUPS."}, {"text": "MEMBERS OF THE SALVADORAN OPPOSITION HAVE COINCIDED IN THER VIEW THAT NEVER BEFORE HAD A HEAD OF STATE CHALLENGED THE MILITARY HIERARCHY TO SUCH AN EXTENT, A HIERARCHY THAT OPPOSES ALL NEGOTIATION WITH THE GUERRILLAS."}, {"text": "THE EXPERTS ALSO SAID, HOWEVER, THAT THE COUNTRY'S INTERNAL SITUATION HAS NEVER BEEN SO SERIOUS."}, {"text": "THE REBEL OFFENSIVE LAUNCHED IN NOVEMBER IS A LANDMARK, AFTER WHICH EVERYTHING WILL BE DIFFERENT IN EL SALVADOR, BEGINNING WITH THE GOVERNMENT PARTY, WHICH WAS LEFT IN A VERY DELICATE SITUATION IN THE EYES OF INFLUENTIAL U.S. POWER CIRCLES."}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLA DRIVE ALSO DEMONSTRATED THAT ONLY TWO ALTERNATIVES ARE LEFT FOR THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "IF SERIOUS PEACE NEGOTIATIONS ARE NOT INITIATED, THE COUNTERINSURGENCY POLICY WILL BE AGGRAVATED."}, {"text": "THIS COULD EVEN GIVE THE UNITED STATES A PRETEXT TO INTERVENE DIRECTLY IN THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "ALTHOUGH PRESIDENT GEORGE BUSH SAID HE WOULD CONTINUE TO AID EL SALVADOR, A LARGE NUMBER OF LEGISLATORS FOR A LONG TIME HAVE BEEN QUESTIONING WHAT USE HAS BEEN NEARLY $4 BILLION DELIVERED TO THE SALVADORAN ARMY IN 10 YEARS OF WAR."}, {"text": "IF FOR THE WHITE HOUSE THE ALTERNATIVE IS TO CONTINUE TO GIVE MILITARY AID TO EL SALVADOR OR RESIGN ITSELF TO AN EVENTUAL VICTORY OF THE REBELS, FOR CRISTIANI THE SITUATION IS EVEN MORE DIFFICULT BECAUSE, TO GET MORE MONEY, HE MUST ENSURE THAT HUMAN RIGHTS ARE RESPECTED."}, {"text": "THIS IS EQUIVALENT TO INFLUENCING THE MOST REACTIONARY MILITARY OFFICERS AND GUARANTEEING THE FULFILLMENT OF THE FAMOUS ECONOMIC RECOVERY PLAN ADVOCATED BY HIS PARTY."}, {"text": "THESE POINTS ARE NEARLY IMPOSSIBLE TO COMPLY WITH IN A COUNTRY IMMERSED IN WAR."}, {"text": "IF THE ECONOMY IS WEAK, RESPECT FOR HUMAN RIGHTS IS EVEN WEAKER."}, {"text": "ANYWAY, THE U.S. GOVERNMENT IS PLANNING TO INCREASE AID FOR THE SALVADORAN GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "THIS CONTRIBUTES TO PUTTING FAR INTO THE DISTANCE ANY PLANS TO END THE WAR."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0085", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 10 FEB 90"]}], {"sentences": [{"text": "CALM APPEARS TO BE RETURNING TO THE COUNTRY FOLLOWING THE DEATH OF ONE NONCOMMISSIONED OFFICER AND SIX SOLDIERS ON 23 FEBRUARY AS A RESULT OF GUERRILLA ATTACKS IN FIVE ANTIOQUIA DEPARTMENT MUNICIPALITIES, THE KIDNAPPING OF A MAYOR, A GOVERNMENT OFFICIAL, AND A CANDIDATE IN CAUCA DEPARTMENT, AND THE DEATH OF A GUERRILLA IN GUAVIARE."}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLA ACTIONS BEGAN ON THE EVENING OF 22 FEBRUARY WHEN A LARGE COLUMN OF THE POPULAR LIBERATION ARMY (ELN) ENTERED TURBO MUNICIPALITY, NORTHEAST OF ANTIOQUIA DEPARTMENT, AND SABOTAGED THE POWER SYSTEM LEAVING THE ENTIRE AREA WITHOUT ELECTRICITY."}, {"text": "NATIONAL ARMY SPOKESMEN SAID THAT ONE NONCOMMISSIONED OFFICER AND SIX SOLDIERS WERE KILLED, FOUR WERE WOUNDED, AND 15 OTHERS WERE KIDNAPPED DURING THE ATTACKS AGAINST MILITARY BASES AND POLICE INSTALLATIONS IN SEGOVIA BY THE 4TH FRONT OF THE FARC (REVOLUTIONARY ARMED FORCES OF COLOMBIA)."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE IN BOGOTA, MILITARY FORCES COMMANDER NELSON MEJIA HENAO DENIED THAT COLOMBIA IS IN GUERRILLA HANDS AND REAFFIRMED THE TROOPS' UNYIELDING DETERMINATION TO DEFEND NATIONAL ORDER AND DEMOCRACY."}, {"text": "THE HIGHEST-RANKING OFFICER, WHO EXPRESSED REGRET OVER THE DEATHS OF THE SOLDIERS IN SEGOVIA, ANTIOQUIA DEPARTMENT, SAID THAT THIS TYPE OF INCIDENT IS NORMAL WITHIN THE FRAMEWORK OF THE WAR THAT THE GOVERNMENT IS WAGING AGAINST ARMED SUBVERSION."}, {"text": "LAST NIGHT, PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO VARGAS, AFTER THE CLOSING CEREMONY OF THE 25TH AGRARIAN CONGRESS OF THE (FAC) (EXPANSION UNKNOWN), SAID THAT THE GUERRILLAS ARE DESPERATE AND THIS IS REFLECTED IN THEIR ACTIONS."}, {"text": "NEVERTHELESS, THE ARMED FORCES WILL CONTINUE TO FIGHT SUBVERSION ANYWHERE IN THE COUNTRY, HE ADDED."}, {"text": "THE PRESIDENT EXPRESSED HIS SATISFACTION AT THE RELEASE OF SANTANDER DEPARTMENT SENATOR JORGE SERRANO GONZALEZ, WHOM HE DESCRIBED AS ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT PEOPLE THAT COLOMBIAN DEMOCRACY HAS AT THIS MOMENT."}, {"text": "HE ADDED FINALLY: I HOPE THAT IS HE ALREADY AT HOME WITH HIS FAMILY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0088", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["22 {"sentences": [{"text": "GENERAL GUSTAVO LEIGH GUZMAN, A FORMER MILITARY REGIME GOVERNMENT JUNTA MEMBER AND FORMER COMMANDER IN CHIEF OF THE AIR FORCE, AND AIR FORCE GENERAL ENRIQUE RUIZ, RETIRED, A PARTNER IN LEIGH'S REAL ESTATE OFFICE, WERE SERIOUSLY INJURED DURING AN ATTACK THIS MORNING."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO WITNESSES' REPORTS, TWO 23 TO 25-YEAR-OLD INDIVIDUALS WALKED TO GEN. LEIGH'S OFFICE, ON THE FOURTH FLOOR OF THE BUILDING LOCATED AT 95 LUIS TALLE OJEDA STREET."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED) WITNESSES SAID THEY HEARD TWO BURSTS OF GUNFIRE: ONE BURST OF THREE SHOTS LASTING THREE SECONDS AND ANOTHER BURST OF SEVEN TO EIGHT SHOTS LASTING LONGER."}, {"text": "GEN. LEIGH'S SECRETARY, JOANNA SANTIS RETAMAL, CAME TO A WINDOW TO REPORT THE INCIDENT."}, {"text": "OTHER REPORTS SAID THAT THE TWO INDIVIDUALS BROKE INTO THE OFFICES AND ENTERED GEN. LEIGH'S PRIVATE OFFICE."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED)"}, {"text": "THE INDIVIDUALS USED 9 MM SEMIAUTOMATIC PISTOLS."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO THE EXPERTS, GEN. RUIZ WAS HIT THREE TIMES AND GEN GUSTAVO LEIGH WAS HIT FIVE TIMES."}, {"text": "THE BULLETS HIT GEN. LEIGH IN HIS EYE, NOSE, RIGHT ARM, RIGHT LEG, AND STOMACH."}, {"text": "THE TWO ATTACKERS THEN WALKED DOWN THE STAIRS AND ESCAPED TOWARD PROVIDENCIA."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED)"}, {"text": "THE GOVERNMENT HAS EXPRESSED ITS STRONG CONDEMNATION OF THE ATTACK ON GEN. GUSTAVO LEIGH, THE FORMER COMMANDER IN CHIEF OF THE AIR FORCE AND MEMBER OF THE MILITARY REGIME'S GOVERNMENT JUNTA."}, {"text": "ON HIS WAY TO THE HOSPITAL ON EXPRESS ORDERS OF THE PRESIDENT, INTERIOR MINISTER ENRIQUE KRAUSS REJECTED THE ATTACK: (BEGIN RECORDING) (KRAUSS) WE HAVE ASKED THE POLICE AUTHORITIES TO FULLY CLARIFY THIS INCIDENT."}, {"text": "THESE ATTITUDES AND ACTS DO NOT HELP IN THE EFFORT REQUIRED TO REUNITE ALL CHILEANS."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) KRAUSS SAID IT WAS A REGRETTABLE INCIDENT BECAUSE IT HURT THE SPIRIT AND PURPOSE OF THE GOVERNMENT AND OPPOSITION'S WORK."}, {"text": "THE ATTACK AGAINST LEIGH WOULD MAKE A GOOD PATHOLOGICAL STUDY, THE MINISTER ADDED."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED) THE NATIONAL COORDINATING BOARD FOR POLITICAL PRISONERS HAS SAID THE ATTACK ON GUSTAVO LEIGH DOES NOT REFLECT THE CURRENT SITUATION IN THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "COMMUNIST PARTY LEADER JORGE MARTINEZ, MOVEMENT OF THE REVOLUTIONARY LEFT (MIR) LEADER CARLOS RUIG, AND MANUEL RODRIGUEZ PATRIOTIC FRONT (FPMR) LEADER FRANCISCO ESCOBAR HEARD THE NEWS WHILE HOLDING A NEWS CONFERENCE AT THE PRISON HOUSE."}, {"text": "THE FPMR'S FRANCISCO ESCOBAR SAID HE IS SURE HIS ORGANIZATION WAS NOT INVOLVED IN THE INCIDENT BECAUSE, AS HE SAID, WE ARE NOT GOING TO ACHIEVE ANYTHING WITH IT."}, {"text": "(PASSAGE OMITTED)"}, {"text": "MIR REPRESENTATIVE CARLOS RUIG SAID THAT THE MIR WOULD NOT CARRY OUT ANY ARMED ACTION AT THIS TIME, IRRESPECTIVE OF THE LEVEL OF GEN. LEIGH'S INVOLVEMENT IN PAST REPRESSIONS."}, {"text": "COMMUNIST LEADER JORGE MARTINEZ SAID THAT HE IS COMMITTED TO RESPECTING THE DEMOCRATIC TRANSITION."}, {"text": "HE SAID THAT HE DOES NOT BELIEVE THAT THIS TYPE OF ACTION WILL CONTRIBUTE TO THE COUNTRY'S PROGRESS AND STABILITY."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0091", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", {"sentences": [{"text": "GOOD EVENING, A COMMUNIQUE HAS JUST BEEN ISSUED AT THE NATIONAL CAPITOL."}, {"text": "THE COMMUNIQUE HAS BEEN SIGNED BY ALL THE DEMOCRATIC FORCES OF THE COUNTRY, WITH THE EXCEPTION OF THE LIBERAL PARTY."}, {"text": "THE COMMUNIQUE ASKS THE GOVERNMENT TO OFFER FULL GUARANTEES DURING THE ELECTIONS PROCESS AND TO POSTPONE THE ELECTIONS."}, {"text": "THE FOLLOWING IS THE COMMUNIQUE THAT HAS BEEN ISSUED IN THE ELIPTICO ROOM OF THE NATIONAL CAPITOL: (BEGIN RECORDING) (UNIDENTIFIED SPEAKER) WE REPORT TO THE COLOMBIAN PEOPLE AND THE PEOPLE OF THE WORLD THE FOLLOWING: 1. WE ONCE AGAIN CONDEMN THE VILE MURDER OF PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE DR. BERNARDO JARAMILLO."}, {"text": "THIS MURDER HAS MADE EVIDENT THE LACK OF GUARANTEES IN THE COUNTRY, GUARANTEES THAT THE GOVERNMENT HAS SYSTEMATICALLY DENIED THE OPPOSITION PARTIES."}, {"text": "WE REJECT THE MANIPULATIONS IN WHICH OFFICIAL ORGANIZATIONS ARE ENGAGED IN CONNECTION WITH INVESTIGATING THIS CRIME."}, {"text": "2. WE DENOUNCE THAT THE OFFICIAL APPARATUS IS AT THE SERVICE OF ONLY ONE CANDIDATE AND THAT IT IS PREPARED TO ESTABLISH PARTY PREDOMINANCE THAT WOULD IN PRACTICE BE A REJECTION OF DEMOCRATIC PLURALISM."}, {"text": "3. WE DEMAND FULL GUARANTEES FOR ALL THE FORCES PARTICIPATING IN THE ELECTIONS AND EQUITABLE ACCESS TO THE STATE MEDIA SO THAT THESE FORCES CAN MAKE KNOWN THEIR POLITICAL POSITIONS."}, {"text": "4. WE REQUEST GUARANTEES THAT THE NEW ELECTORAL SYSTEM WILL NOT HAVE THE SAME DIFFICULTIES THAT EXISTED DURING THE 11 MARCH ELECTIONS, THE RESULTS OF WHICH ARE STILL UNKNOWN."}, {"text": "5. UNDER THE CURRENT CONDITIONS, WE ASK OUR REPRESENTATIVES IN THE NATIONAL ELECTORAL COUNCIL TO ABSTAIN FROM PARTICIPATING IN DISCUSSIONS AND DECISIONS OF THAT COUNCIL."}, {"text": "6. IN VIEW OF THESE CIRCUMSTANCES, WE HAVE AGREED TO TEMPORARILY SUSPEND OUR ELECTION CAMPAIGNS AND DEMAND A POSTPONEMENT OF THE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTIONS SCHEDULED FOR 27 MAY."}, {"text": "7. WE INSIST THAT THE RATIFICATION OF CARLOS LEMOS SIMMONDS IN THE GOVERNMENT MINISTRY REPRESENTS THE BIGGEST OBSTACLE TO THE DEMOCRATIC OPPOSITION TO FINDING AN INSTITUTIONAL INTERLOCUTOR IN NATIONAL GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "8. WE ANNOUNCE THE IMMEDIATE PRESENCE OF INTERNATIONAL (WORDS INDISTINCT) TO VERIFY THAT THE ELECTORAL GUARANTEES WE ARE DEMANDING ARE GRANTED AND TO OBSERVE THE ELECTIONS PROCESS."}, {"text": "9. THE PERMANENT COMMITTEE OF THE OPPOSITION HEREBY STATES ITS DECISION TO WORK FOR THE FORMATION OF A CONSTITUENT NATIONAL ASSEMBLY THAT MUST HAVE A DEMOCRATIC AND PLURALISTIC COMPOSITION WITH THE DECIDING PARTICIPATION OF THE NATIONAL (WORD INDISTINCT) TO APPROVE A NEW CONSTITUTION AND TO CONTRIBUTE TOWARD FINDING POLITICAL SOLUTIONS TO THE SOCIAL CONFLICT OF COLOMBIA."}, {"text": "WE APPEAL TO THE LEADERS OF THE COUNTRY TO URGE THE NATIONAL GOVERNMENT TO DEFEND AND RESPECT HUMAN RIGHTS."}, {"text": "10."}, {"text": "WE REITERATE OUR POSITION THAT THE ONLY WAY OUT OF THE ARMED CONFLICT IN THE COUNTRY IS A NEGOTIATED POLITICAL SOLUTION."}, {"text": "11."}, {"text": "WE URGE THE LIBERAL PARTY TO POSTPONE ITS NATIONAL CONVENTION IN SOLIDARITY WITH THE PATRIOTIC UNION AND THE COLOMBIAN PEOPLE."}, {"text": "12."}, {"text": "WE ACKNOWLEDGE THE CATHOLIC CHURCH'S CALL AND WE WILL PROMOTE THIS CALL THROUGH THIS COMMITTEE."}, {"text": "13."}, {"text": "IN DEFENSE OF A PLURALISTIC DEMOCRACY WE WILL MAINTAIN THE PERMANENT COMMITTEE OF THE OPPOSITION WE HAVE CREATED."}, {"text": "WE HEREBY ASK OUR FOLLOWERS AND ALL OUR COUNTRYMEN TO REMAIN ON A STATE OF ALERT."}, {"text": "THIS COMMITTEE WILL HOLD A NEW MEETING TUESDAY 27 MARCH, AT 1500, IN THE CHAMBER OF REPRESENTATIVES."}, {"text": "WE URGE ALL POLITICAL AND SOCIAL FORCES INTERESTED IN THESE OBJECTIVES TO ACTIVELY PARTICIPATE IN THIS MEETING."}, {"text": "RESOLUTION; DEMOCRATIC SOCIALISM, THE POPULAR MOVEMENT (WORDS INDISTINCT), THE BROAD FRONT (WORDS INDISTINCT), THE NATIONALIST ACTION FOR PEACE, AND THE 19 APRIL MOVEMENT (M-19) WANT TO LEAVE ON RECORD THE FOLLOWING: THE NEGOTIATION PROCESS BETWEEN THE NATIONAL GOVERNMENT AND M-19 THAT BEGAN ON 10 JANUARY 1989 AND THAT PRODUCED ON 9 MARCH 1990 A PEACE AGREEMENT WILL BE AFFECTED BY THE MURDER OF BERNARDO JARAMILLO, BUT WILL NOT RESULT IN AN END TO THE SEARCH FOR PEACE BY THE TWO PARTIES."}, {"text": "WE WILL CONTINUE TO WORK FOR A POLITICAL SOLUTION TO THE ARMED CONFLICT IN COLOMBIA."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING)"}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0093", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 23 {"sentences": [{"text": "FMLN-FDR (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT-REVOLUTIONARY DEMOCRATIC FRONT) TERRORIST GROUPS HAVE CONTINUED THEIR TREACHEROUS ATTACKS AGAINST CIVILIANS AND POLICE OFFICERS IN THE CAPITAL AND THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRYSIDE, OPENLY IGNORING THE AGREEMENTS REACHED BY THEIR LEADERS WITH A GOVERNMENT DELEGATION IN GENEVA, SWITZERLAND."}, {"text": "THE ARMED FORCES TELECOMMUNICATIONS INSTRUCTION CENTER (CITFA) REPORTED THAT A MAN AND A WOMAN WERE CRITICALLY WOUNDED WHEN THE VEHICLE IN WHICH THEY WERE TRAVELLING NEAR OLOCUILTA, LA PAZ DEPARTMENT, WAS MACHINEGUNNED BY FMLN TERRORISTS ON THE EVENING OF 4 APRIL."}, {"text": "THE WOUNDED ARE MAURICIO CAMPOS AND CONCEPCION HERRERA, WHO WERE TAKEN TO A HEALTH CENTER BY THE RED CROSS, THE SOURCES ADDED."}, {"text": "THE NATIONAL POLICE REPORTED THAT TWO OF ITS AGENTS AND A CIVILIAN WERE FIRED AT BY TERRORISTS AT 1800 ON 4 APRIL, AS THEY INSPECTED A CAR CRASH BETWEEN THE HIGHWAY TO COMALAPA AIRPORT AND 49TH SOUTH AVENUE IN THE MONTSERRAT NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": ""THE POLICEMEN WERE MACHINEGUNNED DOWN BY PEOPLE IN A MOVING VEHICLE AND SUSTAINED WOUNDS WHICH HAVE LEFT THEM IN EXTREMELY CRITICAL CONDITION," A SECURITY CORPS SPOKESMAN SAID."}, {"text": "THE TWO AGENTS WERE ASSISTED BY PEOPLE WHO REPUDIATED THE ATTACK."}, {"text": "A PEDESTRIAN, LATER IDENTIFIED AS MANUEL ALVARO MENDOZA, WAS ALSO STRUCK BY THE BULLET AND HE IS AT ROSALES HOSPITAL."}, {"text": "A MILITARY SPOKESMAN ALSO REPORTED THAT A GROUP OF PERSONS WHO IDENTIFIED THEMSELVES AS FMLN-FDR MEMBERS KIDNAPPED A PEASANT, JOSE MANUEL POSADA, NEAR LA COLMENA, IN EL CARMEN DISTRICT, CUSCATLAN DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, 9-YEAR-OLD YOHALMO ANTONIO ORTIZ WAS INJURED BY SHRAPNEL WHEN TERRORISTS THREW A BOMB AT CIVIL DEFENSE MEMBERS IN NEJAPA, NORTH OF SAN SALVADOR, WHILE HARASSING THE PARAMILITARY GROUP'S OUTPOST."}, {"text": "THE BOY IS AT BLOOM HOSPITAL."}, {"text": "IN THE DOCUMENT SIGNED BY THE GOVERNMENT DELEGATION AND THE FMLN-FDR LEADERS, THE LATTER PLEDGED NOT TO ENGAGE IN TERRORISTS ATTACKS THAT MIGHT DAMAGE ASSETS OR INJURE PERSONS, BUT "URBAN COMMANDOS" OR "TERRORISTS SQUADS" THAT OPERATE IN SAN SALVADOR HAVE EITHER NOT BEEN INFORMED OF THIS RESOLUTION OR THEY ACT INDEPENDENTLY, THE MILITARY SOURCES SAID."}, {"text": "REFERRING TO THE 2 APRIL CAR BOMB EXPLOSION PERPETRATED IN SANTA TECLA, THE FMLN-FDR CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE ATTACK IN A COMMUNIQUE, AND SAID THAT IT WAS "AN ACTION AIMED DIRECTLY AT THE POLICE" AND THAT "THEY REGRET THE DEATH OF A CIVILIAN," BUT THEY DID NOT MENTION COMPENSATION FOR THE RELATIVES."}, {"text": "ALSO, THE FMLN-FDR CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE ATTACK ON GENERAL RAFAEL HUMBERTO LARIOS'S SON-IN-LAW, ACCUSING HIM OF BEING A MILITARY PILOT -- WHEN IN FACT HE HAS BEEN A CIVILIAN PILOT AND HE WAS WORKING IN A SMALL AUTOMOBILE SPARE PARTS DISTRIBUTION COMPANY AT THE TIME OF THE ATTACK."}, {"text": "THE YOUNG MAN, OTTO MILLA, IS STILL IN A COMA AND HIS PANCREAS WAS REMOVED IN THE LATEST SURGICAL OPERATION."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0094", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": {"sentences": [{"text": "FMLN-FDR (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT-REVOLUTIONARY DEMOCRATIC FRONT) TERRORIST GROUPS HAVE CONTINUED THEIR TREACHEROUS ATTACKS AGAINST CIVILIANS AND POLICE OFFICERS IN THE CAPITAL AND THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRYSIDE, OPENLY IGNORING THE AGREEMENTS REACHED BY THEIR LEADERS WITH A GOVERNMENT DELEGATION IN GENEVA, SWITZERLAND."}, {"text": "THE ARMED FORCES TELECOMMUNICATIONS INSTRUCTION CENTER (CITFA) REPORTED THAT A MAN AND A WOMAN WERE CRITICALLY WOUNDED WHEN THE VEHICLE IN WHICH THEY WERE TRAVELLING NEAR OLOCUILTA, LA PAZ DEPARTMENT, WAS MACHINEGUNNED BY FMLN TERRORISTS ON THE EVENING OF 4 APRIL."}, {"text": "THE WOUNDED ARE MAURICIO CAMPOS AND CONCEPCION HERRERA, WHO WERE TAKEN TO A HEALTH CENTER BY THE RED CROSS, THE SOURCES ADDED."}, {"text": "THE NATIONAL POLICE REPORTED THAT TWO OF ITS AGENTS AND A CIVILIAN WERE FIRED AT BY TERRORISTS AT 1800 ON 4 APRIL, AS THEY INSPECTED A CAR CRASH BETWEEN THE HIGHWAY TO COMALAPA AIRPORT AND 49TH SOUTH AVENUE IN THE MONTSERRAT NEIGHBORHOOD."}, {"text": ""THE POLICEMEN WERE MACHINEGUNNED DOWN BY PEOPLE IN A MOVING VEHICLE AND SUSTAINED WOUNDS WHICH HAVE LEFT THEM IN EXTREMELY CRITICAL CONDITION," A SECURITY CORPS SPOKESMAN SAID."}, {"text": "THE TWO AGENTS WERE ASSISTED BY PEOPLE WHO REPUDIATED THE ATTACK."}, {"text": "A PEDESTRIAN, LATER IDENTIFIED AS MANUEL ALVARO MENDOZA, WAS ALSO STRUCK BY THE BULLET AND HE IS AT ROSALES HOSPITAL."}, {"text": "A MILITARY SPOKESMAN ALSO REPORTED THAT A GROUP OF PERSONS WHO IDENTIFIED THEMSELVES AS FMLN-FDR MEMBERS KIDNAPPED A PEASANT, JOSE MANUEL POSADA, NEAR LA COLMENA, IN EL CARMEN DISTRICT, CUSCATLAN DEPARTMENT."}, {"text": "MEANWHILE, 9-YEAR-OLD YOHALMO ANTONIO ORTIZ WAS INJURED BY SHRAPNEL WHEN TERRORISTS THREW A BOMB AT CIVIL DEFENSE MEMBERS IN NEJAPA, NORTH OF SAN SALVADOR, WHILE HARASSING THE PARAMILITARY GROUP'S OUTPOST."}, {"text": "THE BOY IS AT BLOOM HOSPITAL."}, {"text": "IN THE DOCUMENT SIGNED BY THE GOVERNMENT DELEGATION AND THE FMLN-FDR LEADERS, THE LATTER PLEDGED NOT TO ENGAGE IN TERRORISTS ATTACKS THAT MIGHT DAMAGE ASSETS OR INJURE PERSONS, BUT "URBAN COMMANDOS" OR "TERRORISTS SQUADS" THAT OPERATE IN SAN SALVADOR HAVE EITHER NOT BEEN INFORMED OF THIS RESOLUTION OR THEY ACT INDEPENDENTLY, THE MILITARY SOURCES SAID."}, {"text": "REFERRING TO THE 2 APRIL CAR BOMB EXPLOSION PERPETRATED IN SANTA TECLA, THE FMLN-FDR CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE ATTACK IN A COMMUNIQUE, AND SAID THAT IT WAS "AN ACTION AIMED DIRECTLY AT THE POLICE" AND THAT "THEY REGRET THE DEATH OF A CIVILIAN," BUT THEY DID NOT MENTION COMPENSATION FOR THE RELATIVES."}, {"text": "ALSO, THE FMLN-FDR CLAIMED RESPONSIBILITY FOR THE ATTACK ON GENERAL RAFAEL HUMBERTO LARIOS'S SON-IN-LAW, ACCUSING HIM OF BEING A MILITARY PILOT -- WHEN IN FACT HE HAS BEEN A CIVILIAN PILOT AND HE WAS WORKING IN A SMALL AUTOMOBILE SPARE PARTS DISTRIBUTION COMPANY AT THE TIME OF THE ATTACK."}, {"text": "THE YOUNG MAN, OTTO MILLA, IS STILL IN A COMA AND HIS PANCREAS WAS REMOVED IN THE LATEST SURGICAL OPERATION."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0094", "message_template": 5, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": {"sentences": [{"text": "GOOD AFTERNOON, WE HAVE JUST RECEIVED A STATEMENT ISSUED BY PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO VARGAS CONCERNING THE MURDER OF MR. CARLOS PIZARRO LEONGOMEZ."}, {"text": "THE MESSAGE READS AS FOLLOWS: CARLOS PIZARRO'S MURDER IS A MONSTROUS CRIME THAT HAS CUT SHORT THE LIFE OF A MAN WHO HAD SHOWN HIS WILL FOR PEACE AND HIS COMMITMENT TO COLOMBIA."}, {"text": "THE CRIME WAS DIRECTED AT HINDERING THE DEVELOPMENT OF THE ELECTORAL PROCESS AND DESTROYING THE RECONCILIATION PROCESS THAT THE GOVERNMENT AND M-19 (19 APRIL MOVEMENT) CAREFULLY CONSTRUCTED, SURPASSING MANY OBSTACLES."}, {"text": "IN THIS CASE, AS IN MANY OTHERS, THIS PAINFUL TRAGEDY SHOULD SERVE TO CONSOLIDATE THE IDEALS OF PEACE AND PLURALISM FOR WHICH SO MANY COLOMBIANS HAVE STRUGGLED -- ONE OF THEM, CARLOS PIZARRO."}, {"text": "IT SHOULD SERVE TO REASSERT OUR REPUDIATION OF VIOLENCE AND OUR FAITH IN DEMOCRATIC PROCEDURES."}, {"text": "FURTHER ON THE PRESIDENT'S MESSAGE NOTES: PIZARRO'S RELATIVES AND HIS FOLLOWERS KNOW THAT THE GOVERNMENT, AND I PERSONALLY, FEEL STRONG WRATH AND SADNESS, BUT WE WILL NOT BE DISCOURAGED."}, {"text": "WE WILL UPHOLD THE BANNERS OF RECONCILIATION, PLURALISM, AND THE RIGHT TO FREELY AND PEACEFULLY EXPRESS ANY IDEA."}, {"text": "WE WILL ALSO CONTINUE TO UNMASK AND COMBAT ENEMIES OF PEACE."}, {"text": "THE PRESIDENT ADDS IN HIS MESSAGE: I INTERPRET THE DESIRE OF ALL COLOMBIANS WHO ADMIRED CARLOS PIZARRO'S DEMOCRATIC VOCATION, BY WARNING THOSE WHO ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR THIS TRAGIC MURDER THAT THEY WILL NOT MANAGE TO DESTROY WHAT HAS BEEN WORKED FOR SO HARD AND WITH THE SUPPORT OF POLITICAL FORCES AND THE PEOPLE WHO VOTED FOR PEACE ON 11 MARCH TO OPEN A ROAD FOR PEACE THAT IS CLEAR, POSSIBLE, AND DEFINED."}, {"text": "THE PRESIDENT'S MESSAGE CONTINUES: YOU KNOW THAT DURING THIS PEACE PROCESS, MANY ENEMIES AND DIFFICULTIES WERE SURPASSED, BUT NONE HAS BEEN SO LARGE AS THIS TRAGEDY THAT HAS SHAKEN ALL COLOMBIANS."}, {"text": "THE OBLIGATION THAT LIES BEFORE US IS TO KEEP OPEN THE ROAD TO PEACE THAT THE MURDERERS OF CARLOS PIZARRO WANT TO DESTROY."}, {"text": "ARTICLE 95 OF THE ELECTORAL CODE INDICATES THAT WHEN A PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE DIES, ANOTHER PERSON IN HIS OWN MOVEMENT HAS THE RIGHT TO TAKE HIS PLACE."}, {"text": "IN COMPLIANCE WITH THIS NORM, THE GOVERNMENT WILL OFFER EVERY FACILITY FOR THE REGISTRY OF A NEW M-19 PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE, SO THAT HE CAN CONTINUE TO HOIST THE FLAGS OF PEACE AND PLURALISM AS IS PROPER FOR A DEMOCRATIC DEBATE."}, {"text": "THE PRESIDENT ALSO SAYS IN HIS MESSAGE: I HAVE ASKED THE GOVERNMENT MINISTER AND THE PEACE ADVISER TO MEET AS SOON AS POSSIBLE WITH M-19 REPRESENTATIVES SO THAT TOGETHER THEY MAY STUDY ALTERNATIVES TO CONFRONT SUCH A SERIOUS SITUATION."}, {"text": "AS SOON AS POSSIBLE, THE GOVERNMENT MINISTER WILL ALSO DIRECT CONTACTS WITH THE REST OF THE POLITICAL FORCES TO REQUEST THEIR OPINIONS ABOUT THE PRESENT SITUATION AND TO CONTINUE TO GIVE ALL THE NECESSARY GUARANTEES SO THAT THE ELECTORAL PROCESS MAY DEVELOP ACCORDING TO WHAT IS ESTABLISHED IN THE CONSTITUTION AND OUR LAWS."}, {"text": "THE MESSAGE ENDS: I INVITE ALL COLOMBIANS WHO ARE TIRED OF SO MUCH VIOLENCE TO COME TO THE POLLS IN THE NEXT ELECTIONS AND VOTE FOR PEACE AND PLURALISM."}, {"text": "I INVITE ALL POLITICAL AND SOCIAL FORCES TO JOIN IN SOLIDARITY WITH THE ELECTORAL PROCESS AND DEFEND THE INSTITUTIONS THAT ARE THREATENED BY VIOLENCE."}, {"text": "IT IS TIME FOR GOOD SENSE AND PRUDENCE."}, {"text": "IT IS TIME TO RISE TO THE OCCASION AND SHOW OUR COMMITMENT TO DEMOCRACY."}, {"text": "THIS IS THE TEXT OF PRESIDENT VIRGILIO BARCO'S MESSAGE ON THE MURDER MR. CARLOS PIZARRO LEONGOMEZ."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0096", "message_template": 1, "incident_date": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["- 26 APR 90"]}], "incident_location": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["COLOMBIA"], "document_mentions": [[314, 322], [676, 684], [1257, 1265], [1784, 1792], [2893, 2901]], "sentence_mentions": {"1": [[167, 175]], "3": [[134, 142]], "8": [[65, 73]], "9": [[185, 193]], "15": [[31, 39]]}}], "incident_type": "ATTACK", "incident_stage_of_execution": {"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["ACCOMPLISHED"]}, "incident_instrument_id": null, "perp_incident_category": null, "perp_individual_id": null, "perp_organization_id": null, "perp_organization_confidence": null, "phys_tgt_id": null, "phys_tgt_type": null, "phys_tgt_number": null, "phys_tgt_foreign_nation": null, "phys_tgt_effect_of_incident": null, "phys_tgt_total_number": null, "hum_tgt_name": [{"type": "simple_strings", "strings": ["CARLOS PIZARRO LEONGOMEZ"], "document_mentions": [[121, 145], [3352, 3376]], "sentence_mentions": {"0": [[121, 145]], "19": [[73, 97]]}}], "hum_tgt_description": [{"type": "colon_clause", "strings_lhs": ["PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE", "MR."], "strings_rhs": ["CARLOS PIZARRO LEONGOMEZ"]}], "hum_tgt_type": [{"type": "colon_clause", "strings_lhs": ["POLITICAL FIGURE"], "strings_rhs": ["CARLOS PIZARRO LEONGOMEZ"]}], "hum_tgt_number": [{"type": "colon_clause", "strings_lhs": ["1"], "strings_rhs": ["CARLOS PIZARRO LEONGOMEZ"]}], "hum_tgt_foreign_nation": null, "hum_tgt_effect_of_incident": [{"type": "colon_clause", "strings_lhs": ["DEATH"], "strings_rhs": ["CARLOS PIZARRO LEONGOMEZ"]}], "hum_tgt_total_number": null}, "hit_id": 202}

{"sentences": [{"text": "GUERRILLA GROUPS HAVE REPORTED 185 SALVADORAN ARMED FORCES CASUALTIES DURING CLASHES WHICH OCCURRED IN THE LAST FEW HOURS IN SIX OF THE COUNTRY'S 14 DEPARTMENTS, BUT THE ARMY CLAIMS THAT IT ONLY SUSTAINED 48 CASUALTIES IN THOSE CLASHES."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO RADIO FARABUNDO MARTI, A RADIO STATION OF THE GUERRILLA GROUP, THE CASUALTIES WERE SUSTAINED BY THE ARMED FORCES IN CLASHES WHICH OCCURRED ON 1 AND 2 MAY AND EARLY THIS MORNING WHEN SEVERAL AMBUSHES, ATTACKS, AND SABOTAGE AIMED AT THE ECONOMY WERE CARRIED OUT IN SEVERAL PLACES THROUGHOUT THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "RADIO FARABUNDO MARTI HAS REPORTED THAT THE MILITARY ACTIONS, THE LARGEST SINCE THE REBEL OFFENSIVE IN NOVEMBER 1989, WHICH RESULTED IN THOUSANDS OF CASUALTIES, IS PART OF THE "WITH THE WORKERS AND
