{"sentences": [{"text": "SALVADORAN PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI STATED TODAY THAT IT WOULD BE NO PROBLEM FOR THE FOURTH PENAL JUDGE, WHO IS IN CHARGE OF THE CASE OF THE JESUITS MURDERED BY A GROUP OF SOLDIERS, TO ORDER THAT CADETS WHO ARE TAKING COURSES ABROAD RETURN TO THE COUNTRY."}, {"text": "IT WAS RECENTLY REPORTED THAT SEVERAL OFFICERS WHO TESTIFIED DURING THESE INVESTIGATIONS ARE NOW ATTENDING TRAINING COURSES ABROAD."}, {"text": "IT WAS ALSO REPORTED THAT THE MILITARY SCHOOL'S REGISTRATION BOOK FOR PERSONS ENTERING OR LEAVING THE PREMISES HAD BEEN LOST, INCLUDING THE PAGES THAT CORRESPOND TO NOVEMBER 1989."}, {"text": "TODAY, CRISTIANI TALKED ABOUT THIS MATTER AND SAID THE JUDGE SHOULD CONTINUE TO INVESTIGATE AND NOT JUST MAKE STATEMENTS CONCERNING THE PROBLEMS."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (CRISTIANI)"}, {"text": "I DO NOT BELIEVE THERE IS ANY PROBLEM IN THE OFFICERS RETURNING TO THE COUNTRY IF A JUDGE ORDERS THAT THEY COME TO TESTIFY."}, {"text": "ALL THAT IS REQUIRED IS FOR THE JUDGE TO SUMMON THEM; THEY WOULD BE BROUGHT TO THE COUNTRY TO TESTIFY AND, AFTER THAT, RETURNED TO THEIR TRAINING COURSES."}, {"text": "GROUPS OF SOLDIERS ARE FREQUENTLY SENT ABROAD TO TAKE TRAINING COURSES TO MAKE THEM MORE PROFESSIONAL; THIS APPLIES NOT ONLY TO PERSONNEL FROM THE MILITARY SCHOOL, BUT FROM ALL ARMED FORCES UNITS."}, {"text": "CONCERNING THE OTHER MATTER, THE JUDGE HAS TO INVESTIGATE IT."}, {"text": "I BELIEVE THAT INSTEAD OF JUST STAYING THERE, THE JUDGE SHOULD CONTINUE TO SEARCH FOR EVIDENCE."}, {"text": "TELL ME, WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE IF THEY ARE BROUGHT BACK FROM SUCHITOTO OR FROM THE UNITED STATES IF THEY MUST TESTIFY BEFORE THE JUDGE?"}, {"text": "THERE IS NO DIFFERENCE AT ALL."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) THE PRESIDENT SPOKE TODAY AT THE EL SALVADOR MILITARY AIRPORT BEFORE HE LEFT FOR COSTA RICA TO ATTEND THE INAUGURATION CEREMONY OF PRESIDENT-ELECT RAFAEL CALDERON FOURNIER."}, {"text": "HE ALSO SAID THAT THE UNITED STATES CONDITIONING 50 PERCENT OF THE AID GIVEN TO OUR COUNTRY COULD CAUSE THE REBEL FRONT TO INCREASE THEIR ACTIONS."}, {"text": "HE ACCUSED THE FMLN (FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT) OF USING DIALOGUE FOR TACTICAL REASONS."}, {"text": "(BEGIN RECORDING) (CRISTIANI) WE HAVE STATED THAT AN ACTION OF THIS TYPE WOULD BE VERY UNTIMELY, AS IT COULD MAKE THE MOST RADICAL FMLN MEMBERS DECIDE TO CONTINUE THE WAR AND, THUS, HINDER THE DIALOGUE PROCESS."}, {"text": "(REPORTER)"}, {"text": "HOWEVER, (WORDS INDISTINCT) PRESSURE GOVERNMENT FOR THEM (WORDS INDISTINCT) WITH FMLN."}, {"text": "(CRISTIANI)"}, {"text": "I WOULD ASK THE QUESTION: WHO HAS ALWAYS SHOWED GOODWILL AND SINCERELY SOUGHT AN AGREEMENT AND WHO HAS NOT DONE THIS?"}, {"text": "HISTORY SHOWS THAT IN THE PAST, THE FMLN HAS USED THE PROPOSALS BY (JOSE NAPOLEON) DUARTE'S GOVERNMENT AND MY OWN FOR TACTICAL REASONS."}, {"text": "IT HAS NOT BEEN THE GOVERNMENTS."}, {"text": "I BELIEVE THAT THE FMLN MUST UNDERSTAND AND BE PRESSURED TO REALLY SEARCH FOR A POLITICAL SOLUTION."}, {"text": "(END RECORDING) ALSO TODAY, THE UN SECRETARY GENERAL AUTHORIZED A SPOKESMAN TO ANNOUNCE THAT TALKS BETWEEN THE GOVERNMENT AND FMLN WILL BE RENEWED ON 16 MAY."}, {"text": "THE PANORAMA THAT SURROUNDS THIS NEW ENCOUNTER, HOWEVER, PRESENTS AN ENTIRELY DIFFERENT PATTERN FROM MEETINGS IN THE PAST, BECAUSE BOTH SECTORS HAVE MET WITH POLITICAL PARTIES REPRESENTED AT THE (WORD INDISTINCT)."}, {"text": "FURTHERMORE, ALTHOUGH THE GOVERNMENT HAS NOT DONE THE SAME WITH THE COUNTRY'S SOCIAL FORCES, THE REBELS WILL TRY TO DO SO THIS WEEK."}, {"text": "UNDOUBTEDLY, THE RESULTS THAT COULD BE OBTAINED FROM THE DIALOGUE COULD BE MUCH MORE IMPORTANT THAN THOSE OBTAINED DURING PAST NEGOTIATIONS, BECAUSE ALMOST ALL THE SECTORS THAT HAVE BECOME INVOLVED, DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, IN THE NEGOTIATING DEMAND THAT THE AGREEMENTS ATTAINED BE BASED ON INTERNAL COOPERATION."}], "template": {"message_id": "TST3-MUC4-0098", "message_template": {"sentences": [{"text": "OFFICIAL SOURCES HAVE REPORTED BLACKOUTS IN MANY PARTS OF THE COUNTRY BECAUSE OF GUERRILLAS SABOTAGING THE ELECTRIC POWER SYSTEM DURING THE NIGHT OF 31 MAY AND THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO A MILITARY BULLETIN, THE GUERRILLAS DESTROYED 12 ELECTRIC POLES AND 2 POWER PYLONS IN THE CENTRAL AND WESTERN PARTS OF THE COUNTRY IN LESS THAN 12 HOURS."}, {"text": "IN THE EASTERN PART OF THE COUNTRY, THE LEMPA RIVER HYDROELECTRIC EXECUTIVE COMMISSION (CEL) REPORTED THAT ONE OF THE COUNTRY'S MAIN POWER LINES WAS OUT OF SERVICE ON THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE BECAUSE A NUMBER OF PYLONS WERE DESTROYED."}, {"text": "THE ARMED FORCES PRESS COMMITTEE (COPREFA) REPORTED THAT ON THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE GUERRILLAS, USING MORTARS AND RIFLES, ATTACKED A CEL SUB-STATION IN THE NATIVIDAD CANTON IN THE WESTERN DEPARTMENT OF SANTA ANA."}, {"text": "THERE WERE NO CASUALTIES, BUT THE GUERRILLAS HAD DAMAGED A TRANSFORMER."}, {"text": "ON THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE, THERE WAS A BLACKOUT THROUGHOUT MOST OF THE CAPITAL CAUSED BY URBAN COMMANDOS OF THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN)."}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLAS HAVE INCREASED THEIR ACTIVITY ON THE FIRST ANNIVERSARY OF PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI'S GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "CRISTINAI IS SCHEDULED TO ADDRESS THE NATION ON 1 JUNE TO COMMENT ON HIS FIRST YEAR IN OFFICE."}, {"text": "THE ARMY HAS INCREASED ITS PATROLS AIDED BY HELICOPTERS THAT OVERFLY THE CAPITAL CITY."}, {"text": "COPREFA REPORTED THAT ONE SOLDIER WAS KILLED AND SEVEN WERE WOUNDED ON 1 JUNE DURING AN AMBUSH OF A MILITARY CONVOY NEAR TEXISTEPEQUE, WEST OF SAN SALVADOR."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO COPREFA, ANOTHER SOLDIER WAS WOUNDED IN A GUERRILLA AMBUSH AGAINST THE ELITE BRACAMONTE BATTALION ON A HIGHWAY IN CENTRAL EL SALVADOR."}], {"sentences": [{"text": "OFFICIAL SOURCES HAVE REPORTED BLACKOUTS IN MANY PARTS OF THE COUNTRY BECAUSE OF GUERRILLAS SABOTAGING THE ELECTRIC POWER SYSTEM DURING THE NIGHT OF 31 MAY AND THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO A MILITARY BULLETIN, THE GUERRILLAS DESTROYED 12 ELECTRIC POLES AND 2 POWER PYLONS IN THE CENTRAL AND WESTERN PARTS OF THE COUNTRY IN LESS THAN 12 HOURS."}, {"text": "IN THE EASTERN PART OF THE COUNTRY, THE LEMPA RIVER HYDROELECTRIC EXECUTIVE COMMISSION (CEL) REPORTED THAT ONE OF THE COUNTRY'S MAIN POWER LINES WAS OUT OF SERVICE ON THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE BECAUSE A NUMBER OF PYLONS WERE DESTROYED."}, {"text": "THE ARMED FORCES PRESS COMMITTEE (COPREFA) REPORTED THAT ON THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE GUERRILLAS, USING MORTARS AND RIFLES, ATTACKED A CEL SUB-STATION IN THE NATIVIDAD CANTON IN THE WESTERN DEPARTMENT OF SANTA ANA."}, {"text": "THERE WERE NO CASUALTIES, BUT THE GUERRILLAS HAD DAMAGED A TRANSFORMER."}, {"text": "ON THE MORNING OF 1 JUNE, THERE WAS A BLACKOUT THROUGHOUT MOST OF THE CAPITAL CAUSED BY URBAN COMMANDOS OF THE FARABUNDO MARTI NATIONAL LIBERATION FRONT (FMLN)."}, {"text": "THE GUERRILLAS HAVE INCREASED THEIR ACTIVITY ON THE FIRST ANNIVERSARY OF PRESIDENT ALFREDO CRISTIANI'S GOVERNMENT."}, {"text": "CRISTINAI IS SCHEDULED TO ADDRESS THE NATION ON 1 JUNE TO COMMENT ON HIS FIRST YEAR IN OFFICE."}, {"text": "THE ARMY HAS INCREASED ITS PATROLS AIDED BY HELICOPTERS THAT OVERFLY THE CAPITAL CITY."}, {"text": "COPREFA REPORTED THAT ONE SOLDIER WAS KILLED AND SEVEN WERE WOUNDED ON 1 JUNE DURING AN AMBUSH OF A MILITARY CONVOY NEAR TEXISTEPEQUE, WEST OF SAN SALVADOR."}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO COPREFA, ANOTHER SOLDIER WAS WOUNDED IN A GUERRILLA AMBUSH AGAINST THE ELITE BRACAMONTE BATTALION ON A HIGHWAY IN CENTRAL EL SALVADOR."}],
